23 int4 RuleEarlyRemoval::applyOp(PcodeOp *op,Funcdata &data)
24 
25 {
26  Varnode *vn;
27 
28  if (op->isCall()) return 0; // Functions automatically consumed
29  if (op->isIndirectSource()) return 0;
30  vn = op->getOut();
31  if (vn == (Varnode *)0) return 0;
32  // if (vn->isPersist()) return 0;
33  if (!vn->hasNoDescend()) return 0;
34  if (vn->isAutoLive()) return 0;
35  AddrSpace *spc = vn->getSpace();
36  if (spc->doesDeadcode())
37  if (!data.deadRemovalAllowedSeen(spc))
38  return 0;
39 
40  data.opDestroy(op); // Get rid of unused op
41  return 1;
42 }

80 Varnode *RuleCollectTerms::getMultCoeff(Varnode *vn,uintb &coef)
81 
82 {
83  PcodeOp *testop;
84  if (!vn->isWritten()) {
85  coef = 1;
86  return vn;
87  }
88  testop = vn->getDef();
89  if ((testop->code() != CPUI_INT_MULT)||(!testop->getIn(1)->isConstant())) {
90  coef = 1;
91  return vn;
92  }
93  coef = testop->getIn(1)->getOffset();
94  return testop->getIn(0);
95 }

104 int4 RuleCollectTerms::doDistribute(Funcdata &data,PcodeOp *op)
105 
106 {
107  Varnode *newvn1,*newvn2,*newcvn;
108  PcodeOp *newop1, *newop2;
109  PcodeOp *addop = op->getIn(0)->getDef();
110  Varnode *vn0 = addop->getIn(0);
111  Varnode *vn1 = addop->getIn(1);
112  if ((vn0->isFree())&&(!vn0->isConstant())) return 0;
113  if ((vn1->isFree())&&(!vn1->isConstant())) return 0;
114  uintb coeff = op->getIn(1)->getOffset();
115  int4 size = op->getOut()->getSize();
116  // Do distribution
117  newop1 = data.newOp(2,op->getAddr());
118  data.opSetOpcode(newop1,CPUI_INT_MULT);
119  newvn1 = data.newUniqueOut(size,newop1);
120 
121  newop2 = data.newOp(2,op->getAddr());
122  data.opSetOpcode(newop2,CPUI_INT_MULT);
123  newvn2 = data.newUniqueOut(size,newop2);
124 
125  if (vn0->isConstant())
126  data.opSetInput(newop1, data.newConstant(size,vn0->getOffset()),0);
127  else
128  data.opSetInput(newop1, vn0, 0); // To first input of original add
129  newcvn = data.newConstant(size,coeff);
130  data.opSetInput(newop1, newcvn, 1);
131  data.opInsertBefore(newop1, op);
132 
133  if (vn1->isConstant())
134  data.opSetInput(newop2, data.newConstant(size,vn1->getOffset()),0);
135  else
136  data.opSetInput(newop2, vn1, 0); // To second input of original add
137  newcvn = data.newConstant(size,coeff);
138  data.opSetInput(newop2, newcvn, 1);
139  data.opInsertBefore(newop2, op);
140 
141  data.opSetInput( op, newvn1, 0); // new ADD's inputs are outputs of new MULTs
142  data.opSetInput( op, newvn2, 1);
143  data.opSetOpcode(op, CPUI_INT_ADD);
144 
145  return 1;
146 }

156 int4 RuleCollectTerms::applyOp(PcodeOp *op,Funcdata &data)
157 
158 {
159  PcodeOp *nextop = op->getOut()->loneDescend();
160  // Do we have the root of an ADD tree
161  if ((nextop!=(PcodeOp *)0)&&(nextop->code()==CPUI_INT_ADD)) return 0;
162 
163  TermOrder termorder(op);
164  termorder.collect(); // Collect additive terms in the expression
165  termorder.sortTerms(); // Sort them based on termorder
166  Varnode *vn1,*vn2;
167  uintb coef1,coef2;
168  const vector<PcodeOpEdge *> &order( termorder.getSort() );
169  int4 i=0;
170 
171  if (!order[0]->getVarnode()->isConstant()) {
172  for(i=1;i<order.size();++i) {
173  vn1 = order[i-1]->getVarnode();
174  vn2 = order[i]->getVarnode();
175  if (vn2->isConstant()) break;
176  vn1 = getMultCoeff(vn1,coef1);
177  vn2 = getMultCoeff(vn2,coef2);
178  if (vn1 == vn2) { // Terms that can be combined
179  if (order[i-1]->getMultiplier() != (PcodeOp *)0)
180  return doDistribute(data,order[i-1]->getMultiplier());
181  if (order[i]->getMultiplier() != (PcodeOp *)0)
182  return doDistribute(data,order[i]->getMultiplier());
183  coef1 = (coef1 + coef2) & calc_mask(vn1->getSize()); // The new coefficient
184  Varnode *newcoeff = data.newConstant(vn1->getSize(),coef1);
185  Varnode *zerocoeff = data.newConstant(vn1->getSize(),0);
186  data.opSetInput(order[i-1]->getOp(),zerocoeff,order[i-1]->getSlot());
187  if (coef1 == 0)
188  data.opSetInput(order[i]->getOp(),newcoeff,order[i]->getSlot());
189  else {
190  nextop = data.newOp(2,order[i]->getOp()->getAddr());
191  vn2 = data.newUniqueOut(vn1->getSize(),nextop);
192  data.opSetOpcode(nextop,CPUI_INT_MULT);
193  data.opSetInput(nextop,vn1,0);
194  data.opSetInput(nextop,newcoeff,1);
195  data.opInsertBefore(nextop,order[i]->getOp());
196  data.opSetInput(order[i]->getOp(),vn2,order[i]->getSlot());
197  }
198  return 1;
199  }
200  }
201  }
202  coef1 = 0;
203  int4 nonzerocount = 0; // Count non-zero constants
204  int4 lastconst=0;
205  for(int4 j=order.size()-1;j>=i;--j) {
206  if (order[j]->getMultiplier() != (PcodeOp *)0) continue;
207  vn1 = order[j]->getVarnode();
208  uintb val = vn1->getOffset();
209  if (val != 0) {
210  nonzerocount += 1;
211  coef1 += val; // Sum up all the constants
212  lastconst = j;
213  }
214  }
215  if (nonzerocount <= 1) return 0; // Must sum at least two things
216  vn1 = order[lastconst]->getVarnode();
217  coef1 &= calc_mask(vn1->getSize());
218  // Lump all the non-zero constants into one varnode
219  for(int4 j=lastconst+1;j<order.size();++j)
220  if (order[j]->getMultiplier() == (PcodeOp *)0)
221  data.opSetInput(order[j]->getOp(),data.newConstant(vn1->getSize(),0),order[j]->getSlot());
222  data.opSetInput(order[lastconst]->getOp(),data.newConstant(vn1->getSize(),coef1),order[lastconst]->getSlot());
223 
224  return 1;
225 }

236 int4 RuleSelectCse::applyOp(PcodeOp *op,Funcdata &data)
237 
238 {
239  Varnode *vn = op->getIn(0);
240  list<PcodeOp *>::const_iterator iter;
241  OpCode opc = op->code();
242  PcodeOp *otherop;
243  uintm hash;
244  vector< pair<uintm,PcodeOp *> > list;
245  vector<Varnode *> vlist;
246 
247  for(iter=vn->beginDescend();iter!=vn->endDescend();++iter) {
248  otherop = *iter;
249  if (otherop->code() != opc) continue;
250  hash = otherop->getCseHash();
251  if (hash == 0) continue;
252  list.push_back(pair<uintm,PcodeOp *>(hash,otherop));
253  }
254  if (list.size()<=1) return 0;
255  cseEliminateList(data,list,vlist);
256  if (vlist.empty()) return 0;
257  return 1;
258 }

268 int4 RulePiece2Zext::applyOp(PcodeOp *op,Funcdata &data)
269 
270 {
271  Varnode *constvn;
272 
273  constvn = op->getIn(0); // Constant must be most significant bits
274  if (!constvn->isConstant()) return 0; // Must append with constant
275  if (constvn->getOffset() != 0) return 0; // of value 0
276  data.opRemoveInput(op,0); // Remove the constant
277  data.opSetOpcode(op,CPUI_INT_ZEXT);
278  return 1;
279 }

289 int4 RulePiece2Sext::applyOp(PcodeOp *op,Funcdata &data)
290 
291 {
292  Varnode *shiftout,*x;
293  PcodeOp *shiftop;
294 
295  shiftout = op->getIn(0);
296  if (!shiftout->isWritten()) return 0;
297  shiftop = shiftout->getDef();
298  if (shiftop->code() != CPUI_INT_SRIGHT) return 0;
299  if (!shiftop->getIn(1)->isConstant()) return 0;
300  int4 n = shiftop->getIn(1)->getOffset();
301  x = shiftop->getIn(0);
302  if (x != op->getIn(1)) return 0;
303  if (n != 8*x->getSize() -1) return 0;
304 
305  data.opRemoveInput(op,0);
306  data.opSetOpcode(op,CPUI_INT_SEXT);
307  return 1;
308 }

333 int4 RuleOrMask::applyOp(PcodeOp *op,Funcdata &data)
334 
335 {
336  int4 size = op->getOut()->getSize();
337  if (size > sizeof(uintb)) return 0; // FIXME: uintb should be arbitrary precision
338  Varnode *constvn;
339 
340  constvn = op->getIn(1);
341  if (!constvn->isConstant()) return 0;
342  uintb val = constvn->getOffset();
343  uintb mask = calc_mask(size);
344  if ((val&mask) != mask) return 0;
345  data.opSetOpcode(op,CPUI_COPY);
346  data.opSetInput(op,constvn,0);
347  data.opRemoveInput(op,1);
348  return 1;
349 }

358 
359 int4 RuleAndMask::applyOp(PcodeOp *op,Funcdata &data)
360 
361 {
362  uintb mask1,mask2,andmask;
363  int4 size = op->getOut()->getSize();
364  Varnode *vn;
365 
366  if (size > sizeof(uintb)) return 0; // FIXME: uintb should be arbitrary precision
367  mask1 = op->getIn(0)->getNZMask();
368  if (mask1 == 0)
369  andmask = 0;
370  else {
371  mask2 = op->getIn(1)->getNZMask();
372  andmask = mask1 & mask2;
373  }
374 
375  if (andmask==0) // Result of AND is always zero
376  vn = data.newConstant( size, 0);
377  else if ((andmask & op->getOut()->getConsume())==0)
378  vn = data.newConstant( size, 0);
379  else if (andmask == mask1) {
380  if (!op->getIn(1)->isConstant()) return 0;
381  vn = op->getIn(0); // Result of AND is equal to input(0)
382  }
383  else
384  return 0;
385  if (!vn->isHeritageKnown()) return 0;
386 
387  data.opSetOpcode(op,CPUI_COPY);
388  data.opRemoveInput(op,1);
389  data.opSetInput(op,vn,0);
390  return 1;
391 }

404 int4 RuleOrCollapse::applyOp(PcodeOp *op,Funcdata &data)
405 
406 {
407  uintb val,mask;
408  int4 size = op->getOut()->getSize();
409  Varnode *vn;
410 
411  vn = op->getIn(1);
412  if (!vn->isConstant()) return 0;
413  if (size > sizeof(uintb)) return 0; // FIXME: uintb should be arbitrary precision
414  mask = op->getIn(0)->getNZMask();
415  val = vn->getOffset();
416  if ((mask | val)!=val) return 0; // first param may turn on other bits
417 
418  data.opSetOpcode(op,CPUI_COPY);
419  data.opRemoveInput(op,0);
420  return 1;
421 }

433 int4 RuleAndOrLump::applyOp(PcodeOp *op,Funcdata &data)
434 
435 {
436  OpCode opc;
437  Varnode *vn1,*basevn;
438  PcodeOp *op2;
439 
440  opc = op->code();
441  if (!op->getIn(1)->isConstant()) return 0;
442  vn1 = op->getIn(0);
443  if (!vn1->isWritten()) return 0;
444  op2 = vn1->getDef();
445  if (op2->code() != opc) return 0; // Must be same op
446  if (!op2->getIn(1)->isConstant()) return 0;
447  basevn = op2->getIn(0);
448  if (basevn->isFree()) return 0;
449 
450  uintb val = op->getIn(1)->getOffset();
451  uintb val2 = op2->getIn(1)->getOffset();
452  if (opc == CPUI_INT_AND)
453  val &= val2;
454  else if (opc == CPUI_INT_OR)
455  val |= val2;
456  else if (opc == CPUI_INT_XOR)
457  val ^= val2;
458 
459  data.opSetInput(op,basevn,0);
460  data.opSetInput(op,data.newConstant(basevn->getSize(),val),1);
461  return 1;
462 }

471 
472 int4 RuleNegateIdentity::applyOp(PcodeOp *op,Funcdata &data)
473 
474 {
475  Varnode *vn = op->getIn(0);
476  Varnode *outVn = op->getOut();
477  list<PcodeOp *>::const_iterator iter;
478  for(iter=outVn->beginDescend();iter!=outVn->endDescend();++iter) {
479  PcodeOp *logicOp = *iter;
480  OpCode opc = logicOp->code();
481  if (opc != CPUI_INT_AND && opc != CPUI_INT_OR && opc != CPUI_INT_XOR)
482  continue;
483  int4 slot = logicOp->getSlot(outVn);
484  if (logicOp->getIn(1-slot) != vn) continue;
485  uintb value = 0;
486  if (opc != CPUI_INT_AND)
487  value = calc_mask(vn->getSize());
488  data.opSetInput(logicOp,data.newConstant(vn->getSize(),value),0);
489  data.opRemoveInput(logicOp,1);
490  data.opSetOpcode(logicOp,CPUI_COPY);
491  return 1;
492  }
493  return 0;
494 }

501 void RuleShiftBitops::getOpList(vector<uint4> &oplist) const
502 
503 {
504  oplist.push_back(CPUI_INT_LEFT);
505  oplist.push_back(CPUI_INT_RIGHT);
506  oplist.push_back(CPUI_SUBPIECE);
507  oplist.push_back(CPUI_INT_MULT);
508 }
509 
510 int4 RuleShiftBitops::applyOp(PcodeOp *op,Funcdata &data)
511 
512 {
513  Varnode *constvn = op->getIn(1);
514  if (!constvn->isConstant()) return 0; // Must be a constant shift
515  Varnode *vn = op->getIn(0);
516  if (!vn->isWritten()) return 0;
517  int4 sa;
518  bool leftshift;
519 
520  switch(op->code()) {
521  case CPUI_INT_LEFT:
522  sa = (int4) constvn->getOffset();
523  leftshift = true;
524  break;
525  case CPUI_INT_RIGHT:
526  sa = (int4) constvn->getOffset();
527  leftshift = false;
528  break;
529  case CPUI_SUBPIECE:
530  sa = (int4) constvn->getOffset();
531  sa = sa * 8;
532  leftshift = false;
533  break;
534  case CPUI_INT_MULT:
535  sa = leastsigbit_set(constvn->getOffset());
536  if (sa == -1) return 0;
537  leftshift = true;
538  break;
539  default:
540  return 0; // Never reaches here
541  }
542 
543  PcodeOp *bitop = vn->getDef();
544  switch(bitop->code()) {
545  case CPUI_INT_AND:
546  case CPUI_INT_OR:
547  case CPUI_INT_XOR:
548  break;
549  case CPUI_INT_MULT:
550  case CPUI_INT_ADD:
551  if (!leftshift) return 0;
552  break;
553  default:
554  return 0;
555  }
556 
557  int4 i;
558  for(i=0;i<bitop->numInput();++i) {
559  uintb nzm = bitop->getIn(i)->getNZMask();
560  uintb mask = calc_mask(op->getOut()->getSize());
561  if (leftshift)
562  nzm = pcode_left(nzm,sa);
563  else
564  nzm = pcode_right(nzm,sa);
565  if ((nzm&mask)==(uintb)0) break;
566  }
567  if (i==bitop->numInput()) return 0;
568  switch(bitop->code()) {
569  case CPUI_INT_MULT:
570  case CPUI_INT_AND:
571  vn = data.newConstant(vn->getSize(),0);
572  data.opSetInput(op,vn,0); // Result will be zero
573  break;
574  case CPUI_INT_ADD:
575  case CPUI_INT_XOR:
576  case CPUI_INT_OR:
577  vn = bitop->getIn(1-i);
578  if (!vn->isHeritageKnown()) return 0;
579  data.opSetInput(op,vn,0);
580  break;
581  default:
582  break;
583  }
584  return 1;
585 }

616 int4 RuleEquality::applyOp(PcodeOp *op,Funcdata &data)
617 
618 {
619  Varnode *vn;
620  if (!functionalEquality(op->getIn(0),op->getIn(1)))
621  return 0;
622 
623  data.opSetOpcode(op,CPUI_COPY);
624  data.opRemoveInput(op,1);
625  vn = data.newConstant(1,(op->code()==CPUI_INT_EQUAL) ? 1: 0);
626  data.opSetInput(op,vn,0);
627  return 1;
628 }

635 void RuleTermOrder::getOpList(vector<uint4> &oplist) const
636 
637 {
638  // FIXME: All the commutative ops
639  // Use the TypeOp::commutative function
640  uint4 list[]={ CPUI_INT_EQUAL, CPUI_INT_NOTEQUAL, CPUI_INT_ADD, CPUI_INT_CARRY,
641  CPUI_INT_SCARRY, CPUI_INT_XOR, CPUI_INT_AND, CPUI_INT_OR,
642  CPUI_INT_MULT, CPUI_BOOL_XOR, CPUI_BOOL_AND, CPUI_BOOL_OR,
643  CPUI_FLOAT_EQUAL, CPUI_FLOAT_NOTEQUAL, CPUI_FLOAT_ADD,
644  CPUI_FLOAT_MULT };
645  oplist.insert(oplist.end(),list,list+16);

648 int4 RuleTermOrder::applyOp(PcodeOp *op,Funcdata &data)
649 
650 {
651  Varnode *vn1 = op->getIn(0);
652  Varnode *vn2 = op->getIn(1);
653 
654  if (vn1->isConstant() && (!vn2->isConstant())) {
655  data.opSwapInput(op,0,1); // Reverse the order of the terms
656  return 1;
657  }
658  return 0;
659 }

668 void RulePullsubMulti::minMaxUse(Varnode *vn,int4 &maxByte,int4 &minByte)
669 
670 {
671  list<PcodeOp *>::const_iterator iter,enditer;
672  enditer = vn->endDescend();
673 
674  int4 inSize = vn->getSize();
675  maxByte = -1;
676  minByte = inSize;
677  for(iter=vn->beginDescend();iter!=enditer;++iter) {
678  PcodeOp *op = *iter;
679  OpCode opc = op->code();
680  if (opc == CPUI_SUBPIECE) {
681  int4 min = (int4)op->getIn(1)->getOffset();
682  int4 max = min + op->getOut()->getSize() - 1;
683  if (min < minByte)
684  minByte = min;
685  if (max > maxByte)
686  maxByte = max;
687  }
688  else { // By default assume all bytes are used
689  maxByte = inSize - 1;
690  minByte = 0;
691  return;
692  }
693  }
694 }
695 
704 void RulePullsubMulti::replaceDescendants(Varnode *origVn,Varnode *newVn,int4 maxByte,int4 minByte,Funcdata &data)
705 
706 {
707  list<PcodeOp *>::const_iterator iter,enditer;
708  iter = origVn->beginDescend();
709  enditer = origVn->endDescend();
710  while(iter != enditer) {
711  PcodeOp *op = *iter;
712  ++iter;
713  if (op->code() == CPUI_SUBPIECE) {
714  int4 truncAmount = (int4)op->getIn(1)->getOffset();
715  int4 outSize = op->getOut()->getSize();
716  data.opSetInput(op,newVn,0);
717  if (newVn->getSize() == outSize) {
718  if (truncAmount != minByte)
719  throw LowlevelError("Could not perform -replaceDescendants-");
720  data.opSetOpcode(op, CPUI_COPY);
721  data.opRemoveInput(op, 1);
722  }
723  else if (newVn->getSize() > outSize) {
724  int4 newTrunc = truncAmount - minByte;
725  if (newTrunc < 0)
726  throw LowlevelError("Could not perform -replaceDescendants-");
727  if (newTrunc != truncAmount) {
728  data.opSetInput(op, data.newConstant(4, (uintb)newTrunc), 1);
729  }
730  }
731  else
732  throw LowlevelError("Could not perform -replaceDescendants-");
733  }
734  else
735  throw LowlevelError("Could not perform -replaceDescendants-");
736  }
737 }
738 
743 bool RulePullsubMulti::acceptableSize(int4 size)
744 
745 {
746  if (size == 0) return false;
747  if (size >= 8) return true;
748  if (size == 1 || size == 2 || size == 4 || size == 8)
749  return true;
750  return false;
751 }
752 
761 Varnode *RulePullsubMulti::buildSubpiece(Varnode *basevn,uint4 outsize,uint4 shift,Funcdata &data)
762 
763 {
764  Address newaddr;
765  PcodeOp *new_op;
766  Varnode *outvn;
767 
768  if (basevn->isInput()) {
769  BlockBasic *bb = (BlockBasic *)data.getBasicBlocks().getBlock(0);
770  newaddr = bb->getStart();
771  }
772  else {
773  if (!basevn->isWritten()) throw LowlevelError("Undefined pullsub");
774  newaddr = basevn->getDef()->getAddr();
775  }
776  Address smalladdr1;
777  bool usetmp = false;
778  if (basevn->getAddr().isJoin()) {
779  usetmp = true;
780  JoinRecord *joinrec = data.getArch()->findJoin(basevn->getOffset());
781  if (joinrec->numPieces() > 1) { // If only 1 piece (float extension) automatically use unique
782  uint4 skipleft = shift;
783  for(int4 i=joinrec->numPieces()-1;i>=0;--i) { // Move from least significant to most
784  const VarnodeData &vdata(joinrec->getPiece(i));
785  if (skipleft >= vdata.size) {
786  skipleft -= vdata.size;
787  }
788  else {
789  if (skipleft + outsize > vdata.size)
790  break;
791  if (vdata.space->isBigEndian())
792  smalladdr1 = vdata.getAddr() + (vdata.size - (outsize + skipleft));
793  else
794  smalladdr1 = vdata.getAddr() + skipleft;
795  usetmp = false;
796  break;
797  }
798  }
799  }
800  }
801  else {
802  if (!basevn->getSpace()->isBigEndian())
803  smalladdr1 = basevn->getAddr()+shift;
804  else
805  smalladdr1 = basevn->getAddr()+(basevn->getSize()-(shift+outsize));
806  }
807  // Build new subpiece near definition of basevn
808  new_op = data.newOp(2,newaddr);
809  data.opSetOpcode(new_op,CPUI_SUBPIECE);
810  if (usetmp)
811  outvn = data.newUniqueOut(outsize,new_op);
812  else
813  outvn = data.newVarnodeOut(outsize,smalladdr1,new_op);
814  data.opSetInput(new_op,basevn,0);
815  data.opSetInput(new_op,data.newConstant(4,shift),1);
816 
817  if (basevn->isInput())
818  data.opInsertBegin(new_op,(BlockBasic *)data.getBasicBlocks().getBlock(0));
819  else
820  data.opInsertAfter(new_op,basevn->getDef());
821  return outvn;
822 }
823 
832 Varnode *RulePullsubMulti::findSubpiece(Varnode *basevn,uint4 outsize,uint4 shift)
833 
834 {
835  list<PcodeOp *>::const_iterator iter;
836  PcodeOp *prevop;
837 
838  for(iter=basevn->beginDescend();iter!=basevn->endDescend();++iter) {
839  prevop = *iter;
840  if (prevop->code() != CPUI_SUBPIECE) continue; // Find previous SUBPIECE
841  // Make sure output is defined in same block as vn_piece
842  if (basevn->isInput() && (prevop->getParent()->getIndex()!=0)) continue;
843  if (!basevn->isWritten()) continue;
844  if (basevn->getDef()->getParent() != prevop->getParent()) continue;
845  // Make sure subpiece matches form
846  if ((prevop->getIn(0) == basevn)&&
847  (prevop->getOut()->getSize() == outsize)&&
848  (prevop->getIn(1)->getOffset()==shift)) {
849  return prevop->getOut();
850  }
851  }
852  return (Varnode *)0;
853 }
854 
857 void RulePullsubMulti::getOpList(vector<uint4> &oplist) const
858 
859 {
860  oplist.push_back(CPUI_SUBPIECE);
861 }
862 
863 int4 RulePullsubMulti::applyOp(PcodeOp *op,Funcdata &data)
864 
865 {
866  int4 maxByte,minByte,newSize;
867 
868  Varnode *vn = op->getIn(0);
869  if (!vn->isWritten()) return 0;
870  PcodeOp *mult = vn->getDef();
871  if (mult->code()!=CPUI_MULTIEQUAL) return 0;
872  // We only pull up, do not pull "down" to bottom of loop
873  if (mult->getParent()->hasLoopIn()) return 0;
874  minMaxUse(vn, maxByte, minByte); // Figure out what part of -vn- is used
875  newSize = maxByte - minByte + 1;
876  if (maxByte < minByte || (newSize >= vn->getSize()))
877  return 0; // If all or none is getting used, nothing to do
878  if (!acceptableSize(newSize)) return 0;
879  Varnode *outvn = op->getOut();
880  if (outvn->isPrecisLo()||outvn->isPrecisHi()) return 0; // Don't pull apart a double precision object
881 
882  Address smalladdr2;
883  if (!vn->getSpace()->isBigEndian())
884  smalladdr2 = vn->getAddr()+minByte;
885  else
886  smalladdr2 = vn->getAddr()+(vn->getSize()-maxByte-1);
887 
888  vector<Varnode *> params;
889  int4 branches = mult->numInput();
890 
891  for(int4 i=0;i<branches;++i) {
892  Varnode *vn_piece = mult->getIn(i);
893  // We have to be wary of exponential splittings here, do not pull the SUBPIECE
894  // up the MULTIEQUAL if another related SUBPIECE has already been pulled
895  // Search for a previous SUBPIECE
896  Varnode *vn_sub = findSubpiece(vn_piece,newSize,minByte);
897  if (vn_sub == (Varnode *)0) // Couldn't find previous subpieceing
898  vn_sub = buildSubpiece(vn_piece,newSize,minByte,data);
899  params.push_back(vn_sub);
900  }
901  // Build new multiequal near original multiequal
902  PcodeOp *new_multi = data.newOp(params.size(),mult->getAddr());
903  Varnode *new_vn = data.newVarnodeOut(newSize,smalladdr2,new_multi);
904  data.opSetOpcode(new_multi,CPUI_MULTIEQUAL);
905  data.opSetAllInput(new_multi,params);
906  data.opInsertBegin(new_multi,mult->getParent());
907 
908  replaceDescendants(vn, new_vn, maxByte, minByte, data);
909  return 1;
910 }
911 
914 void RulePullsubIndirect::getOpList(vector<uint4> &oplist) const
915 
916 {
917  oplist.push_back(CPUI_SUBPIECE);
918 }
919 
920 int4 RulePullsubIndirect::applyOp(PcodeOp *op,Funcdata &data)
921 
922 {
923  int4 maxByte,minByte,newSize;
924 
925  Varnode *vn = op->getIn(0);
926  if (!vn->isWritten()) return 0;
927  PcodeOp *indir = vn->getDef();
928  if (indir->code()!=CPUI_INDIRECT) return 0;
929  if (indir->getIn(1)->getSpace()->getType()!=IPTR_IOP) return 0;
930 
931  PcodeOp *targ_op = PcodeOp::getOpFromConst(indir->getIn(1)->getAddr());
932  if (targ_op->isDead()) return 0;
933  if (vn->isAddrForce()) return 0;
934  RulePullsubMulti::minMaxUse(vn, maxByte, minByte);
935  newSize = maxByte - minByte + 1;
936  if (maxByte < minByte || (newSize >= vn->getSize()))
937  return 0;
938  if (!RulePullsubMulti::acceptableSize(newSize)) return 0;
939  Varnode *outvn = op->getOut();
940  if (outvn->isPrecisLo()||outvn->isPrecisHi()) return 0; // Don't pull apart double precision object
941 
942  Varnode *small2;
943  Address smalladdr2;
944  PcodeOp *new_ind;
945 
946  if (!vn->getSpace()->isBigEndian())
947  smalladdr2 = vn->getAddr()+minByte;
948  else
949  smalladdr2 = vn->getAddr()+(vn->getSize()-maxByte-1);
950 
951  if (indir->isIndirectCreation()) {
952  bool possibleout = !indir->getIn(0)->isIndirectZero();
953  new_ind = data.newIndirectCreation(targ_op,smalladdr2,newSize,possibleout);
954  small2 = new_ind->getOut();
955  }
956  else {
957  Varnode *basevn = indir->getIn(0);
958  Varnode *small1 = RulePullsubMulti::findSubpiece(basevn,newSize,op->getIn(1)->getOffset());
959  if (small1 == (Varnode *)0)
960  small1 = RulePullsubMulti::buildSubpiece(basevn,newSize,op->getIn(1)->getOffset(),data);
961  // Create new indirect near original indirect
962  new_ind = data.newOp(2,indir->getAddr());
963  data.opSetOpcode(new_ind,CPUI_INDIRECT);
964  small2 = data.newVarnodeOut(newSize,smalladdr2,new_ind);
965  data.opSetInput(new_ind,small1,0);
966  data.opSetInput(new_ind,data.newVarnodeIop(targ_op),1);
967  data.opInsertBefore(new_ind,indir);
968  }
969 
970  RulePullsubMulti::replaceDescendants(vn, small2, maxByte, minByte, data);
971  return 1;
972 }
973 
984 PcodeOp *RulePushMulti::findSubstitute(Varnode *in1,Varnode *in2,BlockBasic *bb,PcodeOp *earliest)
985 
986 {
987  list<PcodeOp *>::const_iterator iter,enditer;
988  iter = in1->beginDescend();
989  enditer = in1->endDescend();
990  while(iter != enditer) {
991  PcodeOp *op = *iter;
992  ++iter;
993  if (op->getParent() != bb) continue;
994  if (op->code() != CPUI_MULTIEQUAL) continue;
995  if (op->getIn(0) != in1) continue;
996  if (op->getIn(1) != in2) continue;
997  return op;
998  }
999  if (in1 == in2) return (PcodeOp *)0;
1000  Varnode *buf1[2];
1001  Varnode *buf2[2];
1002  if (0!=functionalEqualityLevel(in1,in2,buf1,buf2)) return (PcodeOp *)0;
1003  PcodeOp *op1 = in1->getDef(); // in1 and in2 must be written to not be equal and pass functional equality test
1004  PcodeOp *op2 = in2->getDef();
1005  for(int4 i=0;i<op1->numInput();++i) {
1006  Varnode *vn = op1->getIn(i);
1007  if (vn->isConstant()) continue;
1008  if (vn == op2->getIn(i)) // Find matching inputs to op1 and op2,
1009  return cseFindInBlock(op1,vn,bb,earliest); // search for cse of op1 in bb
1010  }
1011 
1012  return (PcodeOp *)0;
1013 }
1014 
1021 void RulePushMulti::getOpList(vector<uint4> &oplist) const
1022 
1023 {
1024  oplist.push_back(CPUI_MULTIEQUAL);
1025 }
1026 
1027 int4 RulePushMulti::applyOp(PcodeOp *op,Funcdata &data)
1028 
1029 {
1030  if (op->numInput() != 2) return 0;
1031 
1032  Varnode *in1 = op->getIn(0);
1033  Varnode *in2 = op->getIn(1);
1034 
1035  if (!in1->isWritten()) return 0;
1036  if (!in2->isWritten()) return 0;
1037  if (in1->isSpacebase()) return 0;
1038  if (in2->isSpacebase()) return 0;
1039  Varnode *buf1[2];
1040  Varnode *buf2[2];
1041  int4 res = functionalEqualityLevel(in1,in2,buf1,buf2);
1042  if (res < 0) return 0;
1043  if (res > 1) return 0;
1044  PcodeOp *op1 = in1->getDef();
1045  if (op1->code() == CPUI_SUBPIECE) return 0; // SUBPIECE is pulled not pushed
1046 
1047  BlockBasic *bl = op->getParent();
1048  PcodeOp *earliest = earliestUseInBlock(op->getOut(),bl);
1049  if (op1->code() == CPUI_COPY) { // Special case of MERGE of 2 shadowing varnodes
1050  if (res==0) return 0;
1051  PcodeOp *substitute = findSubstitute(buf1[0],buf2[0],bl,earliest);
1052  if (substitute == (PcodeOp *)0) return 0;
1053  // Eliminate this op in favor of the shadowed merge
1054  data.totalReplace(op->getOut(),substitute->getOut());
1055  data.opDestroy(op);
1056  return 1;
1057  }
1058  PcodeOp *op2 = in2->getDef();
1059  if (in1->loneDescend() != op) return 0;
1060  if (in2->loneDescend() != op) return 0;
1061 
1062  Varnode *outvn = op->getOut();
1063 
1064  data.opSetOutput(op1,outvn); // Move MULTIEQUAL output to op1, which will be new unified op
1065  data.opUninsert(op1); // Move the unified op
1066  if (res == 1) {
1067  int4 slot1 = op1->getSlot(buf1[0]);
1068  PcodeOp *substitute = findSubstitute(buf1[0],buf2[0],bl,earliest);
1069  if (substitute == (PcodeOp *)0) {
1070  substitute = data.newOp(2,op->getAddr());
1071  data.opSetOpcode(substitute,CPUI_MULTIEQUAL);
1072  // Try to preserve the storage location if the input varnodes share it
1073  // But don't propagate addrtied varnode (thru MULTIEQUAL)
1074  if ((buf1[0]->getAddr() == buf2[0]->getAddr())&&(!buf1[0]->isAddrTied()))
1075  data.newVarnodeOut(buf1[0]->getSize(),buf1[0]->getAddr(),substitute);
1076  else
1077  data.newUniqueOut(buf1[0]->getSize(),substitute);
1078  data.opSetInput(substitute,buf1[0],0);
1079  data.opSetInput(substitute,buf2[0],1);
1080  data.opInsertBegin(substitute,bl);
1081  }
1082  data.opSetInput(op1,substitute->getOut(),slot1); // Replace input to the unified op with the unified varnode
1083  data.opInsertAfter(op1,substitute); // Complete move of unified op into merge block
1084  }
1085  else
1086  data.opInsertBegin(op1,bl); // Complete move of unified op into merge block
1087  data.opDestroy(op); // Destroy the MULTIEQUAL
1088  data.opDestroy(op2); // Remove the duplicate (in favor of the unified)
1089  return 1;
1090 }
1091 
1094 void RuleNotDistribute::getOpList(vector<uint4> &oplist) const
1095 
1096 {
1097  oplist.push_back(CPUI_BOOL_NEGATE);
1098 }
1099 
1100 int4 RuleNotDistribute::applyOp(PcodeOp *op,Funcdata &data)
1101 
1102 {
1103  PcodeOp *compop = op->getIn(0)->getDef();
1104  PcodeOp *newneg1,*newneg2;
1105  Varnode *newout1,*newout2;
1106  OpCode opc;
1107 
1108  if (compop == (PcodeOp *)0) return 0;
1109  switch(compop->code()) {
1110  case CPUI_BOOL_AND:
1111  opc = CPUI_BOOL_OR;
1112  break;
1113  case CPUI_BOOL_OR:
1114  opc = CPUI_BOOL_AND;
1115  break;
1116  default:
1117  return 0;
1118  }
1119 
1120  newneg1 = data.newOp(1,op->getAddr());
1121  newout1 = data.newUniqueOut(1,newneg1);
1122  data.opSetOpcode(newneg1,CPUI_BOOL_NEGATE);
1123  data.opSetInput(newneg1,compop->getIn(0),0);
1124  data.opInsertBefore(newneg1,op);
1125 
1126  newneg2 = data.newOp(1,op->getAddr());
1127  newout2 = data.newUniqueOut(1,newneg2);
1128  data.opSetOpcode(newneg2,CPUI_BOOL_NEGATE);
1129  data.opSetInput(newneg2,compop->getIn(1),0);
1130  data.opInsertBefore(newneg2,op);
1131 
1132  data.opSetOpcode(op,opc);
1133  data.opSetInput(op,newout1,0);
1134  data.opInsertInput(op,newout2,1);
1135  return 1;
1136 }
1137 
1143 void RuleHighOrderAnd::getOpList(vector<uint4> &oplist) const
1144 
1145 {
1146  oplist.push_back(CPUI_INT_AND);
1147 }
1148 
1149 int4 RuleHighOrderAnd::applyOp(PcodeOp *op,Funcdata &data)
1150 
1151 {
1152  Varnode *xalign;
1153  Varnode *cvn1 = op->getIn(1);
1154  if (!cvn1->isConstant()) return 0;
1155  if (!op->getIn(0)->isWritten()) return 0;
1156  PcodeOp *addop = op->getIn(0)->getDef();
1157  if (addop->code() != CPUI_INT_ADD) return 0;
1158 
1159  uintb val = cvn1->getOffset();
1160  int4 size = cvn1->getSize();
1161  // Check that cvn1 is of the form 11110000
1162  if (((val-1)|val) != calc_mask(size)) return 0;
1163 
1164  Varnode *cvn2 = addop->getIn(1);
1165  if (cvn2->isConstant()) {
1166  xalign = addop->getIn(0);
1167  if (xalign->isFree()) return 0;
1168  uintb mask1 = xalign->getNZMask();
1169  // addop->Input(0) must be unaffected by the AND
1170  if ((mask1 & val)!=mask1) return 0;
1171 
1172  data.opSetOpcode(op,CPUI_INT_ADD);
1173  data.opSetInput(op,xalign,0);
1174  val = val & cvn2->getOffset();
1175  data.opSetInput(op,data.newConstant(size,val),1);
1176  return 1;
1177  }
1178  else {
1179  if (addop->getOut()->loneDescend() != op) return 0;
1180  for(int4 i=0;i<2;++i) {
1181  Varnode *zerovn = addop->getIn(i);
1182  uintb mask2 = zerovn->getNZMask();
1183  if ((mask2 & val)!=mask2) continue; // zerovn must be unaffected by the AND operation
1184  Varnode *nonzerovn = addop->getIn(1-i);
1185  if (!nonzerovn->isWritten()) continue;
1186  PcodeOp *addop2 = nonzerovn->getDef();
1187  if (addop2->code() != CPUI_INT_ADD) continue;
1188  if (nonzerovn->loneDescend() != addop) continue;
1189  cvn2 = addop2->getIn(1);
1190  if (!cvn2->isConstant()) continue;
1191  xalign = addop2->getIn(0);
1192  mask2 = xalign->getNZMask();
1193  if ((mask2 & val)!=mask2) continue;
1194  val = val & cvn2->getOffset();
1195  data.opSetInput(addop2,data.newConstant(size,val),1);
1196  // Convert the AND to a COPY
1197  data.opRemoveInput(op,1);
1198  data.opSetOpcode(op,CPUI_COPY);
1199  return 1;
1200  }
1201  }
1202  return 0;
1203 }
1204 
1207 void RuleAndDistribute::getOpList(vector<uint4> &oplist) const
1208 
1209 {
1210  oplist.push_back(CPUI_INT_AND);
1211 }
1212 
1213 int4 RuleAndDistribute::applyOp(PcodeOp *op,Funcdata &data)
1214 
1215 {
1216  Varnode *orvn,*othervn,*newvn1,*newvn2;
1217  PcodeOp *orop = (PcodeOp *)0;
1218  PcodeOp *newop1,*newop2;
1219  uintb ormask1,ormask2,othermask,fullmask;
1220  int4 i,size;
1221 
1222  size = op->getOut()->getSize();
1223  if (size > sizeof(uintb)) return 0; // FIXME: uintb should be arbitrary precision
1224  fullmask = calc_mask(size);
1225  for(i=0;i<2;++i) {
1226  othervn = op->getIn(1-i);
1227  if (!othervn->isHeritageKnown()) continue;
1228  orvn = op->getIn(i);
1229  orop = orvn->getDef();
1230  if (orop == (PcodeOp *)0) continue;
1231  if (orop->code() != CPUI_INT_OR) continue;
1232  if (!orop->getIn(0)->isHeritageKnown()) continue;
1233  if (!orop->getIn(1)->isHeritageKnown()) continue;
1234  othermask = othervn->getNZMask();
1235  if (othermask == 0) continue; // This case picked up by andmask
1236  if (othermask == fullmask) continue; // Nothing useful from distributing
1237  ormask1 = orop->getIn(0)->getNZMask();
1238  if ((ormask1 & othermask)==0) break; // AND would cancel if distributed
1239  ormask2 = orop->getIn(1)->getNZMask();
1240  if ((ormask2 & othermask)==0) break; // AND would cancel if distributed
1241  if (othervn->isConstant()) {
1242  if ((ormask1 & othermask) == ormask1) break; // AND is trivial if distributed
1243  if ((ormask2 & othermask) == ormask2) break;
1244  }
1245  }
1246  if (i==2) return 0;
1247  // Do distribution
1248  newop1 = data.newOp(2,op->getAddr()); // Distribute AND
1249  newvn1 = data.newUniqueOut(size,newop1);
1250  data.opSetOpcode(newop1,CPUI_INT_AND);
1251  data.opSetInput(newop1, orop->getIn(0), 0); // To first input of original OR
1252  data.opSetInput(newop1, othervn, 1);
1253  data.opInsertBefore(newop1, op);
1254 
1255  newop2 = data.newOp(2,op->getAddr()); // Distribute AND
1256  newvn2 = data.newUniqueOut(size,newop2);
1257  data.opSetOpcode(newop2,CPUI_INT_AND);
1258  data.opSetInput(newop2, orop->getIn(1), 0); // To second input of original OR
1259  data.opSetInput(newop2, othervn, 1);
1260  data.opInsertBefore(newop2, op);
1261 
1262  data.opSetInput( op, newvn1, 0); // new OR's inputs are outputs of new ANDs
1263  data.opSetInput( op, newvn2, 1);
1264  data.opSetOpcode(op, CPUI_INT_OR);
1265 
1266  return 1;
1267 }
1268 
1271 void RuleLessOne::getOpList(vector<uint4> &oplist) const
1272 
1273 {
1274  oplist.push_back(CPUI_INT_LESS);
1275  oplist.push_back(CPUI_INT_LESSEQUAL);
1276 }
1277 
1278 int4 RuleLessOne::applyOp(PcodeOp *op,Funcdata &data)
1279 
1280 {
1281  Varnode *constvn = op->getIn(1);
1282 
1283  if (!constvn->isConstant()) return 0;
1284  uintb val = constvn->getOffset();
1285  if ((op->code()==CPUI_INT_LESS)&&(val != 1)) return 0;
1286  if ((op->code()==CPUI_INT_LESSEQUAL)&&(val != 0)) return 0;
1287 
1288  data.opSetOpcode(op,CPUI_INT_EQUAL);
1289  if (val != 0)
1290  data.opSetInput(op,data.newConstant(constvn->getSize(),0),1);
1291  return 1;
1292 }
1293 
1294 void RuleRangeMeld::getOpList(vector<uint4> &oplist) const
1295 
1296 {
1297  oplist.push_back(CPUI_BOOL_OR);
1298  oplist.push_back(CPUI_BOOL_AND);
1299 }
1300 
1310 int4 RuleRangeMeld::applyOp(PcodeOp *op,Funcdata &data)
1311 
1312 {
1313  PcodeOp *sub1,*sub2;
1314  Varnode *vn1,*vn2;
1315  Varnode *A1,*A2;
1316  int4 restype;
1317 
1318  vn1 = op->getIn(0);
1319  if (!vn1->isWritten()) return 0;
1320  vn2 = op->getIn(1);
1321  if (!vn2->isWritten()) return 0;
1322  sub1 = vn1->getDef();
1323  if (!sub1->isBoolOutput())
1324  return 0;
1325  sub2 = vn2->getDef();
1326  if (!sub2->isBoolOutput())
1327  return 0;
1328 
1329  CircleRange range1(true);
1330  Varnode *markup = (Varnode *)0;
1331  A1 = range1.pullBack(sub1,&markup,false);
1332  if (A1 == (Varnode *)0) return 0;
1333  CircleRange range2(true);
1334  A2 = range2.pullBack(sub2,&markup,false);
1335  if (A2 == (Varnode *)0) return 0;
1336  if (sub1->code() == CPUI_BOOL_NEGATE) { // Do an extra pull back, if the last step is a '!'
1337  if (!A1->isWritten()) return 0;
1338  A1 = range1.pullBack(A1->getDef(),&markup,false);
1339  if (A1 == (Varnode *)0) return 0;
1340  }
1341  if (sub2->code() == CPUI_BOOL_NEGATE) { // Do an extra pull back, if the last step is a '!'
1342  if (!A2->isWritten()) return 0;
1343  A2 = range2.pullBack(A2->getDef(),&markup,false);
1344  if (A2 == (Varnode *)0) return 0;
1345  }
1346  if (!functionalEquality(A1,A2)) {
1347  if (A2->getSize() == A1->getSize()) return 0;
1348  if ((A1->getSize() < A2->getSize())&&(A2->isWritten()))
1349  A2 = range2.pullBack(A2->getDef(),&markup,false);
1350  else if (A1->isWritten())
1351  A1 = range1.pullBack(A1->getDef(),&markup,false);
1352  if (A1 != A2) return 0;
1353  }
1354  if (!A1->isHeritageKnown()) return 0;
1355 
1356  if (op->code() == CPUI_BOOL_AND)
1357  restype = range1.intersect(range2);
1358  else
1359  restype = range1.circleUnion(range2);
1360 
1361  if (restype == 0) {
1362  OpCode opc;
1363  uintb resc;
1364  int4 resslot;
1365  restype = range1.translate2Op(opc,resc,resslot);
1366  if (restype == 0) {
1367  Varnode *newConst = data.newConstant(A1->getSize(),resc);
1368  if (markup != (Varnode *)0) { // We have potential constant markup
1369  newConst->copySymbolIfValid(markup); // Propagate the markup into our new constant
1370  }
1371  data.opSetOpcode(op,opc);
1372  data.opSetInput(op,A1,1-resslot);
1373  data.opSetInput(op,newConst,resslot);
1374  return 1;
1375  }
1376  }
1377 
1378  if (restype == 2) return 0; // Cannot represent
1379  if (restype == 1) { // Pieces covers everything, condition is always true
1380  data.opSetOpcode(op,CPUI_COPY);
1381  data.opRemoveInput(op,1);
1382  data.opSetInput(op,data.newConstant(1,1),0);
1383  }
1384  else if (restype == 3) { // Nothing left in intersection, condition is always false
1385  data.opSetOpcode(op,CPUI_COPY);
1386  data.opRemoveInput(op,1);
1387  data.opSetInput(op,data.newConstant(1,0),0);
1388  }
1389  return 1;
1390 }
1391 
1396 void RuleFloatRange::getOpList(vector<uint4> &oplist) const
1397 
1398 {
1399  oplist.push_back(CPUI_BOOL_OR);
1400  oplist.push_back(CPUI_BOOL_AND);
1401 }
1402 
1403 int4 RuleFloatRange::applyOp(PcodeOp *op,Funcdata &data)
1404 
1405 {
1406  PcodeOp *cmp1,*cmp2;
1407  Varnode *vn1,*vn2;
1408 
1409  vn1 = op->getIn(0);
1410  if (!vn1->isWritten()) return 0;
1411  vn2 = op->getIn(1);
1412  if (!vn2->isWritten()) return 0;
1413  cmp1 = vn1->getDef();
1414  cmp2 = vn2->getDef();
1415  OpCode opccmp1 = cmp1->code();
1416  // Set cmp1 to LESS or LESSEQUAL operator, cmp2 is the "other" operator
1417  if ((opccmp1!=CPUI_FLOAT_LESS)&&(opccmp1!=CPUI_FLOAT_LESSEQUAL)) {
1418  cmp1 = cmp2;
1419  cmp2 = vn1->getDef();
1420  opccmp1 = cmp1->code();
1421  }
1422  OpCode resultopc = CPUI_COPY;
1423  if (opccmp1==CPUI_FLOAT_LESS) {
1424  if ((cmp2->code() == CPUI_FLOAT_EQUAL)&&(op->code()==CPUI_BOOL_OR))
1425  resultopc = CPUI_FLOAT_LESSEQUAL;
1426  }
1427  else if (opccmp1==CPUI_FLOAT_LESSEQUAL) {
1428  if ((cmp2->code() == CPUI_FLOAT_NOTEQUAL)&&(op->code()==CPUI_BOOL_AND))
1429  resultopc = CPUI_FLOAT_LESS;
1430  }
1431 
1432  if (resultopc == CPUI_COPY) return 0;
1433 
1434  // Make sure both operators are comparing the same things
1435  Varnode *nvn1,*cvn1;
1436  int4 slot1 = 0;
1437  nvn1 = cmp1->getIn(slot1); // Set nvn1 to a non-constant off of cmp1
1438  if (nvn1->isConstant()) {
1439  slot1 = 1;
1440  nvn1 = cmp1->getIn(slot1);
1441  if (nvn1->isConstant()) return 0;
1442  }
1443  if (nvn1->isFree()) return 0;
1444  cvn1 = cmp1->getIn(1-slot1); // Set cvn1 to the "other" slot off of cmp1
1445  int4 slot2;
1446  if (nvn1 != cmp2->getIn(0)) {
1447  slot2 = 1;
1448  if (nvn1 != cmp2->getIn(1))
1449  return 0;
1450  }
1451  else
1452  slot2 = 0;
1453  Varnode *matchvn = cmp2->getIn(1-slot2);
1454  if (cvn1->isConstant()) {
1455  if (!matchvn->isConstant()) return 0;
1456  if (matchvn->getOffset() != cvn1->getOffset()) return 0;
1457  }
1458  else if (cvn1 != matchvn)
1459  return 0;
1460  else if (cvn1->isFree())
1461  return 0;
1462 
1463  // Collapse the 2 comparisons into 1 comparison
1464  data.opSetOpcode(op,resultopc);
1465  data.opSetInput(op,nvn1,slot1);
1466  if (cvn1->isConstant())
1467  data.opSetInput(op,data.newConstant(cvn1->getSize(),cvn1->getOffset()),1-slot1);
1468  else
1469  data.opSetInput(op,cvn1,1-slot1);
1470  return 1;
1471 }
1472 
1479 void RuleAndCommute::getOpList(vector<uint4> &oplist) const
1480 
1481 {
1482  oplist.push_back(CPUI_INT_AND);
1483 }
1484 
1485 int4 RuleAndCommute::applyOp(PcodeOp *op,Funcdata &data)
1486 
1487 {
1488  Varnode *orvn,*shiftvn,*othervn,*newvn1,*newvn2,*savn;
1489  PcodeOp *orop,*shiftop,*newop1,*newop2;
1490  uintb ormask1,ormask2,othermask,fullmask;
1491  OpCode opc = CPUI_INT_OR; // Unnecessary initialization
1492  int4 sa,i,size;
1493 
1494  orvn = othervn = savn = (Varnode *)0; // Unnecessary initialization
1495  size = op->getOut()->getSize();
1496  if (size > sizeof(uintb)) return 0; // FIXME: uintb should be arbitrary precision
1497  fullmask = calc_mask(size);
1498  for(i=0;i<2;++i) {
1499  shiftvn = op->getIn(i);
1500  shiftop = shiftvn->getDef();
1501  if (shiftop == (PcodeOp *)0) continue;
1502  opc = shiftop->code();
1503  if ((opc != CPUI_INT_LEFT)&&(opc!=CPUI_INT_RIGHT)) continue;
1504  savn = shiftop->getIn(1);
1505  if (!savn->isConstant()) continue;
1506  sa = (int4)savn->getOffset();
1507 
1508  othervn = op->getIn(1-i);
1509  if (!othervn->isHeritageKnown()) continue;
1510  othermask = othervn->getNZMask();
1511  // Check if AND is only zeroing bits which are already
1512  // zeroed by the shift, in which case andmask takes
1513  // care of it
1514  if (opc==CPUI_INT_RIGHT) {
1515  if ((fullmask>>sa)==othermask) continue;
1516  othermask <<= sa; // Calc mask as it will be after commute
1517  }
1518  else {
1519  if (((fullmask<<sa)&&fullmask)==othermask) continue;
1520  othermask >>= sa; // Calc mask as it will be after commute
1521  }
1522  if (othermask == 0) continue; // Handled by andmask
1523  if (othermask == fullmask) continue;
1524 
1525  orvn = shiftop->getIn(0);
1526  if ((opc==CPUI_INT_LEFT)&&(othervn->isConstant())) {
1527  // (v & #c) << #sa if preferred to (v << #sa) & #(c << sa)
1528  // because the mask is right/least justified, so it makes sense as a normalization
1529  // NOTE: if the shift is right(>>) then performing the AND first does NOT give a justified mask
1530  // NOTE: if we don't check that AND is masking with a constant, RuleAndCommute causes an infinite
1531  // sequence of transforms
1532  if (shiftvn->loneDescend() == op) break; // If there is no other use of shift, always do the commute
1533  }
1534 
1535  if (!orvn->isWritten()) continue;
1536  orop = orvn->getDef();
1537 
1538  if (orop->code() == CPUI_INT_OR) {
1539  ormask1 = orop->getIn(0)->getNZMask();
1540  if ((ormask1 & othermask)==0) break;
1541  ormask2 = orop->getIn(1)->getNZMask();
1542  if ((ormask2 & othermask)==0) break;
1543  if (othervn->isConstant()) {
1544  if ((ormask1 & othermask) == ormask1) break;
1545  if ((ormask2 & othermask) == ormask2) break;
1546  }
1547  }
1548  else if (orop->code() == CPUI_PIECE) {
1549  ormask1 = orop->getIn(1)->getNZMask(); // Low part of piece
1550  if ((ormask1 & othermask)==0) break;
1551  ormask2 = orop->getIn(0)->getNZMask(); // High part
1552  ormask2 <<= orop->getIn(1)->getSize() * 8;
1553  if ((ormask2 & othermask)==0) break;
1554  }
1555  else
1556  continue;
1557  }
1558  if (i==2) return 0;
1559  // Do the commute
1560  newop1 = data.newOp(2,op->getAddr());
1561  newvn1 = data.newUniqueOut(size,newop1);
1562  data.opSetOpcode(newop1,(opc==CPUI_INT_LEFT)?CPUI_INT_RIGHT:CPUI_INT_LEFT);
1563  data.opSetInput(newop1, othervn, 0);
1564  data.opSetInput(newop1, savn, 1);
1565  data.opInsertBefore(newop1, op);
1566 
1567  newop2 = data.newOp(2,op->getAddr());
1568  newvn2 = data.newUniqueOut(size,newop2);
1569  data.opSetOpcode(newop2,CPUI_INT_AND);
1570  data.opSetInput(newop2, orvn, 0);
1571  data.opSetInput(newop2, newvn1, 1);
1572  data.opInsertBefore(newop2, op);
1573 
1574  data.opSetInput(op, newvn2, 0);
1575  data.opSetInput(op, savn, 1);
1576  data.opSetOpcode(op, opc);
1577 
1578  return 1;
1579 }
1580 
1587 void RuleAndPiece::getOpList(vector<uint4> &oplist) const
1588 
1589 {
1590  oplist.push_back(CPUI_INT_AND);
1591 }
1592 
1593 int4 RuleAndPiece::applyOp(PcodeOp *op,Funcdata &data)
1594 
1595 {
1596  Varnode *piecevn,*othervn,*highvn,*lowvn,*newvn,*newvn2;
1597  PcodeOp *pieceop,*newop;
1598  uintb othermask,maskhigh,masklow;
1599  OpCode opc = CPUI_PIECE; // Unnecessary initialization
1600  int4 i,size;
1601 
1602  size = op->getOut()->getSize();
1603  highvn = lowvn = (Varnode *)0; // Unnecessary initialization
1604  for(i=0;i<2;++i) {
1605  piecevn = op->getIn(i);
1606  if (!piecevn->isWritten()) continue;
1607  pieceop = piecevn->getDef();
1608  if (pieceop->code() != CPUI_PIECE) continue;
1609  othervn = op->getIn(1-i);
1610  othermask = othervn->getNZMask();
1611  if (othermask == calc_mask(size)) continue;
1612  if (othermask == 0) continue; // Handled by andmask
1613  highvn = pieceop->getIn(0);
1614  if (!highvn->isHeritageKnown()) continue;
1615  lowvn = pieceop->getIn(1);
1616  if (!lowvn->isHeritageKnown()) continue;
1617  maskhigh = highvn->getNZMask();
1618  masklow = lowvn->getNZMask();
1619  if ((maskhigh & (othermask>>(lowvn->getSize()*8)))==0) {
1620  if ((maskhigh==0)&&(highvn->isConstant())) continue; // Handled by piece2zext
1621  opc = CPUI_INT_ZEXT;
1622  break;
1623  }
1624  else if ((masklow & othermask)==0) {
1625  if (lowvn->isConstant()) continue; // Nothing to do
1626  opc = CPUI_PIECE;
1627  break;
1628  }
1629  }
1630  if (i==2) return 0;
1631  if (opc == CPUI_INT_ZEXT) { // Change PIECE(a,b) to ZEXT(b)
1632  newop = data.newOp(1,op->getAddr());
1633  data.opSetOpcode(newop,opc);
1634  data.opSetInput(newop, lowvn, 0);
1635  }
1636  else { // Change PIECE(a,b) to PIECE(a,#0)
1637  newvn2 = data.newConstant(lowvn->getSize(),0);
1638  newop = data.newOp(2,op->getAddr());
1639  data.opSetOpcode(newop,opc);
1640  data.opSetInput(newop, highvn, 0);
1641  data.opSetInput(newop, newvn2, 1);
1642  }
1643  newvn = data.newUniqueOut(size,newop);
1644  data.opInsertBefore(newop, op);
1645  data.opSetInput(op,newvn,i);
1646  return 1;
1647 }

1653 void RuleAndCompare::getOpList(vector<uint4> &oplist) const
1654 
1655 {
1656  oplist.push_back(CPUI_INT_EQUAL);
1657  oplist.push_back(CPUI_INT_NOTEQUAL);
1658 }
1659 
1660 int4 RuleAndCompare::applyOp(PcodeOp *op,Funcdata &data)
1661 
1662 {
1663  if (!op->getIn(1)->isConstant()) return 0;
1664  if (op->getIn(1)->getOffset() != 0) return 0;
1665 
1666  Varnode *andvn,*subvn,*basevn,*constvn;
1667  PcodeOp *andop,*subop;
1668  uintb andconst,baseconst;
1669 
1670  andvn = op->getIn(0);
1671  if (!andvn->isWritten()) return 0;
1672  andop = andvn->getDef();
1673  if (andop->code() != CPUI_INT_AND) return 0;
1674  if (!andop->getIn(1)->isConstant()) return 0;
1675  subvn = andop->getIn(0);
1676  if (!subvn->isWritten()) return 0;
1677  subop = subvn->getDef();
1678  switch(subop->code()) {
1679  case CPUI_SUBPIECE:
1680  basevn = subop->getIn(0);
1681  baseconst = andop->getIn(1)->getOffset();
1682  andconst = baseconst << subop->getIn(1)->getOffset() * 8;
1683  break;
1684  case CPUI_INT_ZEXT:
1685  basevn = subop->getIn(0);
1686  baseconst = andop->getIn(1)->getOffset();
1687  andconst = baseconst & calc_mask(basevn->getSize());
1688  break;
1689  default:
1690  return 0;
1691  }
1692 
1693  if (baseconst == calc_mask(andvn->getSize())) return 0; // Degenerate AND
1694  if (basevn->isFree()) return 0;
1695 
1696  constvn = data.newConstant(basevn->getSize(),andconst);
1697  if (baseconst == andconst) // If no effective change in constant (except varnode size)
1698  constvn->copySymbol(andop->getIn(1)); // Keep any old symbol
1699  // New version of and with bigger inputs
1700  PcodeOp *newop = data.newOp(2,andop->getAddr());
1701  data.opSetOpcode(newop,CPUI_INT_AND);
1702  Varnode *newout = data.newUniqueOut(basevn->getSize(),newop);
1703  data.opSetInput(newop,basevn,0);
1704  data.opSetInput(newop,constvn,1);
1705  data.opInsertBefore(newop,andop);
1706 
1707  data.opSetInput(op,newout,0);
1708  data.opSetInput(op,data.newConstant(basevn->getSize(),0),1);
1709  return 1;
1710 }

1720 int4 RuleDoubleSub::applyOp(PcodeOp *op,Funcdata &data)
1721 
1722 {
1723  PcodeOp *op2;
1724  Varnode *vn;

1726 
1727  vn = op->getIn(0);
1728  if (!vn->isWritten()) return 0;
1729  op2 = vn->getDef();
1730  if (op2->code() != CPUI_SUBPIECE) return 0;
1731  offset1 = op->getIn(1)->getOffset();
1732  offset2 = op2->getIn(1)->getOffset();
1733 
1734  data.opSetInput(op,op2->getIn(0),0); // Skip middleman
1735  data.opSetInput(op,data.newConstant(4,offset1+offset2), 1);
1736  return 1;

1747 void RuleDoubleShift::getOpList(vector<uint4> &oplist) const
1748 
1749 {
1750  oplist.push_back(CPUI_INT_LEFT);
1751  oplist.push_back(CPUI_INT_RIGHT);
1752  oplist.push_back(CPUI_INT_MULT);
1753 }
1754 
1755 int4 RuleDoubleShift::applyOp(PcodeOp *op,Funcdata &data)
1756 
1757 {
1758  Varnode *secvn,*newvn;
1759  PcodeOp *secop;
1760  OpCode opc1,opc2;
1761  int4 sa1,sa2,size;
1762  uintb mask;
1763 
1764  if (!op->getIn(1)->isConstant()) return 0;
1765  secvn = op->getIn(0);
1766  if (!secvn->isWritten()) return 0;
1767  secop = secvn->getDef();
1768  opc2 = secop->code();
1769  if ((opc2!=CPUI_INT_LEFT)&&(opc2!=CPUI_INT_RIGHT)&&(opc2!=CPUI_INT_MULT))
1770  return 0;
1771  if (!secop->getIn(1)->isConstant()) return 0;
1772  opc1 = op->code();
1773  size = secvn->getSize();
1774  if (!secop->getIn(0)->isHeritageKnown()) return 0;
1775 
1776  if (opc1 == CPUI_INT_MULT) {
1777  uintb val = op->getIn(1)->getOffset();
1778  sa1 = leastsigbit_set(val);
1779  if ((val>>sa1) != (uintb)1) return 0; // Not multiplying by a power of 2
1780  opc1 = CPUI_INT_LEFT;
1781  }
1782  else
1783  sa1 = op->getIn(1)->getOffset();
1784  if (opc2 == CPUI_INT_MULT) {
1785  uintb val = secop->getIn(1)->getOffset();
1786  sa2 = leastsigbit_set(val);
1787  if ((val>>sa2) != (uintb)1) return 0; // Not multiplying by a power of 2
1788  opc2 = CPUI_INT_LEFT;
1789  }
1790  else
1791  sa2 = secop->getIn(1)->getOffset();
1792  if (opc1 == opc2) {
1793  if (sa1 + sa2 < 8*size) {
1794  newvn = data.newConstant(size,sa1+sa2);
1795  data.opSetOpcode(op,opc1);
1796  data.opSetInput(op,secop->getIn(0),0);
1797  data.opSetInput(op,newvn,1);
1798  }
1799  else {
1800  newvn = data.newConstant(size,0);
1801  data.opSetOpcode(op,CPUI_COPY);
1802  data.opSetInput(op,newvn,0);
1803  data.opRemoveInput(op,1);
1804  }
1805  }
1806  else if (sa1 == sa2) {
1807  mask = calc_mask(size);
1808  if (opc1 == CPUI_INT_LEFT)
1809  mask = (mask<<sa1) & mask;
1810  else
1811  mask = (mask>>sa1) & mask;
1812  newvn = data.newConstant(size,mask);
1813  data.opSetOpcode(op,CPUI_INT_AND);
1814  data.opSetInput(op,secop->getIn(0),0);
1815  data.opSetInput(op,newvn,1);
1816  }
1817  else
1818  return 0;
1819  return 1;
1820 }
1821 
1828 void RuleConcatShift::getOpList(vector<uint4> &oplist) const
1829 
1830 {
1831  oplist.push_back(CPUI_INT_RIGHT);
1832  oplist.push_back(CPUI_INT_SRIGHT);
1833 }
1834 
1835 int4 RuleConcatShift::applyOp(PcodeOp *op,Funcdata &data)
1836 
1837 {
1838  if (!op->getIn(1)->isConstant()) return 0;
1839 
1840  Varnode *shiftin = op->getIn(0);
1841  if (!shiftin->isWritten()) return 0;
1842  PcodeOp *concat = shiftin->getDef();
1843  if (concat->code() != CPUI_PIECE) return 0;
1844 
1845  int4 sa = op->getIn(1)->getOffset();
1846  int4 leastsize = concat->getIn(1)->getSize() * 8;
1847  if (sa < leastsize) return 0; // Does shift throw away least sig part
1848  Varnode *mainin = concat->getIn(0);
1849  if (mainin->isFree()) return 0;
1850  sa -= leastsize;
1851  OpCode extcode = (op->code() == CPUI_INT_RIGHT) ? CPUI_INT_ZEXT : CPUI_INT_SEXT;
1852  if (sa == 0) { // Exact cancelation
1853  data.opRemoveInput(op,1); // Remove thrown away least
1854  data.opSetOpcode(op,extcode); // Change to extension
1855  data.opSetInput(op,mainin,0);
1856  }
1857  else {
1858  // Create a new extension op
1859  PcodeOp *extop = data.newOp(1,op->getAddr());
1860  data.opSetOpcode(extop,extcode);
1861  Varnode *newvn = data.newUniqueOut(shiftin->getSize(),extop);
1862  data.opSetInput(extop,mainin,0);
1863 
1864  // Adjust the shift amount
1865  data.opSetInput(op,newvn,0);
1866  data.opSetInput(op,data.newConstant(op->getIn(1)->getSize(),sa),1);
1867  data.opInsertBefore(extop,op);
1868  }
1869  return 1;
1870 }

1879 void RuleLeftRight::getOpList(vector<uint4> &oplist) const
1880 
1881 {
1882  oplist.push_back(CPUI_INT_RIGHT);
1883  oplist.push_back(CPUI_INT_SRIGHT);
1884 }
1885 
1886 int4 RuleLeftRight::applyOp(PcodeOp *op,Funcdata &data)
1887 
1888 {
1889  if (!op->getIn(1)->isConstant()) return 0;
1890 
1891  Varnode *shiftin = op->getIn(0);
1892  if (!shiftin->isWritten()) return 0;
1893  PcodeOp *leftshift = shiftin->getDef();
1894  if (leftshift->code() != CPUI_INT_LEFT) return 0;
1895  if (!leftshift->getIn(1)->isConstant()) return 0;
1896  uintb sa = op->getIn(1)->getOffset();
1897  if (leftshift->getIn(1)->getOffset() != sa) return 0; // Left shift must be by same amount
1898 
1899  if ((sa & 7) != 0) return 0; // Must be multiple of 8
1900  int4 isa = (int4)(sa>>3);
1901  int4 tsz = shiftin->getSize() - isa;
1902  if ((tsz!=1)&&(tsz!=2)&&(tsz!=4)&&(tsz!=8)) return 0;
1903 
1904  if (shiftin->loneDescend() != op) return 0;
1905  Address addr = shiftin->getAddr();
1906  if (addr.isBigEndian())
1907  addr = addr + isa;
1908  data.opUnsetInput(op,0);
1909  data.opUnsetOutput(leftshift);
1910  Varnode *newvn = data.newVarnodeOut(tsz,addr,leftshift);
1911  data.opSetOpcode(leftshift,CPUI_SUBPIECE);
1912  data.opSetInput(leftshift, data.newConstant( leftshift->getIn(1)->getSize(), 0), 1);
1913  data.opSetInput(op, newvn, 0);
1914  data.opRemoveInput(op,1); // Remove the right-shift constant
1915  data.opSetOpcode( op, (op->code() == CPUI_INT_SRIGHT) ? CPUI_INT_SEXT : CPUI_INT_ZEXT);
1916  return 1;
1917 }
1918 
1925 void RuleShiftCompare::getOpList(vector<uint4> &oplist) const
1926 
1927 {
1928  oplist.push_back(CPUI_INT_EQUAL);
1929  oplist.push_back(CPUI_INT_NOTEQUAL);
1930 }
1931 
1932 int4 RuleShiftCompare::applyOp(PcodeOp *op,Funcdata &data)
1933 
1934 {
1935  Varnode *shiftvn,*constvn,*savn,*mainvn;
1936  PcodeOp *shiftop;
1937  int4 sa;
1938  uintb constval,nzmask,newconst;
1939  OpCode opc;
1940  bool isleft;
1941 
1942  shiftvn = op->getIn(0);
1943  constvn = op->getIn(1);
1944  if (!constvn->isConstant()) return 0;
1945  if (!shiftvn->isWritten()) return 0;
1946  shiftop = shiftvn->getDef();
1947  opc = shiftop->code();
1948  if (opc==CPUI_INT_LEFT) {
1949  isleft = true;
1950  savn = shiftop->getIn(1);
1951  if (!savn->isConstant()) return 0;
1952  sa = savn->getOffset();
1953  }
1954  else if (opc == CPUI_INT_RIGHT) {
1955  isleft = false;
1956  savn = shiftop->getIn(1);
1957  if (!savn->isConstant()) return 0;
1958  sa = savn->getOffset();
1959  // There are definitely some situations where you don't want this rule to apply, like jump
1960  // table analysis where the switch variable is a bit field.
1961  // When shifting to the right, this is a likely shift out of a bitfield, which we would want to keep
1962  // We only apply when we know we will eliminate a variable
1963  if (shiftvn->loneDescend() != op) return 0;
1964  }
1965  else if (opc == CPUI_INT_MULT) {
1966  isleft = true;
1967  savn = shiftop->getIn(1);
1968  if (!savn->isConstant()) return 0;
1969  uintb val = savn->getOffset();
1970  sa = leastsigbit_set(val);
1971  if ((val>>sa) != (uintb)1) return 0; // Not multiplying by a power of 2
1972  }
1973  else if (opc == CPUI_INT_DIV) {
1974  isleft = false;
1975  savn = shiftop->getIn(1);
1976  if (!savn->isConstant()) return 0;
1977  uintb val = savn->getOffset();
1978  sa = leastsigbit_set(val);
1979  if ((val>>sa) != (uintb)1) return 0; // Not dividing by a power of 2
1980  if (shiftvn->loneDescend() != op) return 0;
1981  }
1982  else
1983  return 0;
1984 
1985  if (sa==0) return 0;
1986  mainvn = shiftop->getIn(0);
1987  if (mainvn->isFree()) return 0;
1988  if (mainvn->getSize() > sizeof(uintb)) return 0; // FIXME: uintb should be arbitrary precision
1989 
1990  constval = constvn->getOffset();
1991  nzmask = mainvn->getNZMask();
1992  if (isleft) {
1993  newconst = constval >> sa;
1994  if ((newconst << sa) != constval) return 0; // Information lost in constval
1995  uintb tmp = (nzmask << sa) & calc_mask(shiftvn->getSize());
1996  if ((tmp>>sa)!=nzmask) { // Information is lost in main
1997  // We replace the LEFT with and AND mask
1998  // This must be the lone use of the shift
1999  if (shiftvn->loneDescend() != op) return 0;
2000  sa = 8*shiftvn->getSize() - sa;
2001  tmp = (((uintb)1) << sa)-1;
2002  Varnode *newmask = data.newConstant(constvn->getSize(),tmp);
2003  PcodeOp *newop = data.newOp(2,op->getAddr());
2004  data.opSetOpcode(newop,CPUI_INT_AND);
2005  Varnode *newtmpvn = data.newUniqueOut(constvn->getSize(),newop);
2006  data.opSetInput(newop, mainvn, 0);
2007  data.opSetInput(newop, newmask, 1);
2008  data.opInsertBefore(newop,shiftop);
2009  data.opSetInput(op,newtmpvn,0);
2010  data.opSetInput(op,data.newConstant(constvn->getSize(),newconst),1);
2011  return 1;
2012  }
2013  }
2014  else {
2015  if (((nzmask >> sa)<<sa)!=nzmask) return 0; // Information is lost
2016  newconst = (constval << sa) & calc_mask(shiftvn->getSize());
2017  if ((newconst>>sa)!=constval) return 0; // Information is lost in constval
2018  }
2019  Varnode *newconstvn = data.newConstant(constvn->getSize(),newconst);
2020  data.opSetInput(op,mainvn,0);
2021  data.opSetInput(op,newconstvn,1);
2022  return 1;
2023 }

2117 int4 RuleLessEqual::applyOp(PcodeOp *op,Funcdata &data)
2118 
2119 {
2120  Varnode *compvn1,*compvn2,*vnout1,*vnout2;
2121  PcodeOp *op_less,*op_equal;
2122  OpCode opc,equalopc;
2123 
2124  vnout1 = op->getIn(0);
2125  if (!vnout1->isWritten()) return 0;
2126  vnout2 = op->getIn(1);
2127  if (!vnout2->isWritten()) return 0;
2128  op_less = vnout1->getDef();
2129  opc = op_less->code();
2130  if ((opc != CPUI_INT_LESS)&&(opc!=CPUI_INT_SLESS)) {
2131  op_equal = op_less;
2132  op_less = vnout2->getDef();
2133  opc = op_less->code();
2134  if ((opc != CPUI_INT_LESS)&&(opc!=CPUI_INT_SLESS))
2135  return 0;
2136  }
2137  else
2138  op_equal = vnout2->getDef();
2139  equalopc = op_equal->code();
2140  if ((equalopc != CPUI_INT_EQUAL)&&( equalopc != CPUI_INT_NOTEQUAL))
2141  return 0;
2142 
2143  compvn1 = op_less->getIn(0);
2144  compvn2 = op_less->getIn(1);
2145  if (!compvn1->isHeritageKnown()) return 0;
2146  if (!compvn2->isHeritageKnown()) return 0;
2147  if (((*compvn1 != *op_equal->getIn(0))||(*compvn2 != *op_equal->getIn(1)))&&
2148  ((*compvn1 != *op_equal->getIn(1))||(*compvn2 != *op_equal->getIn(0))))
2149  return 0;
2150 
2151  if (equalopc == CPUI_INT_NOTEQUAL) { // op_less is redundant
2152  data.opSetOpcode(op, CPUI_COPY); // Convert OR to COPY
2153  data.opRemoveInput(op,1);
2154  data.opSetInput(op,op_equal->getOut(),0); // Taking the NOTEQUAL output
2155  }
2156  else {
2157  data.opSetInput(op,compvn1,0);
2158  data.opSetInput(op,compvn2,1);
2159  data.opSetOpcode(op, (opc==CPUI_INT_SLESS) ? CPUI_INT_SLESSEQUAL : CPUI_INT_LESSEQUAL);
2160  }
2161 
2162  return 1;
2163 }

2228 
2229 {

2231  CPUI_INT_EQUAL, CPUI_INT_SLESSEQUAL, CPUI_INT_LESSEQUAL,
2232  CPUI_INT_XOR, CPUI_INT_AND, CPUI_INT_OR,

2237 int4 RuleTrivialArith::applyOp(PcodeOp *op,Funcdata &data)
2238 
2239 {
2240  Varnode *vn;
2241  Varnode *in0,*in1;
2242 
2243  if (op->numInput() != 2) return 0;
2244  in0 = op->getIn(0);
2245  in1 = op->getIn(1);
2246  if (in0 != in1) { // Inputs must be identical
2247  if (!in0->isWritten()) return 0;
2248  if (!in1->isWritten()) return 0;
2249  if (!in0->getDef()->isCseMatch(in1->getDef())) return 0; // or constructed identically
2250  }
2251  switch(op->code()) {
2252 
2253  case CPUI_INT_NOTEQUAL: // Boolean 0
2254  case CPUI_INT_SLESS:
2255  case CPUI_INT_LESS:
2256  case CPUI_BOOL_XOR:
2257  case CPUI_FLOAT_NOTEQUAL:
2258  case CPUI_FLOAT_LESS:
2259  vn = data.newConstant(1,0);
2260  break;
2261  case CPUI_INT_EQUAL: // Boolean 1
2262  case CPUI_INT_SLESSEQUAL:
2263  case CPUI_INT_LESSEQUAL:
2264  case CPUI_FLOAT_EQUAL:
2265  case CPUI_FLOAT_LESSEQUAL:
2266  vn = data.newConstant(1,1);
2267  break;
2268  case CPUI_INT_XOR: // Same size 0
2269  // case CPUI_INT_SUB:
2270  vn = data.newConstant(op->getOut()->getSize(),0);
2271  break;
2272  case CPUI_BOOL_AND: // Identity
2273  case CPUI_BOOL_OR:
2274  case CPUI_INT_AND:
2275  case CPUI_INT_OR:
2276  vn = (Varnode *)0;
2277  break;
2278  default:
2279  return 0;
2280  }
2281 
2282  data.opRemoveInput(op,1);
2283  data.opSetOpcode(op,CPUI_COPY);
2284  if (vn != (Varnode *)0)
2285  data.opSetInput(op,vn,0);
2286 
2287  return 1;
2288 }

2300 
2301 {
2302  uint4 list[] = { CPUI_BOOL_AND, CPUI_BOOL_OR, CPUI_BOOL_XOR };

2306 int4 RuleTrivialBool::applyOp(PcodeOp *op,Funcdata &data)
2307 
2308 {
2309  Varnode *vnconst = op->getIn(1);
2310  Varnode *vn;
2311  uintb val;
2312  OpCode opc;
2313 
2314  if (!vnconst->isConstant()) return 0;
2315  val = vnconst->getOffset();
2316 
2317  switch(op->code()) {
2318  case CPUI_BOOL_XOR:
2319  vn = op->getIn(0);
2320  opc = (val==1) ? CPUI_BOOL_NEGATE : CPUI_COPY;
2321  break;
2322  case CPUI_BOOL_AND:
2323  opc = CPUI_COPY;
2324  if (val==1)
2325  vn = op->getIn(0);
2326  else
2327  vn = data.newConstant(1,0); // Copy false
2328  break;
2329  case CPUI_BOOL_OR:
2330  opc = CPUI_COPY;
2331  if (val==1)
2332  vn = data.newConstant(1,1);
2333  else
2334  vn = op->getIn(0);
2335  break;
2336  default:
2337  return 0;
2338  }
2339 
2340  data.opRemoveInput(op,1);
2341  data.opSetOpcode(op,opc);
2342  data.opSetInput(op,vn,0);
2343  return 1;
2344 }

2362 int4 RuleZextEliminate::applyOp(PcodeOp *op,Funcdata &data)
2363 
2364 {
2365  PcodeOp *zext;
2366  Varnode *vn1,*vn2,*newvn;
2367  uintb val;
2368  int4 smallsize,zextslot,otherslot;
2369 
2370  // vn1 equals ZEXTed input
2371  // vn2 = other input
2372  vn1 = op->getIn(0);
2373  vn2 = op->getIn(1);
2374  zextslot = 0;
2375  otherslot = 1;
2376  if ((vn2->isWritten())&&(vn2->getDef()->code()==CPUI_INT_ZEXT)) {
2377  vn1 = vn2;
2378  vn2 = op->getIn(0);
2379  zextslot = 1;
2380  otherslot = 0;
2381  }
2382  else if ((!vn1->isWritten())||(vn1->getDef()->code()!=CPUI_INT_ZEXT))
2383  return 0;
2384 
2385  if (!vn2->isConstant()) return 0;
2386  zext = vn1->getDef();
2387  if (!zext->getIn(0)->isHeritageKnown()) return 0;
2388  smallsize = zext->getIn(0)->getSize();
2389  val = vn2->getOffset();
2390  if ((val>>(8*smallsize))==0) { // Is zero extension unnecessary
2391  newvn = data.newConstant(smallsize,val);
2392  data.opSetInput(op,zext->getIn(0),zextslot);
2393  data.opSetInput(op,newvn,otherslot);
2394  return 1;
2395  }
2396  // Should have else for doing
2397  // constant comparison here and now
2398  return 0;
2399 }

2486 
2487 int4 RuleBitUndistribute::applyOp(PcodeOp *op,Funcdata &data)
2488 
2489 {
2490  Varnode *vn1 = op->getIn(0);
2491  Varnode *vn2 = op->getIn(1);
2492  Varnode *in1,*in2,*vnextra;
2493  OpCode opc;
2494 
2495  if (!vn1->isWritten()) return 0;
2496  if (!vn2->isWritten()) return 0;
2497 
2498  opc = vn1->getDef()->code();
2499  if (vn2->getDef()->code() != opc) return 0;
2500  switch(opc) {
2501  case CPUI_INT_ZEXT:
2502  case CPUI_INT_SEXT:
2503  // Test for full equality of extension operation
2504  in1 = vn1->getDef()->getIn(0);
2505  if (in1->isFree()) return 0;
2506  in2 = vn2->getDef()->getIn(0);
2507  if (in2->isFree()) return 0;
2508  if (in1->getSize() != in2->getSize()) return 0;
2509  data.opRemoveInput(op,1);
2510  break;
2511  case CPUI_INT_LEFT:
2512  case CPUI_INT_RIGHT:
2513  case CPUI_INT_SRIGHT:
2514  // Test for full equality of shift operation
2515  in1 = vn1->getDef()->getIn(1);
2516  in2 = vn2->getDef()->getIn(1);
2517  if (in1->isConstant() && in2->isConstant()) {
2518  if (in1->getOffset() != in2->getOffset())
2519  return 0;
2520  vnextra = data.newConstant(in1->getSize(),in1->getOffset());
2521  }
2522  else if (in1 != in2)
2523  return 0;
2524  else {
2525  if (in1->isFree()) return 0;
2526  vnextra = in1;
2527  }
2528  in1 = vn1->getDef()->getIn(0);
2529  if (in1->isFree()) return 0;
2530  in2 = vn2->getDef()->getIn(0);
2531  if (in2->isFree()) return 0;
2532  data.opSetInput(op,vnextra,1);
2533  break;
2534  default:
2535  return 0;
2536  }
2537 
2538  PcodeOp *newext = data.newOp(2,op->getAddr());
2539  Varnode *smalllogic = data.newUniqueOut(in1->getSize(),newext);
2540  data.opSetInput(newext,in1,0);
2541  data.opSetInput(newext,in2,1);
2542  data.opSetOpcode(newext,op->code());
2543 
2544  data.opSetOpcode(op,opc);
2545  data.opSetInput(op,smalllogic,0);
2546  data.opInsertBefore(newext,op);
2547  return 1;
2548 }
2549 
2555 void RuleBooleanNegate::getOpList(vector<uint4> &oplist) const
2556 
2557 {
2558  uint4 list[]= { CPUI_INT_NOTEQUAL, CPUI_INT_EQUAL };
2559  oplist.insert(oplist.end(),list,list+2);

2561 
2562 int4 RuleBooleanNegate::applyOp(PcodeOp *op,Funcdata &data)
2563 
2564 {
2565  OpCode opc;
2566  Varnode *constvn;
2567  Varnode *subbool;
2568  PcodeOp *subop;
2569  bool negate;
2570  uintb val;
2571 
2572  opc = op->code();
2573  constvn = op->getIn(1);
2574  subbool = op->getIn(0);
2575  if (!constvn->isConstant()) return 0;
2576  val = constvn->getOffset();
2577  if ((val!=0)&&(val!=1))
2578  return 0;
2579  negate = (opc==CPUI_INT_NOTEQUAL);
2580  if (val==0)
2581  negate = !negate;
2582 
2583  if (!subbool->isWritten()) return 0;
2584  subop = subbool->getDef();
2585  if (!subop->isCalculatedBool()) return 0; // Subexpression must be boolean output
2586 
2587  data.opRemoveInput(op,1); // Remove second parameter
2588  data.opSetInput(op,subbool,0); // Keep original boolean parameter
2589  if (negate)
2590  data.opSetOpcode(op,CPUI_BOOL_NEGATE);
2591  else
2592  data.opSetOpcode(op,CPUI_COPY);
2593 
2594  return 1;
2595 }

2605 void RuleBoolZext::getOpList(vector<uint4> &oplist) const
2606 
2607 {
2608  oplist.push_back(CPUI_INT_ZEXT);
2609 }
2610 
2611 int4 RuleBoolZext::applyOp(PcodeOp *op,Funcdata &data)
2612 
2613 {
2614  PcodeOp *boolop1,*multop1,*actionop;
2615  PcodeOp *boolop2,*zextop2,*multop2;
2616  uintb coeff,val;
2617  OpCode opc;
2618  int4 size;
2619 
2620  if (!op->getIn(0)->isWritten()) return 0;
2621  boolop1 = op->getIn(0)->getDef();
2622  if (!boolop1->isCalculatedBool()) return 0;
2623 
2624  multop1 = op->getOut()->loneDescend();
2625  if (multop1 == (PcodeOp *)0) return 0;
2626  if (multop1->code() != CPUI_INT_MULT) return 0;
2627  if (!multop1->getIn(1)->isConstant()) return 0;
2628  coeff = multop1->getIn(1)->getOffset();
2629  if (coeff != calc_mask(multop1->getIn(1)->getSize()))
2630  return 0;
2631  size = multop1->getOut()->getSize();
2632 
2633  // If we reached here, we are Multiplying extended boolean by -1
2634  actionop = multop1->getOut()->loneDescend();
2635  if (actionop == (PcodeOp *)0) return 0;
2636  switch(actionop->code()) {
2637  case CPUI_INT_ADD:
2638  if (!actionop->getIn(1)->isConstant()) return 0;
2639  if (actionop->getIn(1)->getOffset() == 1) {
2640  Varnode *vn;
2641  PcodeOp *newop = data.newOp(1,op->getAddr());
2642  data.opSetOpcode(newop,CPUI_BOOL_NEGATE); // Negate the boolean
2643  vn = data.newUniqueOut(1,newop);
2644  data.opSetInput(newop,boolop1->getOut(),0);
2645  data.opInsertBefore(newop,op);
2646  data.opSetInput(op,vn,0);
2647  data.opRemoveInput(actionop,1); // eliminate the INT_ADD operator
2648  data.opSetOpcode(actionop,CPUI_COPY);
2649  data.opSetInput(actionop,op->getOut(),0); // propagate past the INT_MULT operator
2650  return 1;
2651  }
2652  return 0;
2653  case CPUI_INT_EQUAL:
2654  case CPUI_INT_NOTEQUAL:
2655 
2656  if (actionop->getIn(1)->isConstant()) {
2657  val = actionop->getIn(1)->getOffset();
2658  }
2659  else
2660  return 0;
2661 
2662  // Change comparison of extended boolean to 0 or -1
2663  // to comparison of unextended boolean to 0 or 1
2664  if (val==coeff)
2665  val = 1;
2666  else if (val != 0)
2667  return 0; // Not comparing with 0 or -1
2668 
2669  data.opSetInput(actionop,boolop1->getOut(),0);
2670  data.opSetInput(actionop,data.newConstant(1,val),1);
2671  return 1;
2672  case CPUI_INT_AND:
2673  opc = CPUI_BOOL_AND;
2674  break;
2675  case CPUI_INT_OR:
2676  opc = CPUI_BOOL_OR;
2677  break;
2678  case CPUI_INT_XOR:
2679  opc = CPUI_BOOL_XOR;
2680  break;
2681  default:
2682  return 0;
2683  }
2684 
2685  // Apparently doing logical ops with extended boolean
2686 
2687  // Check that the other side is also an extended boolean
2688  multop2 = (multop1 == actionop->getIn(0)->getDef()) ? actionop->getIn(1)->getDef():actionop->getIn(0)->getDef();
2689  if (multop2==(PcodeOp *)0) return 0;
2690  if (multop2->code() != CPUI_INT_MULT) return 0;
2691  if (!multop2->getIn(1)->isConstant()) return 0;
2692  coeff = multop2->getIn(1)->getOffset();
2693  if (coeff != calc_mask(size))
2694  return 0;
2695  zextop2 = multop2->getIn(0)->getDef();
2696  if (zextop2 == (PcodeOp *)0) return 0;
2697  if (zextop2->code() != CPUI_INT_ZEXT) return 0;
2698  boolop2 = zextop2->getIn(0)->getDef();
2699  if (boolop2 == (PcodeOp *)0) return 0;
2700  if (!boolop2->isCalculatedBool()) return 0;
2701 
2702  // Do the boolean calculation on unextended boolean values
2703  // and then extend the result
2704  PcodeOp *newop = data.newOp(2,actionop->getAddr());
2705  Varnode *newres = data.newUniqueOut(1,newop);
2706  data.opSetOpcode(newop,opc);
2707  data.opSetInput(newop, boolop1->getOut(), 0);
2708  data.opSetInput(newop, boolop2->getOut(), 1);
2709  data.opInsertBefore(newop,actionop);
2710 
2711  PcodeOp *newzext = data.newOp(1,actionop->getAddr());
2712  Varnode *newzout = data.newUniqueOut(size,newzext);
2713  data.opSetOpcode(newzext,CPUI_INT_ZEXT);
2714  data.opSetInput(newzext,newres,0);
2715  data.opInsertBefore(newzext,actionop);
2716 
2717  data.opSetOpcode(actionop,CPUI_INT_MULT);
2718  data.opSetInput(actionop,newzout,0);
2719  data.opSetInput(actionop,data.newConstant(size,coeff),1);
2720  return 1;
2721 }

2735 int4 RuleLogic2Bool::applyOp(PcodeOp *op,Funcdata &data)
2736 
2737 {
2738  PcodeOp *boolop;
2739 
2740  if (!op->getIn(0)->isWritten()) return 0;
2741  boolop = op->getIn(0)->getDef();
2742  if (!boolop->isCalculatedBool()) return 0;
2743  Varnode *in1 = op->getIn(1);
2744  if (!in1->isWritten()) {
2745  if ((!in1->isConstant())||(in1->getOffset()>(uintb)1)) // If one side is a constant 0 or 1, this is boolean
2746  return 0;
2747  }
2748  else {
2749  boolop = op->getIn(1)->getDef();
2750  if (!boolop->isCalculatedBool()) return 0;
2751  }
2752  switch(op->code()) {
2753  case CPUI_INT_AND:
2754  data.opSetOpcode(op,CPUI_BOOL_AND);
2755  break;
2756  case CPUI_INT_OR:
2757  data.opSetOpcode(op,CPUI_BOOL_OR);
2758  break;
2759  case CPUI_INT_XOR:
2760  data.opSetOpcode(op,CPUI_BOOL_XOR);
2761  break;
2762  default:
2763  return 0;
2764  }
2765  return 1;
2766 }

2775 
2776 int4 RuleIndirectCollapse::applyOp(PcodeOp *op,Funcdata &data)
2777 
2778 {
2779  PcodeOp *indop;
2780 
2781  if (op->getIn(1)->getSpace()->getType()!=IPTR_IOP) return 0;
2782  indop = PcodeOp::getOpFromConst(op->getIn(1)->getAddr());
2783 
2784  // Is the indirect effect gone?
2785  if (!indop->isDead()) {
2786  if (indop->code() == CPUI_COPY) { // STORE resolved to a COPY
2787  Varnode *vn1 = indop->getOut();
2788  Varnode *vn2 = op->getOut();
2789  int4 res = vn1->characterizeOverlap(*vn2);
2790  if (res > 0) { // Copy has an effect of some sort
2791  if (res == 2) { // vn1 and vn2 are the same storage -> do complete replace
2792  data.opSetInput(op,vn1,0);
2793  data.opRemoveInput(op,1);
2794  data.opSetOpcode(op,CPUI_COPY);
2795  return 1;
2796  }
2797  data.warning("Ignoring partial resolution of indirect",indop->getAddr());
2798  return 0; // Partial overlap, not sure what to do
2799  }
2800  }
2801  else if (indop->isCall()) {
2802  if (op->isIndirectCreation())
2803  return 0;
2804  // If there are no aliases to a local variable, collapse
2805  if (!op->getOut()->hasNoLocalAlias())
2806  return 0;
2807  }
2808  else
2809  return 0;
2810  }
2811 
2812  data.totalReplace(op->getOut(),op->getIn(0));
2813  data.opDestroy(op); // Get rid of the INDIRECT
2814  return 1;
2815 }

2819 void RuleMultiCollapse::getOpList(vector<uint4> &oplist) const
2820 
2821 {
2822  oplist.push_back(CPUI_MULTIEQUAL);
2823 }
2824 
2825 int4 RuleMultiCollapse::applyOp(PcodeOp *op,Funcdata &data)
2826 
2827 {
2828  vector<Varnode *> skiplist,matchlist;
2829  Varnode *defcopyr,*copyr;
2830  bool func_eq,nofunc;
2831  PcodeOp *newop;
2832  int4 j;
2833 
2834  for(int4 i=0;i<op->numInput();++i) // Everything must be heritaged before collapse
2835  if (!op->getIn(i)->isHeritageKnown()) return 0;
2836 
2837  func_eq = false; // Start assuming absolute equality of branches
2838  nofunc = false; // Functional equalities are initially allowed
2839  defcopyr = (Varnode *)0;
2840  j = 0;
2841  for(int4 i=0;i<op->numInput();++i)
2842  matchlist.push_back(op->getIn(i));
2843  for(int4 i=0;i<op->numInput();++i) { // Find base branch to match
2844  copyr = matchlist[i];
2845  if ((!copyr->isWritten())||(copyr->getDef()->code()!=CPUI_MULTIEQUAL)) {
2846  defcopyr = copyr;
2847  break;
2848  }
2849  }
2850 
2851  bool success = true;
2852  op->getOut()->setMark();
2853  skiplist.push_back(op->getOut());
2854  while( j < matchlist.size() ) {
2855  copyr = matchlist[j++];
2856  if (copyr->isMark()) continue; // A varnode we have seen before
2857  // indicates a loop construct, where the
2858  // value is recurring in the loop without change
2859  // so we treat this as equal to all other branches
2860  // I.e. skip this varnode
2861  if (defcopyr == (Varnode *)0) { // This is now the defining branch
2862  defcopyr = copyr; // all other branches must match
2863  if (defcopyr->isWritten()) {
2864  if (defcopyr->getDef()->code()==CPUI_MULTIEQUAL)
2865  nofunc = true; // MULTIEQUAL cannot match by functional equal
2866  }
2867  else
2868  nofunc = true; // Unwritten cannot match by functional equal
2869  }
2870  else if (*defcopyr == *copyr) continue; // A matching branch
2871  else if ((defcopyr!=copyr)&&(!nofunc)&&functionalEquality(defcopyr,copyr)) {
2872  // Cannot match MULTIEQUAL by functional equality
2873  // if (nofunc) return 0; // Not allowed to match by func equal
2874  func_eq = true; // Now matching by functional equality
2875  continue;
2876  }
2877  else if ((copyr->isWritten())&&(copyr->getDef()->code()==CPUI_MULTIEQUAL)) {
2878  // If the non-matching branch is a MULTIEQUAL
2879  newop = copyr->getDef();
2880  skiplist.push_back(copyr); // We give the branch one last chance and
2881  copyr->setMark();
2882  for(int4 i=0;i<newop->numInput();++i) // add its inputs to list of things to match
2883  matchlist.push_back(newop->getIn(i));
2884  }
2885  else { // A non-matching branch
2886  success = false;
2887  break;
2888  }
2889  }
2890  if (success) {
2891  for(j=0;j<skiplist.size();++j) { // Collapse everything in the skiplist
2892  copyr = skiplist[j];
2893  copyr->clearMark();
2894  op = copyr->getDef();
2895  if (func_eq) { // We have only functional equality
2896  PcodeOp *earliest = earliestUseInBlock(op->getOut(),op->getParent());
2897  newop = defcopyr->getDef(); // We must copy newop (defcopyr)
2898  PcodeOp *substitute = (PcodeOp *)0;
2899  for(int4 i=0;i<newop->numInput();++i) {
2900  Varnode *invn = newop->getIn(i);
2901  if (!invn->isConstant()) {
2902  substitute = cseFindInBlock(newop,invn,op->getParent(),earliest); // Has newop already been copied in this block
2903  break;
2904  }
2905  }
2906  if (substitute != (PcodeOp *)0) { // If it has already been copied,
2907  data.totalReplace(copyr,substitute->getOut()); // just use copy's output as substitute for op
2908  data.opDestroy(op);
2909  }
2910  else { // Otherwise, create a copy
2911  bool needsreinsert = (op->code() == CPUI_MULTIEQUAL);
2912  vector<Varnode *> parms;
2913  for(int4 i=0;i<newop->numInput();++i)
2914  parms.push_back(newop->getIn(i)); // Copy parameters
2915  data.opSetAllInput(op,parms);
2916  data.opSetOpcode(op,newop->code()); // Copy opcode
2917  if (needsreinsert) { // If the op is no longer a MULTIEQUAL
2918  BlockBasic *bl = op->getParent();
2919  data.opUninsert(op);
2920  data.opInsertBegin(op,bl); // Insert AFTER any other MULTIEQUAL
2921  }
2922  }
2923  }
2924  else { // We have absolute equality
2925  data.totalReplace(copyr,defcopyr); // Replace all refs to copyr with defcopyr
2926  data.opDestroy(op); // Get rid of the MULTIEQUAL
2927  }
2928  }
2929  return 1;
2930  }
2931  for(j=0;j<skiplist.size();++j)
2932  skiplist[j]->clearMark();
2933  return 0;
2934 }
2935 
2946 void RuleSborrow::getOpList(vector<uint4> &oplist) const
2947 
2948 {
2949  oplist.push_back(CPUI_INT_SBORROW);
2950 }
2951 
2952 int4 RuleSborrow::applyOp(PcodeOp *op,Funcdata &data)
2953 
2954 {
2955  Varnode *svn = op->getOut();
2956  Varnode *cvn,*avn,*bvn;
2957  list<PcodeOp *>::const_iterator iter;
2958  PcodeOp *compop,*signop,*addop;
2959  int4 zside;
2960 
2961  // Check for trivial case
2962  if ((op->getIn(1)->isConstant()&&op->getIn(1)->getOffset()==0)||
2963  (op->getIn(0)->isConstant()&&op->getIn(0)->getOffset()==0)) {
2964  data.opSetOpcode(op,CPUI_COPY);
2965  data.opSetInput(op,data.newConstant(1,0),0);
2966  data.opRemoveInput(op,1);
2967  return 1;
2968  }
2969  for(iter=svn->beginDescend();iter!=svn->endDescend();++iter) {
2970  compop = *iter;
2971  if ((compop->code()!=CPUI_INT_EQUAL)&&(compop->code()!=CPUI_INT_NOTEQUAL))
2972  continue;
2973  cvn = (compop->getIn(0)==svn) ? compop->getIn(1) : compop->getIn(0);
2974  if (!cvn->isWritten()) continue;
2975  signop = cvn->getDef();
2976  if (signop->code() != CPUI_INT_SLESS) continue;
2977  if (!signop->getIn(0)->constantMatch(0)) {
2978  if (!signop->getIn(1)->constantMatch(0)) continue;
2979  zside = 1;
2980  }
2981  else
2982  zside = 0;
2983  if (!signop->getIn(1-zside)->isWritten()) continue;
2984  addop = signop->getIn(1-zside)->getDef();
2985  if (addop->code() == CPUI_INT_ADD) {
2986  avn = op->getIn(0);
2987  if (functionalEquality(avn,addop->getIn(0)))
2988  bvn = addop->getIn(1);
2989  else if (functionalEquality(avn,addop->getIn(1)))
2990  bvn = addop->getIn(0);
2991  else
2992  continue;
2993  }
2994  else
2995  continue;
2996  if (bvn->isConstant()) {
2997  Address flip(bvn->getSpace(),uintb_negate(bvn->getOffset()-1,bvn->getSize()));
2998  bvn = op->getIn(1);
2999  if (flip != bvn->getAddr()) continue;
3000  }
3001  else if (bvn->isWritten()) {
3002  PcodeOp *otherop = bvn->getDef();
3003  if (otherop->code() == CPUI_INT_MULT) {
3004  if (!otherop->getIn(1)->isConstant()) continue;
3005  if (otherop->getIn(1)->getOffset() != calc_mask(otherop->getIn(1)->getSize())) continue;
3006  bvn = otherop->getIn(0);
3007  }
3008  else if (otherop->code()==CPUI_INT_2COMP)
3009  bvn = otherop->getIn(0);
3010  if (!functionalEquality(bvn,op->getIn(1))) continue;
3011  }
3012  else
3013  continue;
3014  if (compop->code() == CPUI_INT_NOTEQUAL) {
3015  data.opSetOpcode(compop,CPUI_INT_SLESS); // Replace all this with simple less than
3016  data.opSetInput(compop,avn,1-zside);
3017  data.opSetInput(compop,bvn,zside);
3018  }
3019  else {
3020  data.opSetOpcode(compop,CPUI_INT_SLESSEQUAL);
3021  data.opSetInput(compop,avn,zside);
3022  data.opSetInput(compop,bvn,1-zside);
3023  }
3024  return 1;
3025  }
3026  return 0;
3027 }

3038 int4 RuleTrivialShift::applyOp(PcodeOp *op,Funcdata &data)
3039 
3040 {

3042  Varnode *constvn = op->getIn(1);
3043  if (!constvn->isConstant()) return 0; // Must shift by a constant
3044  val = constvn->getOffset();
3045  if (val!=0) {
3046  Varnode *replace;
3047  if (val < 8*op->getIn(0)->getSize()) return 0; // Non-trivial
3048  if (op->code() == CPUI_INT_SRIGHT) return 0; // Cant predict signbit
3049  replace = data.newConstant(op->getIn(0)->getSize(),0);
3050  data.opSetInput(op,replace,0);
3051  }
3052  data.opRemoveInput(op,1);

3074 int4 RuleIdentityEl::applyOp(PcodeOp *op,Funcdata &data)
