3112 int4 RuleShift2Mult::applyOp(PcodeOp *op,Funcdata &data)
3113 
3114 {
3115  int4 flag;
3116  list<PcodeOp *>::const_iterator desc;
3117  Varnode *vn,*constvn;
3118  PcodeOp *arithop;
3119  OpCode opc;
3120  int4 val;
3121 
3122  flag = 0;
3123  vn = op->getOut();
3124  constvn = op->getIn(1);
3125  if (!constvn->isConstant()) return 0; // Shift amount must be a constant
3126  val = constvn->getOffset();
3127  if (val >= 32) // FIXME: This is a little arbitrary. Anything
3128  // this big is probably not an arithmetic multiply
3129  return 0;
3130  arithop = op->getIn(0)->getDef();
3131  desc = vn->beginDescend();
3132  for(;;) {
3133  if (arithop != (PcodeOp *)0) {
3134  opc = arithop->code();
3135  if ((opc==CPUI_INT_ADD)||(opc==CPUI_INT_SUB)||(opc==CPUI_INT_MULT)) {
3136  flag = 1;
3137  break;
3138  }
3139  }
3140  if (desc == vn->endDescend()) break;
3141  arithop = *desc++;
3142  }
3143 
3144  if (flag==0) return 0;
3145  constvn = data.newConstant(vn->getSize(),((uintb)1)<<val);
3146  data.opSetInput(op,constvn,1);
3147  data.opSetOpcode(op,CPUI_INT_MULT);
3148  return 1;

3169 int4 RuleShiftPiece::applyOp(PcodeOp *op,Funcdata &data)
3170 
3171 {
3172  PcodeOp *shiftop,*zextloop,*zexthiop;
3173  Varnode *vn1,*vn2;
3174 
3175  vn1 = op->getIn(0);
3176  if (!vn1->isWritten()) return 0;
3177  vn2 = op->getIn(1);
3178  if (!vn2->isWritten()) return 0;
3179  shiftop = vn1->getDef();
3180  zextloop = vn2->getDef();
3181  if (shiftop->code() != CPUI_INT_LEFT) {
3182  if (zextloop->code() != CPUI_INT_LEFT) return 0;
3183  PcodeOp *tmpop = zextloop;
3184  zextloop = shiftop;
3185  shiftop = tmpop;
3186  }
3187  if (!shiftop->getIn(1)->isConstant()) return 0;
3188  vn1 = shiftop->getIn(0);
3189  if (!vn1->isWritten()) return 0;
3190  zexthiop = vn1->getDef();
3191  if ((zexthiop->code() != CPUI_INT_ZEXT)&&
3192  (zexthiop->code()!= CPUI_INT_SEXT))
3193  return 0;
3194  vn1 = zexthiop->getIn(0);
3195  if (vn1->isFree()) return 0;
3196  int4 sa = shiftop->getIn(1)->getOffset();
3197  int4 concatsize = sa + 8*vn1->getSize();
3198  if (op->getOut()->getSize() * 8 < concatsize) return 0;
3199  if (zextloop->code() != CPUI_INT_ZEXT) {
3200  // This is a special case triggered by CDQ: IDIV
3201  // This would be handled by the base case, but it interacts with RuleSubZext sometimes
3202  if (!vn1->isWritten()) return 0;
3203  PcodeOp *rShiftOp = vn1->getDef(); // Look for s<< #c forming the high piece
3204  if (rShiftOp->code() != CPUI_INT_SRIGHT) return 0;
3205  if (!rShiftOp->getIn(1)->isConstant()) return 0;
3206  vn2 = rShiftOp->getIn(0);
3207  if (!vn2->isWritten()) return 0;
3208  PcodeOp *subop = vn2->getDef();
3209  if (subop->code() != CPUI_SUBPIECE) return 0; // SUBPIECE connects high and low parts
3210  if (subop->getIn(1)->getOffset() != 0) return 0; // (must be low part)
3211  Varnode *bigVn = zextloop->getOut();
3212  if (subop->getIn(0) != bigVn) return 0; // Verify we have link thru SUBPIECE with low part
3213  int4 rsa = (int4)rShiftOp->getIn(1)->getOffset();
3214  if (rsa != vn2->getSize() * 8 -1) return 0; // Arithmetic shift must copy sign-bit thru whole high part
3215  if ((bigVn->getNZMask() >> sa) != 0) return 0; // The original most significant bytes must be zero
3216  if (sa != 8*(vn2->getSize())) return 0;
3217  data.opSetOpcode(op,CPUI_INT_SEXT); // Original op is simply a sign extension of low part
3218  data.opSetInput(op,vn2,0);
3219  data.opRemoveInput(op,1);
3220  return 1;
3221  }
3222  vn2 = zextloop->getIn(0);
3223  if (vn2->isFree()) return 0;
3224  if (sa != 8*(vn2->getSize())) return 0;
3225  if (concatsize == op->getOut()->getSize() * 8) {
3226  data.opSetOpcode(op,CPUI_PIECE);
3227  data.opSetInput(op,vn1,0);
3228  data.opSetInput(op,vn2,1);
3229  }
3230  else {
3231  PcodeOp *newop = data.newOp(2,op->getAddr());
3232  data.newUniqueOut(concatsize/8,newop);
3233  data.opSetOpcode(newop,CPUI_PIECE);
3234  data.opSetInput(newop,vn1,0);
3235  data.opSetInput(newop,vn2,1);
3236  data.opInsertBefore(newop,op);
3237  data.opSetOpcode(op,zexthiop->code());
3238  data.opRemoveInput(op,1);
3239  data.opSetInput(op,newop->getOut(),0);
3240  }
3241  return 1;
3242 }

3246 int4 RuleCollapseConstants::applyOp(PcodeOp *op,Funcdata &data)
3247 
3248 {
3249  int4 i;
3250  Varnode *vn;
3251 
3252  if (!op->isCollapsible()) return 0; // Expression must be collapsible
3253 
3254  Address newval;
3255  bool markedInput = false;
3256  try {
3257  newval = data.getArch()->getConstant(op->collapse(markedInput));
3258  }
3259  catch(LowlevelError &err) {
3260  data.opSetFlag(op,PcodeOp::nocollapse); // Dont know how or dont want to collapse further
3261  return 0;
3262  }
3263 
3264  vn = data.newVarnode(op->getOut()->getSize(),newval); // Create new collapsed constant
3265  if (markedInput) {
3266  op->collapseConstantSymbol(vn);
3267  }
3268  for(i=op->numInput()-1;i>0;--i)
3269  data.opRemoveInput(op,i); // unlink old constants
3270  data.opSetInput(op,vn,0); // Link in new collapsed constant
3271  data.opSetOpcode(op,CPUI_COPY); // Change ourselves to a copy
3272 
3273  return 1;
3274 }

3287 int4 RuleTransformCpool::applyOp(PcodeOp *op,Funcdata &data)
3288 
3289 {
3290  if (op->isCpoolTransformed()) return 0; // Already visited
3291  data.opSetFlag(op,PcodeOp::is_cpool_transformed); // Mark our visit
3292  vector<uintb> refs;
3293  for(int4 i=1;i<op->numInput();++i)
3294  refs.push_back(op->getIn(i)->getOffset());
3295  const CPoolRecord *rec = data.getArch()->cpool->getRecord(refs); // Recover the record
3296  if (rec != (const CPoolRecord *)0) {
3297  if (rec->getTag() == CPoolRecord::instance_of) {
3298  data.opSetFlag(op,PcodeOp::calculated_bool);
3299  }
3300  else if (rec->getTag() == CPoolRecord::primitive) {
3301  int4 sz = op->getOut()->getSize();
3302  Varnode *cvn = data.newConstant(sz,rec->getValue() & calc_mask(sz));
3303  cvn->updateType(rec->getType(),true,true);
3304  while(op->numInput() > 1) {
3305  data.opRemoveInput(op,op->numInput()-1);
3306  }
3307  data.opSetOpcode(op,CPUI_COPY);
3308  data.opSetInput(op,cvn,0);
3309  return 1;
3310  }
3311  data.opInsertInput(op,data.newConstant(4,rec->getTag()),op->numInput());
3312  }
3313  return 1;
3314 }

3318 int4 RulePropagateCopy::applyOp(PcodeOp *op,Funcdata &data)
3319 
3320 {
3321  int4 i;
3322  PcodeOp *copyop;
3323  Varnode *vn,*invn;
3324  OpCode opc;
3325 
3326  opc = op->code();
3327  if (opc==CPUI_RETURN) return 0; // Preserve the address of return variable
3328 // else if (opc == CPUI_INDIRECT) {
3329 // if (op->Output()->isAddrForce()) return 0;
3330 // }
3331  for(i=0;i<op->numInput();++i) {
3332  vn = op->getIn(i);
3333  if (!vn->isWritten()) continue; // Varnode must be written to
3334 
3335  copyop = vn->getDef();
3336  if (copyop->code()!=CPUI_COPY)
3337  continue; // not a propagating instruction
3338 
3339  invn = copyop->getIn(0);
3340  if (!invn->isHeritageKnown()) continue; // Don't propagate free's away from their first use
3341  if (invn == vn)
3342  throw LowlevelError("Self-defined varnode");
3343  if (op->isMarker()) {
3344  if (invn->isConstant()) continue; // Don't propagate constants into markers
3345  if (invn->isAddrTied() && op->getOut()->isAddrTied() &&
3346  (op->getOut()->getAddr() != invn->getAddr()))
3347  continue; // We must not allow merging of different addrtieds
3348  }
3349  data.opSetInput(op,invn,i); // otherwise propagate just a single copy
3350  return 1;
3351  }
3352  return 0;
3353 }

3385

3404  data.opSetInput(op,data.newConstant(vn1->getSize(),off),0); // Put the new constant in first position

3446 int4 RuleXorCollapse::applyOp(PcodeOp *op,Funcdata &data)
3447 
3448 {
3449  uintb coeff1,coeff2;
3450 
3451  if (!op->getIn(1)->isConstant()) return 0;
3452  PcodeOp *xorop = op->getIn(0)->getDef();
3453  if (xorop == (PcodeOp *)0) return 0;
3454  if (xorop->code() != CPUI_INT_XOR) return 0;
3455  if (op->getIn(0)->loneDescend() == (PcodeOp *)0) return 0;
3456  coeff1 = op->getIn(1)->getOffset();
3457  Varnode *xorvn = xorop->getIn(1);
3458  if (xorop->getIn(0)->isFree()) return 0; // This will be propagated
3459  if (!xorvn->isConstant()) {
3460  if (coeff1 != 0) return 0;
3461  if (xorvn->isFree()) return 0;
3462  data.opSetInput(op,xorvn,1); // Move term to other side
3463  data.opSetInput(op,xorop->getIn(0),0);
3464  return 1;
3465  }
3466  coeff2 = xorvn->getOffset();
3467  if (coeff2 == 0) return 0;
3468  data.opSetInput(op,data.newConstant(op->getIn(1)->getSize(),coeff1^coeff2),1);
3469  data.opSetInput(op,xorop->getIn(0),0);
3470  return 1;
3471 }

3486 
3487 int4 RuleAddMultCollapse::applyOp(PcodeOp *op,Funcdata &data)
3488 
3489 {
3490  Varnode *c[2]; // Constant varnodes
3491  Varnode *sub,*sub2,*newvn;
3492  PcodeOp *subop;
3493  OpCode opc;
3494 
3495  opc = op->code();
3496  // Constant is in c[0], other is in sub
3497  c[0] = op->getIn(1);
3498  if (!c[0]->isConstant()) return 0; // Neither input is a constant
3499  sub = op->getIn(0);
3500  // Find other constant one level down
3501  if (!sub->isWritten()) return 0;
3502  subop = sub->getDef();
3503  if (subop->code() != opc) return 0; // Must be same exact operation
3504  c[1] = subop->getIn(1);
3505  if (!c[1]->isConstant()) {
3506  // a = ((stackbase + c[1]) + othervn) + c[0] => (stackbase + c[0] + c[1]) + othervn
3507  // This lets two constant offsets get added together even in the case where there is:
3508  // another term getting added in AND
3509  // the result of the intermediate sum is used more than once (otherwise collectterms should pick it up)
3510  if (opc != CPUI_INT_ADD) return 0;
3511  Varnode *othervn,*basevn;
3512  PcodeOp *baseop;
3513  for(int4 i=0;i<2;++i) {
3514  othervn = subop->getIn(i);
3515  if (othervn->isConstant()) continue;
3516  if (othervn->isFree()) continue;
3517  sub2 = subop->getIn(1-i);
3518  if (!sub2->isWritten()) continue;
3519  baseop = sub2->getDef();
3520  if (baseop->code() != CPUI_INT_ADD) continue;
3521  c[1] = baseop->getIn(1);
3522  if (!c[1]->isConstant()) continue;
3523  basevn = baseop->getIn(0);
3524  if (!basevn->isSpacebase()) continue; // Only apply this particular case if we are adding to a base pointer
3525  if (!basevn->isInput()) continue; // because this adds a new add operation
3526 
3527  uintb val = op->getOpcode()->evaluateBinary(c[0]->getSize(),c[0]->getSize(),c[0]->getOffset(),c[1]->getOffset());
3528  newvn = data.newConstant(c[0]->getSize(),val);
3529  PcodeOp *newop = data.newOp(2,op->getAddr());
3530  data.opSetOpcode(newop,CPUI_INT_ADD);
3531  Varnode *newout = data.newUniqueOut(c[0]->getSize(),newop);
3532  data.opSetInput(newop,basevn,0);
3533  data.opSetInput(newop,newvn,1);
3534  data.opInsertBefore(newop,op);
3535  data.opSetInput(op,newout,0);
3536  data.opSetInput(op,othervn,1);
3537  return 1;
3538  }
3539  return 0;
3540  }
3541  sub2 = subop->getIn(0);
3542  if (sub2->isFree()) return 0;
3543 
3544  uintb val = op->getOpcode()->evaluateBinary(c[0]->getSize(),c[0]->getSize(),c[0]->getOffset(),c[1]->getOffset());
3545  newvn = data.newConstant(c[0]->getSize(),val);
3546  data.opSetInput(op,newvn,1); // Replace c[0] with c[0]+c[1] or c[0]*c[1]
3547  data.opSetInput(op,sub2,0); // Replace sub with sub2
3548  return 1;
3549 }

3559 AddrSpace *RuleLoadVarnode::correctSpacebase(Architecture *glb,Varnode *vn,AddrSpace *spc)
3560 
3561 {
3562  if (!vn->isSpacebase()) return (AddrSpace *)0;
3563  if (vn->isConstant()) // We have a global pseudo spacebase
3564  return spc; // Associate with load/stored space
3565  if (!vn->isInput()) return (AddrSpace *)0;
3566  AddrSpace *assoc = glb->getSpaceBySpacebase(vn->getAddr(),vn->getSize());
3567  if (assoc->getContain() != spc) // Loading off right space?
3568  return (AddrSpace *)0;
3569  return assoc;
3570 }

3580 AddrSpace *RuleLoadVarnode::vnSpacebase(Architecture *glb,Varnode *vn,uintb &val,AddrSpace *spc)
3581 
3582 {
3583  PcodeOp *op;
3584  Varnode *vn1,*vn2;
3585  AddrSpace *retspace;
3586 
3587  retspace = correctSpacebase(glb,vn,spc);
3588  if (retspace != (AddrSpace *)0) {
3589  val = 0;
3590  return retspace;
3591  }
3592  if (!vn->isWritten()) return (AddrSpace *)0;
3593  op = vn->getDef();
3594  if (op->code() != CPUI_INT_ADD) return (AddrSpace *)0;
3595  vn1 = op->getIn(0);
3596  vn2 = op->getIn(1);
3597  retspace = correctSpacebase(glb,vn1,spc);
3598  if (retspace != (AddrSpace *)0) {
3599  if (vn2->isConstant()) {
3600  val = vn2->getOffset();
3601  return retspace;
3602  }
3603  return (AddrSpace *)0;
3604  }
3605  retspace = correctSpacebase(glb,vn2,spc);
3606  if (retspace != (AddrSpace *)0) {
3607  if (vn1->isConstant()) {
3608  val = vn1->getOffset();
3609  return retspace;
3610  }
3611  }
3612  return (AddrSpace *)0;
3613 }

3622 AddrSpace *RuleLoadVarnode::checkSpacebase(Architecture *glb,PcodeOp *op,uintb &offoff)
3623 
3624 {
3625  Varnode *offvn;
3626  AddrSpace *loadspace;
3627 
3628  offvn = op->getIn(1); // Address offset
3629  loadspace = Address::getSpaceFromConst(op->getIn(0)->getAddr()); // Space being loaded/stored
3630  // Treat segmentop as part of load/store
3631  if (offvn->isWritten()&&(offvn->getDef()->code()==CPUI_SEGMENTOP)) {
3632  offvn = offvn->getDef()->getIn(2);
3633  // If we are looking for a spacebase (i.e. stackpointer)
3634  // Then currently we COMPLETELY IGNORE the base part of the
3635  // segment. We assume it is all correct.
3636  // If the segmentop inner is constant, we are NOT looking
3637  // for a spacebase, and we do not igore the base. If the
3638  // base is also constant, we let RuleSegmentOp reduce
3639  // the whole segmentop to a constant. If the base
3640  // is not constant, we are not ready for a fixed address.
3641  if (offvn->isConstant())
3642  return (AddrSpace *)0;
3643  }
3644  else if (offvn->isConstant()) { // Check for constant
3645  offoff = offvn->getOffset();
3646  return loadspace;
3647  }
3648  return vnSpacebase(glb,offvn,offoff,loadspace);
3649 }

3663 int4 RuleLoadVarnode::applyOp(PcodeOp *op,Funcdata &data)

3677  data.opSetInput(op,newvn,0);
3678  data.opRemoveInput(op,1);
3679  data.opSetOpcode(op, CPUI_COPY );
3680  Varnode *refvn = op->getOut();
3681  if (refvn->isSpacebasePlaceholder()) {

3684  if (op != (PcodeOp *)0) {
3685  FuncCallSpecs *fc = data.getCallSpecs(op);
3686  if (fc != (FuncCallSpecs *)0)
3687  fc->resolveSpacebaseRelative(data,refvn);
3688  }
3689  }
3690  return 1;

3781 int4 RuleSubExtComm::applyOp(PcodeOp *op,Funcdata &data)
3782 
3783 {
3784  int4 subcut = (int4)op->getIn(1)->getOffset();
3785  Varnode *base = op->getIn(0);
3786  // Make sure subpiece preserves most sig bytes
3787  if (op->getOut()->getSize()+subcut != base->getSize()) return 0;
3788  if (!base->isWritten()) return 0;
3789  PcodeOp *extop = base->getDef();
3790  if ((extop->code()!=CPUI_INT_ZEXT)&&(extop->code()!=CPUI_INT_SEXT))
3791  return 0;
3792  Varnode *invn = extop->getIn(0);
3793  if (invn->isFree()) return 0;
3794  if (subcut >= invn->getSize()) return 0;
3795 
3796  PcodeOp *newop = data.newOp(2,op->getAddr());
3797  data.opSetOpcode(newop,CPUI_SUBPIECE);
3798  Varnode *newvn = data.newUniqueOut(invn->getSize()-subcut,newop);
3799  data.opSetInput(newop,data.newConstant(op->getIn(1)->getSize(),(uintb)subcut),1);
3800  data.opSetInput(newop,invn,0);
3801  data.opInsertBefore(newop,op);
3802 
3803  data.opRemoveInput(op,1);
3804  data.opSetOpcode(op,extop->code());
3805  data.opSetInput(op,newvn,0);
3806  return 1;
3807 }

3821 
3831 bool RuleSubCommute::cancelExtensions(PcodeOp *longform,PcodeOp *subOp,Varnode *ext0In,Varnode *ext1In,Funcdata &data)
3832 
3833 {
3834  if (ext0In->getSize() != ext1In->getSize()) return false; // Sizes must match
3835  if (ext0In->isFree()) return false; // Must be able to propagate inputs
3836  if (ext1In->isFree()) return false;
3837  Varnode *outvn = longform->getOut();
3838  if (outvn->loneDescend() != subOp) return false; // Must be exactly one output to SUBPIECE
3839  data.opUnsetOutput(longform);
3840  outvn = data.newUniqueOut(ext0In->getSize(),longform); // Create truncated form of longform output
3841  data.opSetInput(longform,ext0In,0);
3842  data.opSetInput(longform,ext1In,1);
3843  data.opSetInput(subOp,outvn,0);
3844  return true;
3845 }
3846 
3847 int4 RuleSubCommute::applyOp(PcodeOp *op,Funcdata &data)
3848 
3849 {
3850  Varnode *base,*vn,*newvn,*outvn;
3851  PcodeOp *longform,*newsub,*prevop;
3852  int4 i,j,offset,insize;
3853 
3854  base = op->getIn(0);
3855  if (!base->isWritten()) return 0;
3856  offset = op->getIn(1)->getOffset();
3857  outvn = op->getOut();
3858  if (outvn->isPrecisLo()||outvn->isPrecisHi()) return 0;
3859  insize = base->getSize();
3860  longform = base->getDef();
3861  j = -1;
3862  switch( longform->code() ) { // Determine if this op commutes with SUBPIECE
3863  // case CPUI_COPY:
3864  case CPUI_INT_LEFT:
3865  j = 1; // Special processing for shift amount param
3866  if (offset != 0) return 0;
3867  if (!longform->getIn(0)->isWritten()) return 0;
3868  prevop = longform->getIn(0)->getDef();
3869  if (prevop->code()==CPUI_INT_ZEXT) {
3870  }
3871  else if (prevop->code()==CPUI_PIECE) {
3872  }
3873  else
3874  return 0;
3875  break;
3876  case CPUI_INT_REM:
3877  case CPUI_INT_DIV:
3878  {
3879  // Only commutes if inputs are zero extended
3880  if (offset != 0) return 0;
3881  if (!longform->getIn(0)->isWritten()) return 0;
3882  PcodeOp *zext0 = longform->getIn(0)->getDef();
3883  if (zext0->code() != CPUI_INT_ZEXT) return 0;
3884  Varnode *zext0In = zext0->getIn(0);
3885  if (longform->getIn(1)->isWritten()) {
3886  PcodeOp *zext1 = longform->getIn(1)->getDef();
3887  if (zext1->code() != CPUI_INT_ZEXT) return 0;
3888  Varnode *zext1In = zext1->getIn(0);
3889  if (zext1In->getSize() > outvn->getSize() || zext0In->getSize() > outvn->getSize()) {
3890  // Special case where we need a PARTIAL commute of the SUBPIECE
3891  // SUBPIECE cancels the ZEXTs, but there is still some SUBPIECE left
3892  if (cancelExtensions(longform,op,zext0In,zext1In,data)) // Cancel ZEXT operations
3893  return 1; // Leave SUBPIECE intact
3894  return 0;
3895  }
3896  // If ZEXT sizes are both not bigger, go ahead and commute SUBPIECE (fallthru)
3897  }
3898  else if (longform->getIn(1)->isConstant() && (zext0In->getSize() <= outvn->getSize())) {
3899  uintb val = longform->getIn(1)->getOffset();
3900  uintb smallval = val & calc_mask(outvn->getSize());
3901  if (val != smallval)
3902  return 0;
3903  }
3904  else
3905  return 0;
3906  break;
3907  }
3908  case CPUI_INT_SREM:
3909  case CPUI_INT_SDIV:
3910  {
3911  // Only commutes if inputs are sign extended
3912  if (offset != 0) return 0;
3913  if (!longform->getIn(0)->isWritten()) return 0;
3914  PcodeOp *sext0 = longform->getIn(0)->getDef();
3915  if (sext0->code() != CPUI_INT_SEXT) return 0;
3916  Varnode *sext0In = sext0->getIn(0);
3917  if (longform->getIn(1)->isWritten()) {
3918  PcodeOp *sext1 = longform->getIn(1)->getDef();
3919  if (sext1->code() != CPUI_INT_SEXT) return 0;
3920  Varnode *sext1In = sext1->getIn(0);
3921  if (sext1In->getSize() > outvn->getSize() || sext0In->getSize() > outvn->getSize()) {
3922  // Special case where we need a PARTIAL commute of the SUBPIECE
3923  // SUBPIECE cancels the SEXTs, but there is still some SUBPIECE left
3924  if (cancelExtensions(longform,op,sext0In,sext1In,data)) // Cancel SEXT operations
3925  return 1; // Leave SUBPIECE intact
3926  return 0;
3927  }
3928  // If SEXT sizes are both not bigger, go ahead and commute SUBPIECE (fallthru)
3929  }
3930  else if (longform->getIn(1)->isConstant() && (sext0In->getSize() <= outvn->getSize())) {
3931  uintb val = longform->getIn(1)->getOffset();
3932  uintb smallval = val & calc_mask(outvn->getSize());
3933  smallval = sign_extend(smallval,outvn->getSize(),insize);
3934  if (val != smallval)
3935  return 0;
3936  }
3937  else
3938  return 0;
3939  break;
3940  }
3941  case CPUI_INT_ADD:
3942  case CPUI_INT_MULT:
3943  // These only commute with least significant SUBPIECE
3944  if (offset != 0) return 0;
3945  break;
3946  // Bitwise ops, type of subpiece doesnt matter
3947  case CPUI_INT_NEGATE:
3948  case CPUI_INT_XOR:
3949  case CPUI_INT_AND:
3950  case CPUI_INT_OR:
3951  break;
3952  default: // Most ops don't commute
3953  return 0;
3954  }
3955 
3956  // Make sure no other piece of base is getting used
3957  if (base->loneDescend() != op) return 0;
3958 
3959  if (offset == 0) { // Look for overlap with RuleSubZext
3960  PcodeOp *nextop = outvn->loneDescend();
3961  if ((nextop != (PcodeOp *)0)&&(nextop->code() == CPUI_INT_ZEXT)) {
3962  if (nextop->getOut()->getSize() == insize)
3963  return 0;
3964  }
3965  }
3966 
3967  for(i=0;i<longform->numInput();++i) {
3968  vn = longform->getIn(i);
3969  if (i!=j) {
3970  newsub = data.newOp(2,op->getAddr()); // Commuted SUBPIECE op
3971  data.opSetOpcode(newsub,CPUI_SUBPIECE);
3972  newvn = data.newUniqueOut(outvn->getSize(),newsub); // New varnode is subpiece
3973  data.opSetInput(longform,newvn,i);
3974  data.opSetInput(newsub,vn,0); // of old varnode
3975  data.opSetInput(newsub,data.newConstant(4,offset),1);
3976  data.opInsertBefore(newsub,longform);
3977  }
3978  }
3979  data.opSetOutput(longform,outvn);
3980  data.opDestroy(op); // Get rid of old SUBPIECE
3981  return 1;
3982 }

3991 
3992 {
3993  oplist.push_back(CPUI_PIECE);
3994 }
3995 
3996 int4 RuleConcatCommute::applyOp(PcodeOp *op,Funcdata &data)
3997 
3998 {
3999  Varnode *vn;
4000  Varnode *hi,*lo,*newvn;
4001  PcodeOp *logicop,*newconcat;
4002  OpCode opc;
4003  uintb val;
4004 
4005  for(int4 i=0;i<2;++i) {
4006  vn = op->getIn(i);
4007  if (!vn->isWritten()) continue;
4008  logicop = vn->getDef();
4009  opc = logicop->code();
4010  if ((opc == CPUI_INT_OR)||(opc == CPUI_INT_XOR)) {
4011  if (!logicop->getIn(1)->isConstant()) continue;
4012  val = logicop->getIn(1)->getOffset();
4013  if (i==0) {
4014  hi = logicop->getIn(0);
4015  lo = op->getIn(1);
4016  val <<= 8*lo->getSize();
4017  }
4018  else {
4019  hi = op->getIn(0);
4020  lo = logicop->getIn(0);
4021  }
4022  }
4023  else if (opc == CPUI_INT_AND) {
4024  if (!logicop->getIn(1)->isConstant()) continue;
4025  val = logicop->getIn(1)->getOffset();
4026  if (i==0) {
4027  hi = logicop->getIn(0);
4028  lo = op->getIn(1);
4029  val <<= 8*lo->getSize();
4030  val |= calc_mask(lo->getSize());
4031  }
4032  else {
4033  hi = op->getIn(0);
4034  lo = logicop->getIn(0);
4035  val |= (calc_mask(hi->getSize()) << 8*lo->getSize());
4036  }
4037  }
4038  else
4039  continue;
4040  if (hi->isFree()) continue;
4041  if (lo->isFree()) continue;
4042  newconcat = data.newOp(2,op->getAddr());
4043  data.opSetOpcode(newconcat,CPUI_PIECE);
4044  newvn = data.newUniqueOut(op->getOut()->getSize(),newconcat);
4045  data.opSetInput(newconcat,hi,0);
4046  data.opSetInput(newconcat,lo,1);
4047  data.opInsertBefore(newconcat,op);
4048  data.opSetOpcode(op,opc);
4049  data.opSetInput(op,newvn,0);
4050  data.opSetInput(op,data.newConstant(newvn->getSize(),val),1);
4051  return 1;
4052  }
4053  return 0;
4054 }

4120 int4 RuleConcatZext::applyOp(PcodeOp *op,Funcdata &data)
4121 
4122 {
4123  PcodeOp *zextop;
4124  Varnode *hi,*lo;
4125 
4126  hi = op->getIn(0);
4127  if (!hi->isWritten()) return 0;
4128  zextop = hi->getDef();
4129  if (zextop->code() != CPUI_INT_ZEXT) return 0;
4130  hi = zextop->getIn(0);
4131  lo = op->getIn(1);
4132  if (hi->isFree()) return 0;
4133  if (lo->isFree()) return 0;
4134 
4135  // Create new (earlier) concat out of hi and lo
4136  PcodeOp *newconcat = data.newOp(2,op->getAddr());
4137  data.opSetOpcode(newconcat,CPUI_PIECE);
4138  Varnode *newvn = data.newUniqueOut(hi->getSize()+lo->getSize(),newconcat);
4139  data.opSetInput(newconcat,hi,0);
4140  data.opSetInput(newconcat,lo,1);
4141  data.opInsertBefore(newconcat,op);
4142 
4143  // Change original op into a ZEXT
4144  data.opRemoveInput(op,1);
4145  data.opSetInput(op,newvn,0);
4146  data.opSetOpcode(op,CPUI_INT_ZEXT);
4147  return 1;
4148 }

4191 int4 RuleZextShiftZext::applyOp(PcodeOp *op,Funcdata &data)
4192 
4193 {
4194  Varnode *invn = op->getIn(0);
4195  if (!invn->isWritten()) return 0;
4196  PcodeOp *shiftop = invn->getDef();
4197  if (shiftop->code() == CPUI_INT_ZEXT) { // Check for ZEXT( ZEXT( a ) )
4198  Varnode *vn = shiftop->getIn(0);
4199  if (vn->isFree()) return 0;
4200  if (invn->loneDescend() != op) // Only propagate if -op- is only use of -invn-
4201  return 0;
4202  data.opSetInput(op,vn,0);
4203  return 1;
4204  }
4205  if (shiftop->code() != CPUI_INT_LEFT) return 0;
4206  if (!shiftop->getIn(1)->isConstant()) return 0;
4207  if (!shiftop->getIn(0)->isWritten()) return 0;
4208  PcodeOp *zext2op = shiftop->getIn(0)->getDef();
4209  if (zext2op->code() != CPUI_INT_ZEXT) return 0;
4210  Varnode *rootvn = zext2op->getIn(0);
4211  if (rootvn->isFree()) return 0;
4212 
4213  uintb sa = shiftop->getIn(1)->getOffset();
4214  if (sa > 8* (uintb)(zext2op->getOut()->getSize() - rootvn->getSize()))
4215  return 0; // Shift might lose bits off the top
4216  PcodeOp *newop = data.newOp(1,op->getAddr());
4217  data.opSetOpcode(newop,CPUI_INT_ZEXT);
4218  Varnode *outvn = data.newUniqueOut(op->getOut()->getSize(),newop);
4219  data.opSetInput(newop,rootvn,0);
4220  data.opSetOpcode(op,CPUI_INT_LEFT);
4221  data.opSetInput(op,outvn,0);
4222  data.opInsertInput(op,data.newConstant(4,sa),1);
4223  data.opInsertBefore(newop,op);
4224  return 1;
4225 }

4231 void RuleShiftAnd::getOpList(vector<uint4> &oplist) const
4232 
4233 {
4234  oplist.push_back(CPUI_INT_RIGHT);
4235  oplist.push_back(CPUI_INT_LEFT);
4236  oplist.push_back(CPUI_INT_MULT);
4237 }
4238 
4239 int4 RuleShiftAnd::applyOp(PcodeOp *op,Funcdata &data)
4240 
4241 {
4242  Varnode *cvn = op->getIn(1);
4243  if (!cvn->isConstant()) return 0;
4244  Varnode *shiftin = op->getIn(0);
4245  if (!shiftin->isWritten()) return 0;
4246  PcodeOp *andop = shiftin->getDef();
4247  if (andop->code() != CPUI_INT_AND) return 0;
4248  if (shiftin->loneDescend() != op) return 0;
4249  Varnode *maskvn = andop->getIn(1);
4250  if (!maskvn->isConstant()) return 0;
4251  uintb mask = maskvn->getOffset();
4252  Varnode *invn = andop->getIn(0);
4253  if (invn->isFree()) return 0;
4254 
4255  OpCode opc = op->code();
4256  int4 sa;
4257  if ((opc == CPUI_INT_RIGHT)||(opc == CPUI_INT_LEFT))
4258  sa = (int4)cvn->getOffset();
4259  else {
4260  sa = leastsigbit_set(cvn->getOffset()); // Make sure the multiply is really a shift
4261  if (sa <= 0) return 0;
4262  uintb testval = 1;
4263  testval <<= sa;
4264  if (testval != cvn->getOffset()) return 0;
4265  opc = CPUI_INT_LEFT; // Treat CPUI_INT_MULT as CPUI_INT_LEFT
4266  }
4267  uintb nzm = invn->getNZMask();
4268  uintb fullmask = calc_mask(invn->getSize());
4269  if (opc == CPUI_INT_RIGHT) {
4270  nzm >>= sa;
4271  mask >>= sa;
4272  }
4273  else {
4274  nzm <<= sa;
4275  mask <<= sa;
4276  nzm &= fullmask;
4277  mask &= fullmask;
4278  }
4279  if ((mask & nzm) != nzm) return 0;
4280  data.opSetOpcode(andop,CPUI_COPY); // AND effectively does nothing, so we change it to a copy
4281  data.opRemoveInput(andop,1);
4282  return 1;
4283 }

4292 
4293 int4 RuleConcatZero::applyOp(PcodeOp *op,Funcdata &data)
4294 
4295 {
4296  if (!op->getIn(1)->isConstant()) return 0;
4297  if (op->getIn(1)->getOffset() != 0) return 0;
4298 
4299  int4 sa = 8*op->getIn(1)->getSize();
4300  Varnode *highvn = op->getIn(0);
4301  PcodeOp *newop = data.newOp(1,op->getAddr());
4302  Varnode *outvn = data.newUniqueOut(op->getOut()->getSize(),newop);
4303  data.opSetOpcode(newop,CPUI_INT_ZEXT);
4304  data.opSetOpcode(op,CPUI_INT_LEFT);
4305  data.opSetInput(op,outvn,0);
4306  data.opSetInput(op,data.newConstant(4,sa),1);
4307  data.opSetInput(newop,highvn,0);
4308  data.opInsertBefore(newop,op);
4309  return 1;
4310 }

4314 void RuleConcatLeftShift::getOpList(vector<uint4> &oplist) const
4315 
4316 {
4317  oplist.push_back(CPUI_PIECE);
4318 }
4319 
4320 int4 RuleConcatLeftShift::applyOp(PcodeOp *op,Funcdata &data)
4321 
4322 {
4323  Varnode *vn2 = op->getIn(1);
4324  if (!vn2->isWritten()) return 0;
4325  PcodeOp *shiftop = vn2->getDef();
4326  if (shiftop->code() != CPUI_INT_LEFT) return 0;
4327  if (!shiftop->getIn(1)->isConstant()) return 0; // Must be a constant shift
4328  int4 sa = shiftop->getIn(1)->getOffset();
4329  if ((sa&7)!=0) return 0; // Not a multiple of 8
4330  Varnode *tmpvn = shiftop->getIn(0);
4331  if (!tmpvn->isWritten()) return 0;
4332  PcodeOp *zextop = tmpvn->getDef();
4333  if (zextop->code() != CPUI_INT_ZEXT) return 0;
4334  Varnode *b = zextop->getIn(0);
4335  if (b->isFree()) return 0;
4336  Varnode *vn1 = op->getIn(0);
4337  if (vn1->isFree()) return 0;
4338  sa /= 8; // bits to bytes
4339  if (sa + b->getSize() != tmpvn->getSize()) return 0; // Must shift to most sig boundary
4340 
4341  PcodeOp *newop = data.newOp(2,op->getAddr());
4342  data.opSetOpcode(newop,CPUI_PIECE);
4343  Varnode *newout = data.newUniqueOut(vn1->getSize() + b->getSize(),newop);
4344  data.opSetInput(newop,vn1,0);
4345  data.opSetInput(newop,b,1);
4346  data.opInsertBefore(newop,op);
4347  data.opSetInput(op,newout,0);
4348  data.opSetInput(op,data.newConstant(op->getOut()->getSize()-newout->getSize() ,0),1);
4349  return 1;
4350 }

4359 void RuleSubZext::getOpList(vector<uint4> &oplist) const
4360 
4361 {
4362  oplist.push_back(CPUI_INT_ZEXT);
4363 }
4364 
4365 int4 RuleSubZext::applyOp(PcodeOp *op,Funcdata &data)
4366 
4367 {
4368  Varnode *subvn,*basevn,*constvn;
4369  PcodeOp *subop;
4370  uintb val;
4371 
4372  subvn = op->getIn(0);
4373  if (!subvn->isWritten()) return 0;
4374  subop = subvn->getDef();
4375  if (subop->code() == CPUI_SUBPIECE) {
4376  basevn = subop->getIn(0);
4377  if (basevn->isFree()) return 0;
4378  if (basevn->getSize() != op->getOut()->getSize()) return 0; // Truncating then extending to same size
4379  if (subop->getIn(1)->getOffset() != 0) { // If truncating from middle
4380  if (subvn->loneDescend() != op) return 0; // and there is no other use of the truncated value
4381  Varnode *newvn = data.newUnique(basevn->getSize(),(Datatype *)0);
4382  constvn = subop->getIn(1);
4383  uintb val = constvn->getOffset() * 8;
4384  data.opSetInput(op,newvn,0);
4385  data.opSetOpcode(subop,CPUI_INT_RIGHT); // Convert the truncation to a shift
4386  data.opSetInput(subop,data.newConstant(constvn->getSize(),val),1);
4387  data.opSetOutput(subop,newvn);
4388  }
4389  else
4390  data.opSetInput(op,basevn,0); // Otherwise, bypass the truncation entirely
4391  val = calc_mask(subvn->getSize());
4392  constvn = data.newConstant(basevn->getSize(),val);
4393  data.opSetOpcode(op,CPUI_INT_AND);
4394  data.opInsertInput(op,constvn,1);
4395  return 1;
4396  }
4397  else if (subop->code() == CPUI_INT_RIGHT) {
4398  PcodeOp *shiftop = subop;
4399  if (!shiftop->getIn(1)->isConstant()) return 0;
4400  Varnode *midvn = shiftop->getIn(0);
4401  if (!midvn->isWritten()) return 0;
4402  subop = midvn->getDef();
4403  if (subop->code() != CPUI_SUBPIECE) return 0;
4404  basevn = subop->getIn(0);
4405  if (basevn->isFree()) return 0;
4406  if (basevn->getSize() != op->getOut()->getSize()) return 0; // Truncating then extending to same size
4407  if (midvn->loneDescend() != shiftop) return 0;
4408  if (subvn->loneDescend() != op) return 0;
4409  val = calc_mask(midvn->getSize()); // Mask based on truncated size
4410  uintb sa = shiftop->getIn(1)->getOffset(); // The shift shrinks the mask even further
4411  val >>= sa;
4412  sa += subop->getIn(1)->getOffset() * 8; // The total shift = truncation + small shift
4413  Varnode *newvn = data.newUnique(basevn->getSize(),(Datatype *)0);
4414  data.opSetInput(op,newvn,0);
4415  data.opSetInput(shiftop,basevn,0); // Shift the full value, instead of the truncated value
4416  data.opSetInput(shiftop,data.newConstant(shiftop->getIn(1)->getSize(),sa),1); // by the combined amount
4417  data.opSetOutput(shiftop,newvn);
4418  constvn = data.newConstant(basevn->getSize(),val);
4419  data.opSetOpcode(op,CPUI_INT_AND); // Turn the ZEXT into an AND
4420  data.opInsertInput(op,constvn,1); // With the appropriate mask
4421  return 1;
4422  }
4423  return 0;
4424 }

4436 void RuleSubCancel::getOpList(vector<uint4> &oplist) const

4439  oplist.push_back(CPUI_SUBPIECE);
4440 }
4441 
4442 int4 RuleSubCancel::applyOp(PcodeOp *op,Funcdata &data)
4443 
4444 { // A SUBPIECE of an extension may cancel
4445  Varnode *base,*thruvn;
4446  int4 offset,outsize,insize,farinsize;
4447  PcodeOp *extop;
4448  OpCode opc;
4449 
4450  base = op->getIn(0);
4451  if (!base->isWritten()) return 0;
4452  extop = base->getDef();
4453  opc = extop->code();
4454  if ((opc != CPUI_INT_ZEXT)&&(opc != CPUI_INT_SEXT))
4455  return 0;
4456  offset = op->getIn(1)->getOffset();
4457  outsize = op->getOut()->getSize();
4458  insize = base->getSize();
4459  farinsize = extop->getIn(0)->getSize();
4460 
4461  if (offset == 0) { // If SUBPIECE is of least sig part
4462  thruvn = extop->getIn(0); // Something still comes through
4463  if (thruvn->isFree()) {
4464  if (thruvn->isConstant() && (insize > sizeof(uintb)) && (outsize == farinsize)) {
4465  // If we have a constant that is too big to represent, and the elimination is total
4466  opc = CPUI_COPY; // go ahead and do elimination
4467  thruvn = data.newConstant(thruvn->getSize(),thruvn->getOffset()); // with new constant varnode
4468  }
4469  else
4470  return 0; // If original is constant or undefined don't proceed
4471  }
4472  else if (outsize == farinsize)
4473  opc = CPUI_COPY; // Total elimination of extension
4474  else if (outsize < farinsize)
4475  opc = CPUI_SUBPIECE;
4476  }
4477  else {
4478  if ((opc==CPUI_INT_ZEXT)&&(farinsize<=offset)) { // output contains nothing of original input
4479  opc = CPUI_COPY; // Nothing but zero coming through
4480  thruvn = data.newConstant(outsize,0);
4481  }
4482  else // Missing one case here
4483  return 0;
4484  }
4485 
4486  data.opSetOpcode(op,opc); // SUBPIECE <- EXT replaced with one op
4487  data.opSetInput(op,thruvn,0);
4488 
4489  if (opc == CPUI_SUBPIECE)
4490  data.opSetInput(op,data.newConstant(op->getIn(1)->getSize(),offset),1);
4491  else
4492  data.opRemoveInput(op,1); // ZEXT, SEXT, or COPY has only 1 input
4493  return 1;
4494 }

4510  if (!shiftop->getIn(1)->isConstant()) return 0;

4512  return 0;

4530 
4531 int4 RuleHumptyDumpty::applyOp(PcodeOp *op,Funcdata &data)
4532 
4533 {
4534  uintb pos1,pos2;
4535  int4 size1,size2;
4536  Varnode *vn1,*vn2,*root;
4537  PcodeOp *sub1,*sub2;
4538  // op is something "put together"
4539  vn1 = op->getIn(0);
4540  if (!vn1->isWritten()) return 0;
4541  sub1 = vn1->getDef();
4542  if (sub1->code() != CPUI_SUBPIECE) return 0; // from piece1
4543  vn2 = op->getIn(1);
4544  if (!vn2->isWritten()) return 0;
4545  sub2 = vn2->getDef();
4546  if (sub2->code() != CPUI_SUBPIECE) return 0; // from piece2
4547 
4548  root = sub1->getIn(0);
4549  if (root != sub2->getIn(0)) return 0; // pieces of the same whole
4550 
4551  pos1 = sub1->getIn(1)->getOffset();
4552  pos2 = sub2->getIn(1)->getOffset();
4553  size1 = vn1->getSize();
4554  size2 = vn2->getSize();
4555 
4556  if (pos1 != pos2 + size2) return 0; // Pieces do not match up
4557 
4558  if ((pos2==0)&&(size1+size2==root->getSize())) { // Pieced together whole thing
4559  data.opRemoveInput(op,1);
4560  data.opSetInput(op,root,0);
4561  data.opSetOpcode(op,CPUI_COPY);
4562  }
4563  else { // Pieced together a larger part of the whole
4564  data.opSetInput(op,root,0);
4565  data.opSetInput(op,data.newConstant(sub2->getIn(1)->getSize(),pos2),1);
4566  data.opSetOpcode(op,CPUI_SUBPIECE);
4567  }
4568  return 1;
4569 }

4584 int4 RuleDumptyHump::applyOp(PcodeOp *op,Funcdata &data)
4585 
4586 { // If we append something to a varnode
4587  // And then take a subpiece that cuts off what
4588  // we just appended, treat whole thing as COPY
4589  Varnode *base,*vn,*vn1,*vn2;
4590  PcodeOp *pieceop;
4591  int4 offset,outsize;
4592 
4593  base = op->getIn(0);
4594  if (!base->isWritten()) return 0;
4595  pieceop = base->getDef();
4596  if (pieceop->code() != CPUI_PIECE) return 0;
4597  offset = op->getIn(1)->getOffset();
4598  outsize = op->getOut()->getSize();
4599 
4600  vn1 = pieceop->getIn(0);
4601  vn2 = pieceop->getIn(1);
4602 
4603  if (offset < vn2->getSize()) { // Sub draws from vn2
4604  if (offset+outsize > vn2->getSize()) return 0; // Also from vn1
4605  vn = vn2;
4606  }
4607  else { // Sub draws from vn1
4608  vn = vn1;
4609  offset -= vn2->getSize(); // offset relative to vn1
4610  }
4611 
4612  if (vn->isFree() && (!vn->isConstant())) return 0;
4613  if ((offset==0)&&(outsize==vn->getSize())) {
4614  // Eliminate SUB and CONCAT altogether
4615  data.opSetOpcode(op,CPUI_COPY);
4616  data.opRemoveInput(op,1);
4617  data.opSetInput(op,vn,0); // Skip over CONCAT
4618  }
4619  else {
4620  // Eliminate CONCAT and adjust SUB
4621  data.opSetInput(op,vn,0); // Skip over CONCAT
4622  data.opSetInput(op,data.newConstant(4,offset),1);
4623  }
4624  return 1;
4625 }

4632 void RuleHumptyOr::getOpList(vector<uint4> &oplist) const
4633 
4634 {
4635  oplist.push_back(CPUI_INT_OR);
4636 }
4637 
4638 int4 RuleHumptyOr::applyOp(PcodeOp *op,Funcdata &data)
4639 
4640 {
4641  Varnode *vn1,*vn2;
4642  Varnode *a, *b, *c, *d;
4643  PcodeOp *and1,*and2;
4644 
4645  vn1 = op->getIn(0);
4646  if (!vn1->isWritten()) return 0;
4647  vn2 = op->getIn(1);
4648  if (!vn2->isWritten()) return 0;
4649  and1 = vn1->getDef();
4650  if (and1->code() != CPUI_INT_AND) return 0;
4651  and2 = vn2->getDef();
4652  if (and2->code() != CPUI_INT_AND) return 0;
4653  a = and1->getIn(0);
4654  b = and1->getIn(1);
4655  c = and2->getIn(0);
4656  d = and2->getIn(1);
4657  if (a == c) {
4658  c = d; // non-matching are b and d
4659  }
4660  else if (a == d) { // non-matching are b and c
4661  }
4662  else if (b == c) { // non-matching are a and d
4663  b = a;
4664  a = c;
4665  c = d;
4666  }
4667  else if (b == d) { // non-matching are a and c
4668  b = a;
4669  a = d;
4670  }
4671  else
4672  return 0;
4673  // Reaching here a, matches across both ANDs, b and c are the respective other params
4674  // We know a is not free, because there are at least two references to it
4675  if (b->isConstant() && c->isConstant()) {
4676  uintb totalbits = b->getOffset() | c->getOffset();
4677  if (totalbits == calc_mask(a->getSize())) {
4678  // Between the two sides, we get all bits of a. Convert to COPY
4679  data.opSetOpcode(op,CPUI_COPY);
4680  data.opRemoveInput(op,1);
4681  data.opSetInput(op,a,0);
4682  }
4683  else {
4684  // We get some bits, but not all. Convert to an AND
4685  data.opSetOpcode(op,CPUI_INT_AND);
4686  data.opSetInput(op,a,0);
4687  Varnode *newconst = data.newConstant(a->getSize(),totalbits);
4688  data.opSetInput(op,newconst,1);
4689  }
4690  }
4691  else {
4692  if (!b->isHeritageKnown()) return 0;
4693  if (!c->isHeritageKnown()) return 0;
4694  uintb aMask = a->getNZMask();
4695  if ((b->getNZMask() & aMask)==0) return 0; // RuleAndDistribute would reverse us
4696  if ((c->getNZMask() & aMask)==0) return 0; // RuleAndDistribute would reverse us
4697  PcodeOp *newOrOp = data.newOp(2,op->getAddr());
4698  data.opSetOpcode(newOrOp,CPUI_INT_OR);
4699  Varnode *orVn = data.newUniqueOut(a->getSize(),newOrOp);
4700  data.opSetInput(newOrOp,b,0);
4701  data.opSetInput(newOrOp,c,1);
4702  data.opInsertBefore(newOrOp,op);
4703  data.opSetInput(op,a,0);
4704  data.opSetInput(op,orVn,1);
4705  data.opSetOpcode(op,CPUI_INT_AND);
4706  }
4707  return 1;
4708 }

4715 void RuleEmbed::getOpList(vector<uint4> &oplist) const
4716 
4717 {
4718  oplist.push_back(CPUI_PIECE);
4719 }
4720 
4721 int4 RuleEmbed::applyOp(PcodeOp *op,Funcdata &data)
4722 
4723 {
4724  // Beware of humpty dumpty
4725  Varnode *a,*subout,*x;
4726  PcodeOp *subop;
4727  int4 i;
4728 
4729  for(i=0;i<2;++i) {
4730  subout = op->getIn(i);
4731  if (!subout->isWritten()) continue;
4732  subop = subout->getDef();
4733  if (subop->code() != CPUI_SUBPIECE) continue;
4734  int4 c = subop->getIn(1)->getOffset();
4735  a = subop->getIn(0);
4736  if (a->isFree()) continue;
4737  if (a->getSize() != op->getOut()->getSize()) continue;
4738  x = op->getIn(1-i);
4739  if (x->isFree()) continue;
4740  if (i==0) {
4741  if (subout->getSize()+c != a->getSize()) continue; // Not hi SUB
4742  }
4743  else {
4744  if (c != 0) continue; // Not lo SUB
4745  }
4746 
4747  if (x->isWritten()) { // Check for humptydumpty
4748  PcodeOp *othersub = x->getDef();
4749  if (othersub->code() == CPUI_SUBPIECE) {
4750  if (othersub->getIn(0)==a) {
4751  int4 d = othersub->getIn(1)->getOffset();
4752  if ((i==0)&&(d==0)) continue;
4753  if ((i==1)&&(d==subout->getSize())) continue;
4754  }
4755  }
4756  }
4757 
4758  // Be careful of precision limit when constructing mask
4759  if (subout->getSize() + c > sizeof(uintb)) continue;
4760  uintb mask = calc_mask(subout->getSize());
4761  mask <<= 8*c;
4762 
4763  // Construct mask
4764  PcodeOp *andop = data.newOp(2,op->getAddr());
4765  data.opSetOpcode(andop,CPUI_INT_AND);
4766  data.newUniqueOut(a->getSize(),andop);
4767  data.opSetInput(andop,a,0);
4768  data.opSetInput(andop,data.newConstant(a->getSize(),mask),1);
4769  data.opInsertBefore(andop,op);
4770  // Extend x
4771  PcodeOp *extop = data.newOp(1,op->getAddr());
4772  data.opSetOpcode(extop,CPUI_INT_ZEXT);
4773  data.newUniqueOut(a->getSize(),extop);
4774  data.opSetInput(extop,x,0);
4775  data.opInsertBefore(extop,op);
4776  x = extop->getOut();
4777  if (i==1) { // Shift x into position
4778  PcodeOp *shiftop = data.newOp(2,op->getAddr());
4779  data.opSetOpcode(shiftop,CPUI_INT_LEFT);
4780  data.newUniqueOut(a->getSize(),shiftop);
4781  data.opSetInput(shiftop,x,0);
4782  data.opSetInput(shiftop,data.newConstant(4,8*subout->getSize()),1);
4783  data.opInsertBefore(shiftop,op);
4784  x = shiftop->getOut();
4785  }
4786  data.opSetOpcode(op,CPUI_INT_OR);
4787  data.opSetInput(op,andop->getOut(),0);
4788  data.opSetInput(op,x,1);
4789  return 1;
4790  }
4791  return 0;
4792 }

4796 void RuleSwitchSingle::getOpList(vector<uint4> &oplist) const
4797 
4798 {
4799  oplist.push_back(CPUI_BRANCHIND);
4800 }
4801 
4802 int4 RuleSwitchSingle::applyOp(PcodeOp *op,Funcdata &data)
4803 
4804 {
4805  BlockBasic *bb = op->getParent();
4806  if (bb->sizeOut() != 1) return 0;
4807 
4808  JumpTable *jt = data.findJumpTable(op);
4809  if (jt == (JumpTable *)0) return 0;
4810  if (jt->numEntries() == 0) return 0;
4811  if (!jt->isLabelled()) return 0; // Labels must be recovered (as this discovers multistage issues)
4812  Address addr = jt->getAddressByIndex(0);
4813  bool needwarning = false;
4814  bool allcasesmatch = false;
4815  if (jt->numEntries() != 1) {
4816  needwarning = true;
4817  allcasesmatch = true;
4818  for(int4 i=1;i<jt->numEntries();++i) {
4819  if (jt->getAddressByIndex(i) != addr) {
4820  allcasesmatch = false;
4821  break;
4822  }
4823  }
4824  }
4825 
4826  if (!op->getIn(0)->isConstant())
4827  needwarning = true;
4828  // If the switch variable is a constant this is final
4829  // confirmation that the switch has only one destination
4830  // otherwise this may indicate some other problem
4831 
4832  if (needwarning) {
4833  ostringstream s;
4834  s << "Switch with 1 destination removed at ";
4835  op->getAddr().printRaw(s);
4836  if (allcasesmatch) {
4837  s << " : " << dec << jt->numEntries() << " cases all go to same destination";
4838  }
4839  data.warningHeader(s.str());
4840  }
4841 
4842  // Convert the BRANCHIND to just a branch
4843  data.opSetOpcode(op,CPUI_BRANCH);
4844  // Stick in the coderef of the single jumptable entry
4845  data.opSetInput(op,data.newCodeRef(addr),0);
4846  data.removeJumpTable(jt);
4847  data.getStructure().clear(); // Get rid of any block switch structures
4848  return 1;
4849 }

4901 int4 RuleBoolNegate::applyOp(PcodeOp *op,Funcdata &data)
4902 
4903 {
4904  Varnode *vn;
4905  PcodeOp *flip_op;
4906  OpCode opc;
4907  bool flipyes;
4908 
4909  vn = op->getIn(0);
4910  if (!vn->isWritten()) return 0;
4911  flip_op = vn->getDef();
4912 
4913  list<PcodeOp *>::const_iterator iter;
4914 
4915  // ALL descendants must be negates
4916  for(iter=vn->beginDescend();iter!=vn->endDescend();++iter)
4917  if ((*iter)->code() != CPUI_BOOL_NEGATE) return 0;
4918 
4919  opc = get_booleanflip(flip_op->code(),flipyes);
4920  if (opc == CPUI_MAX) return 0;
4921  data.opSetOpcode(flip_op,opc); // Set the negated opcode
4922  if (flipyes) // Do we need to reverse the two operands
4923  data.opSwapInput(flip_op,0,1);
4924  for(iter=vn->beginDescend();iter!=vn->endDescend();++iter)
4925  data.opSetOpcode(*iter,CPUI_COPY); // Remove all the negates
4926  return 1;
4927 }

4943 int4 RuleLess2Zero::applyOp(PcodeOp *op,Funcdata &data)
4944 
4945 {
4946  Varnode *lvn,*rvn;
4947  lvn = op->getIn(0);
4948  rvn = op->getIn(1);
4949 
4950  if (lvn->isConstant()) {
4951  if (lvn->getOffset() == 0) {
4952  data.opSetOpcode(op,CPUI_INT_NOTEQUAL); // All values except 0 are true -> NOT_EQUAL
4953  return 1;
4954  }
4955  else if (lvn->getOffset() == calc_mask(lvn->getSize())) {
4956  data.opSetOpcode(op,CPUI_COPY); // Always false
4957  data.opRemoveInput(op,1);
4958  data.opSetInput(op,data.newConstant(1,0),0);
4959  return 1;
4960  }
4961  }
4962  else if (rvn->isConstant()) {
4963  if (rvn->getOffset() == 0) {
4964  data.opSetOpcode(op,CPUI_COPY); // Always false
4965  data.opRemoveInput(op,1);
4966  data.opSetInput(op,data.newConstant(1,0),0);
4967  return 1;
4968  }
4969  else if (rvn->getOffset() == calc_mask(rvn->getSize())) { // All values except -1 are true -> NOT_EQUAL
4970  data.opSetOpcode(op,CPUI_INT_NOTEQUAL);
4971  return 1;
4972  }
4973  }
4974  return 0;
4975 }

4991 int4 RuleLessEqual2Zero::applyOp(PcodeOp *op,Funcdata &data)
4992

5003  return 1;
5004  }

5013  return 1;
5014  }
5015  else if (rvn->getOffset() == calc_mask(rvn->getSize())) {
5016  data.opSetOpcode(op,CPUI_COPY); // All values => true
5017  data.opRemoveInput(op,1);

5019  return 1;

5031 Varnode *RuleSLess2Zero::getHiBit(PcodeOp *op)
5032 
5033 {
5034  OpCode opc = op->code();
5035  if ((opc != CPUI_INT_ADD)&&(opc != CPUI_INT_OR)&&(opc != CPUI_INT_XOR))
5036  return (Varnode *)0;
5037 
5038  Varnode *vn1 = op->getIn(0);
5039  Varnode *vn2 = op->getIn(1);
5040  uintb mask = calc_mask(vn1->getSize());
5041  mask = (mask ^ (mask>>1)); // Only high-bit is set
5042  uintb nzmask1 = vn1->getNZMask();
5043  if ((nzmask1!=mask)&&((nzmask1 & mask)!=0)) // If high-bit is set AND some other bit
5044  return (Varnode *)0;
5045  uintb nzmask2 = vn2->getNZMask();
5046  if ((nzmask2!=mask)&&((nzmask2 & mask)!=0))
5047  return (Varnode *)0;
5048 
5049  if (nzmask1 == mask)
5050  return vn1;
5051  if (nzmask2 == mask)
5052  return vn2;
5053  return (Varnode *)0;
5054 }

5077 int4 RuleSLess2Zero::applyOp(PcodeOp *op,Funcdata &data)
5078 
5079 {
5080  Varnode *lvn,*rvn,*coeff,*avn;
5081  PcodeOp *multop;
5082  lvn = op->getIn(0);
5083  rvn = op->getIn(1);
5084 
5085  if (lvn->isConstant()) {
5086  if (!rvn->isWritten()) return 0;
5087  if (lvn->getOffset() == 0) {
5088  multop = rvn->getDef();
5089  if (multop->code() == CPUI_INT_MULT) {
5090  coeff = multop->getIn(1);
5091  if (!coeff->isConstant()) return 0;
5092  if (coeff->getOffset() != calc_mask(coeff->getSize())) return 0;
5093  avn = multop->getIn(0);
5094  if (avn->isFree()) return 0;
5095  data.opSetInput(op,avn,0);
5096  data.opSetInput(op,lvn,1);
5097  return 1;
5098  }
5099  else if (op->code() == CPUI_INT_SLESSEQUAL) {
5100  Varnode *hibit = getHiBit(multop);
5101  if (hibit != (Varnode *)0) { // Test for 0 s<= (hi ^ lo)
5102  if (hibit->isConstant())
5103  data.opSetInput(op,data.newConstant(hibit->getSize(),hibit->getOffset()),1);
5104  else
5105  data.opSetInput(op,hibit,1);
5106  data.opSetOpcode(op,CPUI_INT_EQUAL);
5107  return 1;
5108  }
5109  }
5110  }
5111  else if (lvn->getOffset() == calc_mask(lvn->getSize())) {
5112  if (op->code() == CPUI_INT_SLESS) {
5113  Varnode *hibit = getHiBit(rvn->getDef());
5114  if (hibit != (Varnode *)0) { // Test for -1 s< (hi ^ lo)
5115  if (hibit->isConstant())
5116  data.opSetInput(op,data.newConstant(hibit->getSize(),hibit->getOffset()),1);
5117  else
5118  data.opSetInput(op,hibit,1);
5119  data.opSetOpcode(op,CPUI_INT_EQUAL);
5120  data.opSetInput(op,data.newConstant(hibit->getSize(),0),0);
5121  return 1;
5122  }
5123  }
5124  }
5125  }
5126  else if (rvn->isConstant()) {
5127  if (!lvn->isWritten()) return 0;
5128  if (rvn->getOffset() == 0) {
5129  multop = lvn->getDef();
5130  if (multop->code() == CPUI_INT_MULT) {
5131  coeff = multop->getIn(1);
5132  if (!coeff->isConstant()) return 0;
5133  if (coeff->getOffset() != calc_mask(coeff->getSize())) return 0;
5134  avn = multop->getIn(0);
5135  if (avn->isFree()) return 0;
5136  data.opSetInput(op,avn,1);
5137  data.opSetInput(op,rvn,0);
5138  return 1;
5139  }
5140  else if (op->code() == CPUI_INT_SLESS) {
5141  Varnode *hibit = getHiBit(multop);
5142  if (hibit != (Varnode *)0) { // Test for (hi ^ lo) s< 0
5143  if (hibit->isConstant())
5144  data.opSetInput(op,data.newConstant(hibit->getSize(),hibit->getOffset()),0);
5145  else
5146  data.opSetInput(op,hibit,0);
5147  data.opSetOpcode(op,CPUI_INT_NOTEQUAL);
5148  return 1;
5149  }
5150  }
5151  }
5152  else if (rvn->getOffset() == calc_mask(rvn->getSize())) {
5153  if (op->code() == CPUI_INT_SLESSEQUAL) {
5154  Varnode *hibit = getHiBit(lvn->getDef());
5155  if (hibit != (Varnode *)0) { // Test for (hi ^ lo) s<= -1
5156  if (hibit->isConstant())
5157  data.opSetInput(op,data.newConstant(hibit->getSize(),hibit->getOffset()),0);
5158  else
5159  data.opSetInput(op,hibit,0);
5160  data.opSetOpcode(op,CPUI_INT_NOTEQUAL);
5161  data.opSetInput(op,data.newConstant(hibit->getSize(),0),1);
5162  return 1;
5163  }
5164  }
5165  }
5166  }
5167  return 0;
5168 }

5180 
5181 int4 RuleEqual2Zero::applyOp(PcodeOp *op,Funcdata &data)
5182 
5183 {
5184  Varnode *vn,*vn2,*addvn;
5185  Varnode *posvn,*negvn,*unnegvn;
5186  PcodeOp *addop;
5187 
5188  vn = op->getIn(0);
5189  if ((vn->isConstant())&&(vn->getOffset() == 0))
5190  addvn = op->getIn(1);
5191  else {
5192  addvn = vn;
5193  vn = op->getIn(1);
5194  if ((!vn->isConstant())||(vn->getOffset() != 0))
5195  return 0;
5196  }
5197  for(list<PcodeOp *>::const_iterator iter=addvn->beginDescend();iter!=addvn->endDescend();++iter) {
5198  // make sure the sum is only used in comparisons
5199  PcodeOp *boolop = *iter;
5200  if (!boolop->isBoolOutput()) return 0;
5201  }
5202  // if (addvn->lone_descendant() != op) return 0;
5203  addop = addvn->getDef();
5204  if (addop==(PcodeOp *)0) return 0;
5205  if (addop->code() != CPUI_INT_ADD) return 0;
5206  vn = addop->getIn(0);
5207  vn2 = addop->getIn(1);
5208  if (vn2->isConstant()) {
5209  Address val(vn2->getSpace(),uintb_negate(vn2->getOffset()-1,vn2->getSize()));
5210  unnegvn = data.newVarnode(vn2->getSize(),val);
5211  posvn = vn;
5212  }
5213  else {
5214  if ((vn->isWritten())&&(vn->getDef()->code()==CPUI_INT_MULT)) {
5215  negvn = vn;
5216  posvn = vn2;
5217  }
5218  else if ((vn2->isWritten())&&(vn2->getDef()->code()==CPUI_INT_MULT)) {
5219  negvn = vn2;
5220  posvn = vn;
5221  }
5222  else
5223  return 0;
5224  uintb multiplier;
5225  if (!negvn->getDef()->getIn(1)->isConstant()) return 0;
5226  unnegvn = negvn->getDef()->getIn(0);
5227  multiplier = negvn->getDef()->getIn(1)->getOffset();
5228  if (multiplier != calc_mask(unnegvn->getSize())) return 0;
5229  }
5230  if (!posvn->isHeritageKnown()) return 0;
5231  if (!unnegvn->isHeritageKnown()) return 0;
5232 
5233  data.opSetInput(op,posvn,0);
5234  data.opSetInput(op,unnegvn,1);
5235  return 1;
5236 }

5244 void RuleEqual2Constant::getOpList(vector<uint4> &oplist) const
5245 
5246 {
5247  uint4 list[] = { CPUI_INT_EQUAL, CPUI_INT_NOTEQUAL };
5248  oplist.insert(oplist.end(),list,list+2);

5250 
5251 int4 RuleEqual2Constant::applyOp(PcodeOp *op,Funcdata &data)
5252 
5253 {
5254  Varnode *cvn = op->getIn(1);
5255  if (!cvn->isConstant()) return 0;
5256 
5257  Varnode *lhs = op->getIn(0);
5258  if (!lhs->isWritten()) return 0;
5259  PcodeOp *leftop = lhs->getDef();
5260  Varnode *a;
5261  uintb newconst;
5262  if (leftop->code() == CPUI_INT_ADD) {
5263  Varnode *otherconst = leftop->getIn(1);
5264  if (!otherconst->isConstant()) return 0;
5265  newconst = cvn->getOffset() - otherconst->getOffset();
5266  newconst &= calc_mask(cvn->getSize());
5267  }
5268  else if (leftop->code() == CPUI_INT_MULT) {
5269  Varnode *otherconst = leftop->getIn(1);
5270  if (!otherconst->isConstant()) return 0;
5271  // The only multiply we transform, is multiply by -1
5272  if (otherconst->getOffset() != calc_mask(otherconst->getSize())) return 0;
5273  newconst = cvn->getOffset();
5274  newconst = (-newconst) & calc_mask(otherconst->getSize());
5275  }
5276  else
5277  return 0;
5278 
5279  a = leftop->getIn(0);
5280  if (a->isFree()) return 0;
5281 
5282  // Make sure the transformed form of a is only used
5283  // in comparisons of similar form
5284  list<PcodeOp *>::const_iterator iter;
5285  for(iter=lhs->beginDescend();iter!=lhs->endDescend();++iter) {
5286  PcodeOp *dop = *iter;
5287  if (dop == op) continue;
5288  if ((dop->code()!=CPUI_INT_EQUAL)&&(dop->code()!=CPUI_INT_NOTEQUAL))
5289  return 0;
5290  if (!dop->getIn(1)->isConstant()) return 0;
5291  }
5292 
5293  data.opSetInput(op,a,0);
5294  data.opSetInput(op,data.newConstant(a->getSize(),newconst),1);
5295  return 1;
5296 }
5297 
5305 bool RulePtrArith::checkTerm(Varnode *vn,AddTreeState *state)
5306 
5307 {
5308  uintb val,rem;
5309  Varnode *vnconst,*vnterm;
5310  PcodeOp *def;
5311 
5312  if (vn == state->ptr) return false;
5313  if (vn->isConstant()) {
5314  val = vn->getOffset();
5315  rem = (state->size==0) ? val : val % state->size;
5316  if (rem!=0) { // constant is not multiple of size
5317  state->nonmultsum += val;
5318  return true;
5319  }
5320  state->multsum += val; // Add multiples of size into multsum
5321  return false;
5322  }
5323  if (vn->isWritten()) {
5324  def = vn->getDef();
5325  if (def->code() == CPUI_INT_ADD) // Recurse
5326  return spanAddTree(def,state);
5327  if (def->code() == CPUI_COPY) { // Not finished reducing yet
5328  state->valid = false;
5329  return false;
5330  }
5331  if (def->code() == CPUI_INT_MULT) { // Check for constant coeff indicating size
5332  vnconst = def->getIn(1);
5333  vnterm = def->getIn(0);
5334  if (vnconst->isConstant()) {
5335  val = vnconst->getOffset();
5336  rem = (state->size==0) ? val : val % state->size;
5337  if (rem!=0) {
5338  if ((val > state->size)&&(state->size!=0)) {
5339  state->valid = false; // Size is too big: pointer type must be wrong
5340  return false;
5341  }
5342  return true;
5343  }
5344  if (rem==0) {
5345  state->multiple.push_back(vnterm);
5346  state->coeff.push_back(val);
5347  return false;
5348  }
5349  }
5350  }
5351  }
5352  return true;
5353 }
5354 
5360 bool RulePtrArith::spanAddTree(PcodeOp *op,AddTreeState *state)
5361 
5362 {
5363  bool one_is_non,two_is_non;
5364 
5365  one_is_non = checkTerm(op->getIn(0),state);
5366  if (!state->valid) return false;
5367  two_is_non = checkTerm(op->getIn(1),state);
5368  if (!state->valid) return false;
5369 
5370  if (one_is_non&&two_is_non) return true;
5371  if (one_is_non)
5372  state->nonmult.push_back(op->getIn(0));
5373  if (two_is_non)
5374  state->nonmult.push_back(op->getIn(1));
5375  return false;
5376 }
5377 
5393 int4 RulePtrArith::transformPtr(PcodeOp *bottom_op,PcodeOp *ptr_op,int4 slot,Funcdata &data)
5394 
5395 {
5396  AddTreeState state;
5397  const TypePointer *ct;
5398  bool yes_subtype,offset_corrected;
5399  int4 i,ptrsize;
5400  uintb correct,coeff,offset,nonmultbytes,extra;
5401  Varnode *ptrbump; // Will contain final result of PTR addition
5402  Varnode *fullother; // Will contain anything else not part of PTR add
5403  Varnode *newvn;
5404  PcodeOp *newop = (PcodeOp *)0;
5405 
5406  state.ptr = ptr_op->getIn(slot);
5407  ct = (const TypePointer *) state.ptr->getType();
5408  ptrsize = state.ptr->getSize();
5409  state.size = AddrSpace::byteToAddressInt(ct->getPtrTo()->getSize(),ct->getWordSize());
5410  state.multsum = 0; // Sums start out as zero
5411  state.nonmultsum = 0;
5412  state.valid = true; // Valid until proven otherwise
5413 
5414  spanAddTree(bottom_op,&state); // Find multiples and non-multiples of ct->getSize()
5415  if (!state.valid) return 0; // Were there any show stoppers
5416  state.nonmultsum &= calc_mask(ptrsize); // Make sure we are modulo ptr's space
5417  state.multsum &= calc_mask(ptrsize);
5418  offset = (state.size==0) ? state.nonmultsum : state.nonmultsum % state.size;
5419  correct = state.nonmultsum - offset;
5420  state.nonmultsum = offset;
5421  state.multsum = (state.multsum + correct)&calc_mask(ptrsize); // Some extra multiples of size
5422 
5423  // Figure out if there is any subtype
5424  if (state.nonmult.empty()) {
5425  if ((state.multsum==0)&&state.multiple.empty()) // Is there anything at all
5426  return 0;
5427  yes_subtype = false; // If there are no offsets INTO the pointer
5428  offset = 0; // Do not check if there are sub structures
5429  }
5430  else if (ct->getPtrTo()->getMetatype()==TYPE_SPACEBASE) {
5431  nonmultbytes = AddrSpace::addressToByte(state.nonmultsum,ct->getWordSize()); // Convert to bytes
5432  // Get offset into mapped variable
5433  if (ct->getPtrTo()->getSubType(nonmultbytes,&extra)==(Datatype *)0)
5434  return 0; // Cannot find mapped variable but nonmult is non-empty
5435  extra = AddrSpace::byteToAddress(extra,ct->getWordSize()); // Convert back to address units
5436  offset = (state.nonmultsum - extra)&calc_mask(ptrsize);
5437  yes_subtype = true;
5438  }
5439  else if (ct->getPtrTo()->getMetatype()==TYPE_STRUCT) {
5440  nonmultbytes = AddrSpace::addressToByte(state.nonmultsum,ct->getWordSize()); // Convert to bytes
5441  // Get offset into field in structure
5442  if (ct->getPtrTo()->getSubType(nonmultbytes,&extra)==(Datatype *)0) {
5443  if (nonmultbytes >= ct->getPtrTo()->getSize()) return 0; // Out of structure's bounds
5444  extra = 0; // No field, but pretend there is something there
5445  }
5446  extra = AddrSpace::byteToAddress(extra,ct->getWordSize()); // Convert back to address units
5447  offset = (state.nonmultsum - extra)&calc_mask(ptrsize);
5448  yes_subtype = true;
5449  }
5450  else if (ct->getPtrTo()->getMetatype()==TYPE_ARRAY) {
5451  yes_subtype = true;
5452  offset = 0;
5453  }
5454  else // No struct or array, but nonmult is non-empty
5455  return 0; // There is substructure we don't know about
5456 
5457  // Be sure to preserve sign in division below
5458  // Calc size-relative constant PTR addition
5459  intb smultsum = (intb)state.multsum;
5460  sign_extend(smultsum,state.ptr->getSize()*8-1);
5461  coeff = (state.size==0) ? (uintb)0 : (smultsum / state.size)&calc_mask(ptrsize);
5462  if (coeff == 0)
5463  ptrbump = (Varnode *)0;
5464  else
5465  ptrbump = data.newConstant(ptrsize,coeff);
5466  for(i=0;i<state.multiple.size();++i) {
5467  coeff = (state.size==0) ? (uintb)0 : state.coeff[i] / state.size;
5468  newvn = state.multiple[i];
5469  if (coeff != 1) {
5470  newop = data.newOpBefore(bottom_op,CPUI_INT_MULT,newvn,data.newConstant(ptrsize,coeff));
5471  newvn = newop->getOut();
5472  }
5473  if (ptrbump == (Varnode *)0)
5474  ptrbump = newvn;
5475  else {
5476  newop = data.newOpBefore(bottom_op,CPUI_INT_ADD, newvn, ptrbump);
5477  ptrbump = newop->getOut();
5478  }
5479  }
5480  // Create PTRADD portion of operation
5481  if (ptrbump != (Varnode *)0) {
5482  newop = data.newOpBefore(bottom_op,CPUI_PTRADD,
5483  state.ptr,ptrbump,data.newConstant(ptrsize,state.size));
5484  ptrbump = newop->getOut();
5485  }
5486  else
5487  ptrbump = state.ptr;
5488  // Add up any remaining pieces
5489  correct = (correct+offset)&calc_mask(ptrsize); // Total correction that needs to be made
5490  offset_corrected= (correct==0);
5491  fullother = (Varnode *)0;
5492  for(i=0;i<state.nonmult.size();++i) {
5493  newvn = state.nonmult[i];
5494  if ((!offset_corrected)&&(newvn->isConstant()))
5495  if (newvn->getOffset() == correct) {
5496  offset_corrected = true;
5497  continue;
5498  }
5499  if (fullother == (Varnode *)0)
5500  fullother = newvn;
5501  else {
5502  newop = data.newOpBefore(bottom_op,CPUI_INT_ADD,newvn,fullother);
5503  fullother = newop->getOut();
5504  }
5505  }
5506  if (!offset_corrected) {
5507  newvn = data.newConstant(ptrsize,uintb_negate(correct-1,ptrsize));
5508  if (fullother == (Varnode *)0)
5509  fullother = newvn;
5510  else {
5511  newop = data.newOpBefore(bottom_op,CPUI_INT_ADD,newvn,fullother);
5512  fullother = newop->getOut();
5513  }
5514  }
5515  // Do PTRSUB portion of operation
5516  if (yes_subtype) {
5517  newop = data.newOpBefore(bottom_op,CPUI_PTRSUB,ptrbump,data.newConstant(ptrsize,offset));
5518  ptrbump = newop->getOut();
5519  }
5520 
5521  if (fullother != (Varnode *)0)
5522  newop = data.newOpBefore(bottom_op,CPUI_INT_ADD,ptrbump,fullother);
5523 
5524  if (newop == (PcodeOp *)0) {
5525  // This shouldn't happen, but does because of negative offsets
5526  // Should be fixed when we convert everything to signed calc
5527  data.warning("ptrarith problems",ptr_op->getAddr());
5528  return 0;
5529  }
5530  data.opSetOutput(newop,bottom_op->getOut());
5531  data.opDestroy(bottom_op);
5532  return 1;
5533 }
5534 
5554 void RulePtrArith::getOpList(vector<uint4> &oplist) const
5555 
5556 {
5557  oplist.push_back(CPUI_INT_ADD);
5558 }
5559 
5560 int4 RulePtrArith::applyOp(PcodeOp *op,Funcdata &data)
5561 
5562 {
5563  int4 i;
5564  const Datatype *ct = (const Datatype *)0; // Unnecessary initialization
5565  const TypePointer *tp;
5566  Varnode *vn,*ptrbase;
5567  PcodeOp *lowerop;
5568 
5569  if (!data.isTypeRecoveryOn()) return 0;
5570 
5571  for(i=0;i<op->numInput();++i) { // Search for pointer type
5572  ct = op->getIn(i)->getType();
5573  if (ct->getMetatype() == TYPE_PTR) break;
5574  }
5575  if (i == op->numInput()) return 0;
5576 
5577  vn = op->getOut();
5578  ptrbase = op->getIn(i);
5579  list<PcodeOp *>::const_iterator iter=vn->beginDescend();
5580  OpCode opc;
5581  if (iter == vn->endDescend()) return 0; // Don't bother if no descendants
5582  lowerop = *iter++;
5583  opc = lowerop->code();
5584  if (vn->isSpacebase()) // For the RESULT to be a spacebase pointer
5585  if (iter!=vn->endDescend()) return 0; // It must have only 1 descendant
5586  if (opc == CPUI_INT_ADD) // Check for lone descendant which is an ADD
5587  if (iter==vn->endDescend()) return 0; // this is not bottom of add tree
5588  if (ptrbase->isSpacebase() && (ptrbase->isInput()||(ptrbase->isConstant())) &&
5589  (op->getIn(1-i)->isConstant())) {
5590  // Look for ANY descendant which
5591  // LOADs or STOREs off of vn
5592  if ((opc==CPUI_LOAD)||(opc==CPUI_STORE)) {
5593  if (lowerop->getIn(1) == vn)
5594  return 0;
5595  }
5596  while(iter!=vn->endDescend()) {
5597  opc = (*iter)->code();
5598  if ((opc==CPUI_LOAD)||(opc==CPUI_STORE)) {
5599  if ((*iter)->getIn(1) == vn)
5600  return 0;
5601  }
5602  ++iter;
5603  }
5604  }
5605 
5606  tp = (const TypePointer *) ct;
5607  ct = tp->getPtrTo(); // Type being pointed to
5608  int4 unitsize = AddrSpace::addressToByteInt(1,tp->getWordSize());
5609  if (ct->getSize() == unitsize) { // Degenerate case
5610  vector<Varnode *> newparams;
5611  newparams.push_back( ptrbase );
5612  newparams.push_back( op->getIn(1-i) );
5613  newparams.push_back( data.newConstant(tp->getSize(),1));
5614  data.opSetAllInput(op,newparams);
5615  data.opSetOpcode(op,CPUI_PTRADD);
5616  return 1;
5617  }
5618  if ((ct->getSize() < unitsize)&&(ct->getSize()>0))
5619  // If the size is really less than scale, there is
5620  // probably some sort of padding going on
5621  return 0;
5622 
5623  return transformPtr(op,op,i,data);
5624 }

5641 int4 RuleStructOffset0::applyOp(PcodeOp *op,Funcdata &data)
5642 
5643 {
5644  Datatype *ct,*sub_ct;
5645  PcodeOp *newop;
5646  int4 movesize; // Number of bytes being moved by load or store
5647  uintb offset;
5648 
5649  if (!data.isTypeRecoveryOn()) return 0;
5650  if (op->code()==CPUI_LOAD) {
5651  movesize = op->getOut()->getSize();
5652  }
5653  else if (op->code()==CPUI_STORE) {
5654  movesize = op->getIn(2)->getSize();
5655  }
5656  else
5657  return 0;
5658 
5659  ct = op->getIn(1)->getType();
5660  if (ct->getMetatype() != TYPE_PTR) return 0;
5661  ct = ((TypePointer *)ct)->getPtrTo();
5662  if (ct->getSize()<=movesize) {
5663  // if ((ct->getSize() < movesize)||(ct->getMetatype() != TYPE_STRUCT))
5664  return 0;
5665  // If we reach here (ct->getSize() == movesize) && (ct->getMetatype() == TYPE_STRUCT)
5666  // So the LOAD/STORE encompasses the entire structure. By not returning here, if the first
5667  // field of the struct is the whole struct, we display the field reference
5668  }
5669  if (ct->getMetatype() == TYPE_STRUCT) {
5670  sub_ct = ct->getSubType(0,&offset); // Get field at offset 0
5671  if (sub_ct==(Datatype *)0) return 0;
5672  if (sub_ct->getSize() < movesize) return 0; // Subtype is too small to handle LOAD/STORE
5673  }
5674  else if (ct->getMetatype() != TYPE_ARRAY)
5675  return 0;
5676 
5677  newop = data.newOpBefore(op,CPUI_PTRSUB,op->getIn(1),data.newConstant(op->getIn(1)->getSize(),0));
5678  data.opSetInput(op,newop->getOut(),1);
5679  return 1;
5680 }

5693 int4 RulePushPtr::applyOp(PcodeOp *op,Funcdata &data)
5694 
5695 {
5696  int4 i,j;
5697  PcodeOp *decop,*newop;
5698  Varnode *vn;
5699  Varnode *vni = (Varnode *)0;
5700  const Datatype *ct;
5701 
5702  if (!data.isTypeRecoveryOn()) return 0;
5703  for(i=0;i<op->numInput();++i) { // Search for pointer type
5704  vni = op->getIn(i);
5705  ct = vni->getType();
5706  if (ct->getMetatype() == TYPE_PTR) break;
5707  }
5708  if (i == op->numInput()) return 0;
5709  if ((i==0)&&(op->getIn(1)->getType()->getMetatype() == TYPE_PTR)) return 0; // Prevent infinite loops
5710 
5711  vn = op->getOut();
5712  if ((decop=vn->loneDescend()) == (PcodeOp *)0) return 0;
5713  if (decop->code() != CPUI_INT_ADD) return 0;
5714 
5715  j = decop->getSlot(vn);
5716  if (decop->getIn(1-j)->getType()->getMetatype() == TYPE_PTR) return 0; // Prevent infinite loops
5717 
5718  Varnode *vnadd1 = decop->getIn(1-j);
5719  Varnode *vnadd2 = op->getIn(1-i);
5720  Varnode *newout;
5721 
5722  // vni and vnadd2 are propagated, so they shouldn't be free
5723  if (vnadd2->isFree() && (!vnadd2->isConstant())) return 0;
5724  if (vni->isFree() && (!vni->isConstant())) return 0;
5725 
5726  newop = data.newOp(2,decop->getAddr());
5727  data.opSetOpcode(newop,CPUI_INT_ADD);
5728  newout = data.newUniqueOut(vnadd1->getSize(),newop);
5729 
5730  data.opSetInput(decop,vni,0);
5731  data.opSetInput(decop,newout,1);
5732 
5733  data.opSetInput(newop,vnadd1,0);
5734  data.opSetInput(newop,vnadd2,1);
5735 
5736  data.opInsertBefore(newop,decop);
5737 
5738  return 1;
5739 }

5753 int4 RulePtraddUndo::applyOp(PcodeOp *op,Funcdata &data)
5754 
5755 {
5756  int4 size;
5757  Varnode *basevn,*offvn,*multvn,*addvn;
5758  PcodeOp *multop;
5759  TypePointer *tp;
5760 
5761  if (!data.isTypeRecoveryOn()) return 0;

5763  size = multvn->getOffset(); // Size the PTRADD thinks we are pointing
5764  basevn = op->getIn(0);
5765  tp = (TypePointer *)basevn->getType();
5766  if (tp->getMetatype() == TYPE_PTR) // Make sure we are still a pointer

5769  if ((!indVn->isConstant()) || (indVn->getOffset() != 0)) // and that index isn't zero
5770  return 0;
5771  }
5772 
5773  // At this point we have a type mismatch to fix
5774  data.opRemoveInput(op,2);
5775  data.opSetOpcode(op,CPUI_INT_ADD);

5777  multop = data.newOp(2,op->getAddr());
5778  data.opSetOpcode(multop,CPUI_INT_MULT);
5779  offvn = op->getIn(1);
5780  addvn = data.newUniqueOut(offvn->getSize(),multop);
5781  data.opSetInput(multop,offvn,0);
5782  data.opSetInput(multop,multvn,1);
5783  data.opSetInput(op,addvn,1);
5784  data.opInsertBefore(multop,op);
5785 
5786  return 1;

5801 int4 RulePtrsubUndo::applyOp(PcodeOp *op,Funcdata &data)
5802 
5803 {
5804  if (!data.isTypeRecoveryOn()) return 0;
5805 
5806  Varnode *basevn = op->getIn(0);
5807  TypePointer *ct = (TypePointer *)basevn->getType();
5808  bool undo = false;
5809 
5810  if (ct->getMetatype()!=TYPE_PTR)
5811  undo = true;
5812  else {
5813  Datatype *basetype = ct->getPtrTo();
5814  if (basetype->getMetatype()==TYPE_SPACEBASE) {
5815  uintb newoff = AddrSpace::addressToByte(op->getIn(1)->getOffset(),ct->getWordSize());
5816  basetype->getSubType(newoff,&newoff);
5817  if (newoff != 0)
5818  undo = true;
5819  }
5820  else {
5821  int4 size = op->getIn(1)->getOffset();
5822  int4 typesize = basetype->getSize();
5823  if ((basetype->getMetatype()!=TYPE_ARRAY)&&(basetype->getMetatype()!=TYPE_STRUCT))
5824  undo = true; // Not a pointer to a structured type
5825  else if ((typesize <= AddrSpace::addressToByteInt(size,ct->getWordSize()))&&(typesize!=0))
5826  undo = true;
5827  }
5828  }
5829 
5830  if (!undo) return 0;
5831 
5832  data.opSetOpcode(op,CPUI_INT_ADD);
5833  return 1;
5834 }

5867 int4 RuleAddUnsigned::applyOp(PcodeOp *op,Funcdata &data)
5868 
5869 {
5870  Varnode *constvn = op->getIn(1);
5871 
5872  if (!constvn->isConstant()) return 0;
5873  Datatype *dt = constvn->getType();
5874  if (dt->getMetatype() != TYPE_UINT) return 0;
5875  if (dt->isCharPrint()) return 0; // Only change integer forms
5876  if (dt->isEnumType()) return 0;
5877  uintb val = constvn->getOffset();
5878  uintb mask = calc_mask(constvn->getSize());
5879  int4 sa = constvn->getSize() * 6; // 1/4 less than full bitsize
5880  uintb quarter = (mask>>sa) << sa;
5881  if ((val & quarter) != quarter) return 0; // The first quarter of bits must all be 1's
5882  if (constvn->getSymbolEntry() != (SymbolEntry *)0) {
5883  EquateSymbol *sym = dynamic_cast<EquateSymbol *>(constvn->getSymbolEntry()->getSymbol());
5884  if (sym != (EquateSymbol *)0) {
5885  if (sym->isNameLocked())
5886  return 0; // Dont transform a named equate
5887  }
5888  }
5889  data.opSetOpcode(op,CPUI_INT_SUB);
5890  Varnode *cvn = data.newConstant(constvn->getSize(), (-val) & mask);
5891  cvn->copySymbol(constvn);
5892  data.opSetInput(op,cvn,1);
5893  return 1;
5894 }

5904 int4 Rule2Comp2Sub::applyOp(PcodeOp *op,Funcdata &data)

5928 
5929 int4 RuleSubRight::applyOp(PcodeOp *op,Funcdata &data)
5930 
5931 {
5932  int4 c = op->getIn(1)->getOffset();
5933  if (c==0) return 0; // SUBPIECE is not least sig
5934  Varnode *a = op->getIn(0);
5935  Varnode *outvn = op->getOut();
5936  if (outvn->isAddrTied() && a->isAddrTied()) {
5937  if (outvn->overlap(*a) == c) // This SUBPIECE should get converted to a marker by ActionCopyMarker
5938  return 0; // So don't convert it
5939  }
5940  OpCode opc = CPUI_INT_RIGHT; // Default shift type
5941  int4 d = c*8; // Convert to bit shift
5942  // Search for lone right shift descendant
5943  PcodeOp *lone = outvn->loneDescend();
5944  if (lone!=(PcodeOp *)0) {
5945  OpCode opc2 = lone->code();
5946  if ((opc2==CPUI_INT_RIGHT)||(opc2==CPUI_INT_SRIGHT)) {
5947  if (lone->getIn(1)->isConstant()) { // Shift by constant
5948  if (outvn->getSize() + c == a->getSize()) {
5949  // If SUB is "hi" lump the SUB and shift together
5950  d += lone->getIn(1)->getOffset();
5951  data.opUnlink(op);
5952  op = lone;
5953  data.opSetOpcode(op,CPUI_SUBPIECE);
5954  opc = opc2;
5955  }
5956  }
5957  }
5958  }
5959  // Create shift BEFORE the SUBPIECE happens
5960  Datatype *ct;
5961  if (opc == CPUI_INT_RIGHT)
5962  ct = data.getArch()->types->getBase(a->getSize(),TYPE_UINT);
5963  else
5964  ct = data.getArch()->types->getBase(a->getSize(),TYPE_INT);
5965  PcodeOp *shiftop = data.newOp(2,op->getAddr());
5966  data.opSetOpcode(shiftop,opc);
5967  Varnode *newout = data.newUnique(a->getSize(),ct);
5968  data.opSetOutput(shiftop,newout);
5969  data.opSetInput(shiftop,a,0);
5970  data.opSetInput(shiftop,data.newConstant(4,d),1);
5971  data.opInsertBefore(shiftop,op);
5972 
5973  // Change SUBPIECE into a least sig SUBPIECE
5974  data.opSetInput(op,newout,0);
5975  data.opSetInput(op,data.newConstant(4,0),1);
5976  return 1;
5977 }
5978 
5989 bool RulePtrsubCharConstant::pushConstFurther(Funcdata &data,TypePointer *outtype,PcodeOp *op,int4 slot,uintb val)
5990 
5991 {
5992  if (op->code() != CPUI_PTRADD) return false; // Must be a PTRADD
5993  if (slot != 0) return false;
5994  Varnode *vn = op->getIn(1);
5995  if (!vn->isConstant()) return false; // that is adding a constant
5996  uintb addval = vn->getOffset();
5997  if (addval > 128) return false; // Sanity check on string size
5998  addval *= op->getIn(2)->getOffset();
5999  val += addval;
6000  Varnode *newconst = data.newConstant(vn->getSize(),val);
6001  newconst->updateType(outtype,false,false); // Put the pointer datatype on new constant
6002  data.opRemoveInput(op,2);
6003  data.opRemoveInput(op,1);
6004  data.opSetOpcode(op,CPUI_COPY);
6005  data.opSetInput(op,newconst,0);
6006  return true;
6007 }
6008 
6015 void RulePtrsubCharConstant::getOpList(vector<uint4> &oplist) const
6016 
6017 {
6018  oplist.push_back(CPUI_PTRSUB);
6019 }
6020 
6021 int4 RulePtrsubCharConstant::applyOp(PcodeOp *op,Funcdata &data)
6022 
6023 {
6024  Varnode *sb = op->getIn(0);
6025  if (sb->getType()->getMetatype() != TYPE_PTR) return 0;
6026  TypeSpacebase *sbtype = (TypeSpacebase *)((TypePointer *)sb->getType())->getPtrTo();
6027  if (sbtype->getMetatype() != TYPE_SPACEBASE) return 0;
6028  Varnode *vn1 = op->getIn(1);
6029  if (!vn1->isConstant()) return 0;
6030  Varnode *outvn = op->getOut();
6031  TypePointer *outtype = (TypePointer *)outvn->getType();
6032  if (outtype->getMetatype() != TYPE_PTR) return 0;
6033  Datatype *basetype = outtype->getPtrTo();
6034  if (!basetype->isCharPrint()) return 0;
6035  Address symaddr = sbtype->getAddress(vn1->getOffset(),vn1->getSize(),op->getAddr());
6036  Scope *scope = sbtype->getMap();
6037  if (!scope->isReadOnly(symaddr,1,op->getAddr()))
6038  return 0;
6039  // Check if data at the address looks like a string
6040  uint1 buffer[128];
6041  try {
6042  data.getArch()->loader->loadFill(buffer,128,symaddr);
6043  } catch(DataUnavailError &err) {
6044  return 0;
6045  }
6046  bool isstring = data.getArch()->print->isCharacterConstant(buffer,128,basetype->getSize());
6047  if (!isstring) return 0;
6048 
6049  // If we reach here, the PTRSUB should be converted to a (COPY of a) pointer constant.
6050  list<PcodeOp *>::const_iterator iter,enditer;
6051  iter = outvn->beginDescend();
6052  enditer = outvn->endDescend();
6053  bool removeCopy = true;
6054  while(iter != enditer) {
6055  PcodeOp *subop = *iter; // Give each descendant of op a chance to further propagate the constant
6056  ++iter;
6057  if (!pushConstFurther(data,outtype,subop,subop->getSlot(outvn),vn1->getOffset()))
6058  removeCopy = false; // If the descendant does NOT propagate const, do NOT remove op
6059  }
6060  if (removeCopy) {
6061  data.opDestroy(op);
6062  }
6063  else { // Convert the original PTRSUB to a COPY of the constant
6064  Varnode *newvn = data.newConstant(outvn->getSize(),vn1->getOffset());
6065  newvn->updateType(outtype,false,false);
6066  data.opRemoveInput(op,1);
6067  data.opSetInput(op,newvn,0);
6068  data.opSetOpcode(op,CPUI_COPY);
6069  }
6070  return 1;
6071 }

6078 void RuleSubNormal::getOpList(vector<uint4> &oplist) const
6079 
6080 {
6081  oplist.push_back(CPUI_SUBPIECE);
6082 }
6083 
6084 int4 RuleSubNormal::applyOp(PcodeOp *op,Funcdata &data)
6085 
6086 {
6087  Varnode *shiftout = op->getIn(0);
6088  if (!shiftout->isWritten()) return 0;
6089  PcodeOp *shiftop = shiftout->getDef();
6090  OpCode opc = shiftop->code();
6091  if ((opc!=CPUI_INT_RIGHT)&&(opc!=CPUI_INT_SRIGHT))
6092  return 0;
6093  if (!shiftop->getIn(1)->isConstant()) return 0;
6094  Varnode *a = shiftop->getIn(0);
6095  if (a->isFree()) return 0;
6096  int4 n = shiftop->getIn(1)->getOffset();
6097  int4 c = op->getIn(1)->getOffset();
6098  int4 k = (n/8);
6099  int4 outsize = op->getOut()->getSize();
6100  // If totalcut + remain > original input, shrink cut
6101  if (k+c+outsize > shiftout->getSize())
6102  k = shiftout->getSize()-c-outsize;
6103 
6104  // Total shift + outsize must be greater equal to size of input
6105  if ((n+8*c+8*outsize < 8*a->getSize())&&(n != k*8)) return 0;
6106  // if n == k*8, then a shift is unnecessary
6107  c += k;
6108  n -= k*8;
6109  if (n==0) { // Extra shift is unnecessary
6110  data.opSetInput(op,a,0);
6111  data.opSetInput(op,data.newConstant(4,c),1);
6112  return 1;
6113  }
6114 
6115  PcodeOp *newop = data.newOp(2,op->getAddr());
6116  data.opSetOpcode(newop,CPUI_SUBPIECE);
6117  data.newUniqueOut(op->getOut()->getSize(),newop);
6118  data.opSetInput(newop,a,0);
6119  data.opSetInput(newop,data.newConstant(4,c),1);
6120  data.opInsertBefore(newop,op);
6121 
6122  data.opSetInput(op,newop->getOut(),0);
6123  data.opSetInput(op,data.newConstant(4,n),1);
6124  data.opSetOpcode(op,opc);
6125  return 1;
6126 }
