6136 void RuleDivTermAdd::getOpList(vector<uint4> &oplist) const
6137 
6138 {
6139  oplist.push_back(CPUI_SUBPIECE);
6140  oplist.push_back(CPUI_INT_RIGHT); // added
6141  oplist.push_back(CPUI_INT_SRIGHT); // added
6142 }
6143 
6144 int4 RuleDivTermAdd::applyOp(PcodeOp *op,Funcdata &data)
6145 
6146 {
6147  int4 n;
6148  OpCode shiftopc;
6149  PcodeOp *subop = RuleDivOpt::findSubshift(op,n,shiftopc);
6150  if (subop == (PcodeOp *)0) return 0;
6151  // TODO: Cannot currently support 128-bit arithmetic, except in special case of 2^64
6152  if (n > 64) return 0;
6153 
6154  Varnode *multvn = subop->getIn(0);
6155  if (!multvn->isWritten()) return 0;
6156  PcodeOp *multop = multvn->getDef();
6157  if (multop->code() != CPUI_INT_MULT) return 0;
6158  uintb multConst;
6159  int4 constExtType = multop->getIn(1)->isConstantExtended(multConst);
6160  if (constExtType < 0) return 0;
6161 
6162  Varnode *extvn = multop->getIn(0);
6163  if (!extvn->isWritten()) return 0;
6164  PcodeOp *extop = extvn->getDef();
6165  OpCode opc = extop->code();
6166  if (opc == CPUI_INT_ZEXT) {
6167  if (op->code()==CPUI_INT_SRIGHT) return 0;
6168  }
6169  else if (opc == CPUI_INT_SEXT) {
6170  if (op->code()==CPUI_INT_RIGHT) return 0;
6171  }
6172 
6173  uintb newc;
6174  if (n < 64 || (extvn->getSize() <= 8)) {
6175  uintb pow = 1;
6176  pow <<= n; // Calculate 2^n
6177  newc = multConst + pow;
6178  }
6179  else {
6180  if (constExtType != 2) return 0; // TODO: Can't currently represent
6181  if (!signbit_negative(multConst,8)) return 0;
6182  // Adding 2^64 to a sign-extended 64-bit value with its sign set, causes all the
6183  // set extension bits to be cancelled out, converting it into a
6184  // zero-extended 64-bit value.
6185  constExtType = 1; // Set extension of constant to INT_ZEXT
6186  }
6187  Varnode *x = extop->getIn(0);
6188 
6189  list<PcodeOp *>::const_iterator iter;
6190  for(iter=op->getOut()->beginDescend();iter!=op->getOut()->endDescend();++iter) {
6191  PcodeOp *addop = *iter;
6192  if (addop->code() != CPUI_INT_ADD) continue;
6193  if ((addop->getIn(0)!=x)&&(addop->getIn(1)!=x))
6194  continue;
6195 
6196  // Construct the new constant
6197  Varnode *newConstVn;
6198  if (constExtType == 0)
6199  newConstVn = data.newConstant(extvn->getSize(),newc);
6200  else {
6201  // Create new extension of the constant
6202  PcodeOp *newExtOp = data.newOp(1,op->getAddr());
6203  data.opSetOpcode(newExtOp,(constExtType==1) ? CPUI_INT_ZEXT : CPUI_INT_SEXT);
6204  newConstVn = data.newUniqueOut(extvn->getSize(),newExtOp);
6205  data.opSetInput(newExtOp,data.newConstant(8,multConst),0);
6206  data.opInsertBefore(newExtOp,op);
6207  }
6208 
6209  // Construct the new multiply
6210  PcodeOp *newmultop = data.newOp(2,op->getAddr());
6211  data.opSetOpcode(newmultop,CPUI_INT_MULT);
6212  Varnode *newmultvn = data.newUniqueOut(extvn->getSize(),newmultop);
6213  data.opSetInput(newmultop,extvn,0);
6214  data.opSetInput(newmultop,newConstVn,1);
6215  data.opInsertBefore(newmultop,op);
6216 
6217  PcodeOp *newshiftop = data.newOp(2,op->getAddr());
6218  if (shiftopc == CPUI_MAX)
6219  shiftopc = CPUI_INT_RIGHT;
6220  data.opSetOpcode(newshiftop,shiftopc);
6221  Varnode *newshiftvn = data.newUniqueOut(extvn->getSize(),newshiftop);
6222  data.opSetInput(newshiftop,newmultvn,0);
6223  data.opSetInput(newshiftop,data.newConstant(4,n),1);
6224  data.opInsertBefore(newshiftop,op);
6225 
6226  data.opSetOpcode(addop,CPUI_SUBPIECE);
6227  data.opSetInput(addop,newshiftvn,0);
6228  data.opSetInput(addop,data.newConstant(4,0),1);
6229  return 1;
6230  }
6231  return 0;
6232 }
6233 
6242 void RuleDivTermAdd2::getOpList(vector<uint4> &oplist) const
6243 
6244 {
6245  oplist.push_back(CPUI_INT_RIGHT);
6246 }
6247 
6248 int4 RuleDivTermAdd2::applyOp(PcodeOp *op,Funcdata &data)
6249 
6250 {
6251  if (!op->getIn(1)->isConstant()) return 0;
6252  if (op->getIn(1)->getOffset() != 1) return 0;
6253  if (!op->getIn(0)->isWritten()) return 0;
6254  PcodeOp *subop = op->getIn(0)->getDef();
6255  if (subop->code() != CPUI_INT_ADD) return 0;
6256  Varnode *x = (Varnode *)0;
6257  Varnode *compvn;
6258  PcodeOp *compop;
6259  int4 i;
6260  for(i=0;i<2;++i) {
6261  compvn = subop->getIn(i);
6262  if (compvn->isWritten()) {
6263  compop = compvn->getDef();
6264  if (compop->code() == CPUI_INT_MULT) {
6265  Varnode *invn = compop->getIn(1);
6266  if (invn->isConstant()) {
6267  if (invn->getOffset() == calc_mask(invn->getSize())) {
6268  x = subop->getIn(1-i);
6269  break;
6270  }
6271  }
6272  }
6273  }
6274  }
6275  if (i==2) return 0;
6276  Varnode *z = compvn->getDef()->getIn(0);
6277  if (!z->isWritten()) return 0;
6278  PcodeOp *subpieceop = z->getDef();
6279  if (subpieceop->code() != CPUI_SUBPIECE) return 0;
6280  int4 n = subpieceop->getIn(1)->getOffset() *8;
6281  if (n!= 8*(subpieceop->getIn(0)->getSize() - z->getSize())) return 0;
6282  Varnode *multvn = subpieceop->getIn(0);
6283  if (!multvn->isWritten()) return 0;
6284  PcodeOp *multop = multvn->getDef();
6285  if (multop->code() != CPUI_INT_MULT) return 0;
6286  if (!multop->getIn(1)->isConstant()) return 0;
6287  Varnode *zextvn = multop->getIn(0);
6288  if (!zextvn->isWritten()) return 0;
6289  PcodeOp *zextop = zextvn->getDef();
6290  if (zextop->code() != CPUI_INT_ZEXT) return 0;
6291  if (zextop->getIn(0) != x) return 0;
6292 
6293  list<PcodeOp *>::const_iterator iter;
6294  for(iter=op->getOut()->beginDescend();iter!=op->getOut()->endDescend();++iter) {
6295  PcodeOp *addop = *iter;
6296  if (addop->code() != CPUI_INT_ADD) continue;
6297  if ((addop->getIn(0)!=z)&&(addop->getIn(1)!=z)) continue;
6298 
6299  uintb pow = 1;
6300  pow <<= n; // Calculate 2^n
6301  uintb newc = multop->getIn(1)->getOffset() + pow;
6302  PcodeOp *newmultop = data.newOp(2,op->getAddr());
6303  data.opSetOpcode(newmultop,CPUI_INT_MULT);
6304  Varnode *newmultvn = data.newUniqueOut(zextvn->getSize(),newmultop);
6305  data.opSetInput(newmultop,zextvn,0);
6306  data.opSetInput(newmultop,data.newConstant(zextvn->getSize(),newc),1);
6307  data.opInsertBefore(newmultop,op);
6308 
6309  PcodeOp *newshiftop = data.newOp(2,op->getAddr());
6310  data.opSetOpcode(newshiftop,CPUI_INT_RIGHT);
6311  Varnode *newshiftvn = data.newUniqueOut(zextvn->getSize(),newshiftop);
6312  data.opSetInput(newshiftop,newmultvn,0);
6313  data.opSetInput(newshiftop,data.newConstant(4,n+1),1);
6314  data.opInsertBefore(newshiftop,op);
6315 
6316  data.opSetOpcode(addop,CPUI_SUBPIECE);
6317  data.opSetInput(addop,newshiftvn,0);
6318  data.opSetInput(addop,data.newConstant(4,0),1);
6319  return 1;
6320  }
6321  return 0;
6322 }
6323 
6335 PcodeOp *RuleDivOpt::findSubshift(PcodeOp *op,int4 &n,OpCode &shiftopc)
6336 
6337 { // SUB( .,#c) or SUB(.,#c)>>n return baseop and n+c*8
6338  // make SUB is high
6339  PcodeOp *subop;
6340  shiftopc = op->code();
6341  if (shiftopc != CPUI_SUBPIECE) { // Must be right shift
6342  Varnode *vn = op->getIn(0);
6343  if (!vn->isWritten()) return (PcodeOp *)0;
6344  subop = vn->getDef();
6345  if (subop->code() != CPUI_SUBPIECE) return (PcodeOp *)0;
6346  if (!op->getIn(1)->isConstant()) return (PcodeOp *)0;
6347  n = op->getIn(1)->getOffset();
6348  }
6349  else {
6350  shiftopc = CPUI_MAX; // Indicate there was no shift
6351  subop = op;
6352  n = 0;
6353  }
6354  int4 c = subop->getIn(1)->getOffset();
6355  if (subop->getOut()->getSize() + c != subop->getIn(0)->getSize())
6356  return (PcodeOp *)0; // SUB is not high
6357  n += 8*c;
6358 
6359  return subop;
6360 }
6361 
6374 uintb RuleDivOpt::calcDivisor(uintb n,uint8 y,int4 xsize)
6375 
6376 {
6377  if (n > 127) return 0; // Not enough precision
6378  if (y <= 1) return 0; // Boundary cases are wrong form
6379 
6380  uint8 d,r;
6381  uint8 power;
6382  if (n < 64) {
6383  power = ((uint8)1) << n;
6384  d = power / (y-1);
6385  r = power % (y-1);
6386  }
6387  else {
6388  if (0 != power2Divide(n,y-1,d,r))
6389  return 0; // Result is bigger than 64-bits
6390  }
6391  if (d>=y) return 0;
6392  if (r >= d) return 0;
6393  // The optimization of division to multiplication
6394  // by the reciprocal holds true, if the maximum value
6395  // of x times the remainder is less than 2^n
6396  uint8 maxx = 1;
6397  maxx <<= xsize;
6398  maxx -= 1; // Maximum possible x value
6399  uint8 tmp;
6400  if (n < 64)
6401  tmp = power / (d-r); // r < d => divisor is non-zero
6402  else {
6403  uint8 unused;
6404  if (0 != power2Divide(n,d-r,tmp,unused))
6405  return (uintb)d; // tmp is bigger than 2^64 > maxx
6406  }
6407  if (tmp<=maxx) return 0;
6408  return (uintb)d;
6409 }
6410 
6417 void RuleDivOpt::getOpList(vector<uint4> &oplist) const
6418 
6419 {
6420  oplist.push_back(CPUI_SUBPIECE);
6421  oplist.push_back(CPUI_INT_RIGHT);
6422  oplist.push_back(CPUI_INT_SRIGHT);
6423 }
6424 
6425 int4 RuleDivOpt::applyOp(PcodeOp *op,Funcdata &data)
6426 
6427 {
6428  PcodeOp *subop,*extop,*multop;
6429  Varnode *subin,*xvn;
6430 
6431  int4 nint;
6432  OpCode opc;
6433  subop = findSubshift(op,nint,opc);
6434  if (subop == (PcodeOp *)0) return 0;
6435  if (!subop->getIn(0)->isWritten()) return 0;
6436  multop = subop->getIn(0)->getDef();
6437  if (multop->code() != CPUI_INT_MULT) return 0;
6438  uintb y;
6439  if (multop->getIn(1)->isConstantExtended(y) < 0) return 0;
6440  if (!multop->getIn(0)->isWritten()) return 0;
6441  uintb n = nint;
6442  extop = multop->getIn(0)->getDef();
6443  OpCode extopc = extop->code();
6444  if ((extopc != CPUI_INT_ZEXT)&&(extopc != CPUI_INT_SEXT))
6445  return 0;
6446  xvn = extop->getIn(0);
6447  if (xvn->isFree()) return 0;
6448  int4 xsize = xvn->getSize();
6449  subin = op->getOut();
6450  bool needInputExtension = false;
6451  if (xsize != subin->getSize()) {
6452  if (xsize > subin->getSize()) // Allow input to be smaller than eventual result
6453  return 0;
6454  needInputExtension = true;
6455  xsize = subin->getSize();
6456  }
6457  // Check for signed mismatch
6458  if (((extopc == CPUI_INT_ZEXT)&&(opc==CPUI_INT_SRIGHT))||
6459  ((extopc == CPUI_INT_SEXT)&&(opc==CPUI_INT_RIGHT))) {
6460  if (8*subin->getSize() - n != xsize*8)
6461  return 0;
6462  // op's signedness does not matter because all the extension
6463  // bits are truncated
6464  }
6465 
6466  int4 maxx = xsize * 8;
6467  if (extopc == CPUI_INT_SEXT)
6468  maxx -= 1; // one less bit for signed, because of signbit
6469  uintb divisor = calcDivisor(n,y,maxx);
6470  if (divisor == 0) return 0;
6471  if (needInputExtension) { // Do we need an extension to get to final size
6472  PcodeOp *inExt = data.newOp(1,op->getAddr());
6473  data.opSetOpcode(inExt,extopc);
6474  Varnode *extOut = data.newUniqueOut(xsize,inExt);
6475  data.opSetInput(inExt,xvn,0);
6476  xvn = extOut;
6477  data.opInsertBefore(inExt,op);
6478  }
6479  if (extopc == CPUI_INT_ZEXT) { // Unsigned division
6480  data.opSetInput(op,xvn,0);
6481  data.opSetInput(op,data.newConstant(xsize,divisor),1);
6482  data.opSetOpcode(op,CPUI_INT_DIV);
6483  }
6484  else { // Sign division
6485  PcodeOp *divop = data.newOp(2,op->getAddr());
6486  data.opSetOpcode(divop,CPUI_INT_SDIV);
6487  Varnode *newout = data.newUniqueOut(xsize,divop);
6488  data.opSetInput(divop,xvn,0);
6489  data.opSetInput(divop,data.newConstant(xsize,divisor),1);
6490  data.opInsertBefore(divop,op);
6491  // Build the sign value correction
6492  PcodeOp *sgnop = data.newOp(2,op->getAddr());
6493  data.opSetOpcode(sgnop,CPUI_INT_SRIGHT);
6494  Varnode *sgnvn = data.newUniqueOut(xvn->getSize(),sgnop);
6495  data.opSetInput(sgnop,xvn,0);
6496  data.opSetInput(sgnop,data.newConstant(xvn->getSize(),xsize*8-1),1);
6497  data.opInsertBefore(sgnop,op);
6498  // Add the correction into the division op
6499  data.opSetInput(op,newout,0);
6500  data.opSetInput(op,sgnvn,1);
6501  data.opSetOpcode(op,CPUI_INT_ADD);
6502  }
6503  return 1;
6504 }
6505

6509 
6510 {
6511  oplist.push_back(CPUI_INT_SRIGHT);

6514 int4 RuleSignDiv2::applyOp(PcodeOp *op,Funcdata &data)
6515 
6516 {
6517  Varnode *addout,*multout,*shiftout,*a;
6518  PcodeOp *addop,*multop,*shiftop;
6519 
6520  if (!op->getIn(1)->isConstant()) return 0;
6521  if (op->getIn(1)->getOffset() != 1) return 0;
6522  addout = op->getIn(0);
6523  if (!addout->isWritten()) return 0;
6524  addop = addout->getDef();
6525  if (addop->code() != CPUI_INT_ADD) return 0;
6526  int4 i;
6527  a = (Varnode *)0;
6528  for(i=0;i<2;++i) {
6529  multout = addop->getIn(i);
6530  if (!multout->isWritten()) continue;
6531  multop = multout->getDef();
6532  if (multop->code() != CPUI_INT_MULT)
6533  continue;
6534  if (!multop->getIn(1)->isConstant()) continue;
6535  if (multop->getIn(1)->getOffset() !=
6536  calc_mask(multop->getIn(1)->getSize()))
6537  continue;
6538  shiftout = multop->getIn(0);
6539  if (!shiftout->isWritten()) continue;

6541  if (shiftop->code() != CPUI_INT_SRIGHT)
6542  continue;
6543  if (!shiftop->getIn(1)->isConstant()) continue;
6544  int4 n = shiftop->getIn(1)->getOffset();
6545  a = shiftop->getIn(0);
6546  if (a != addop->getIn(1-i)) continue;
6547  if (n != 8*a->getSize() - 1) continue;
6548  if (a->isFree()) continue;
6549  break;
6550  }
6551  if (i==2) return 0;
6552 
6553  data.opSetInput(op,a,0);
6554  data.opSetInput(op,data.newConstant(a->getSize(),2),1);
6555  data.opSetOpcode(op,CPUI_INT_SDIV);

6598 int4 RuleSignNearMult::applyOp(PcodeOp *op,Funcdata &data)
6599 
6600 {
6601  if (!op->getIn(1)->isConstant()) return 0;
6602  if (!op->getIn(0)->isWritten()) return 0;
6603  PcodeOp *addop = op->getIn(0)->getDef();
6604  if (addop->code() != CPUI_INT_ADD) return 0;
6605  Varnode *shiftvn;
6606  PcodeOp *unshiftop = (PcodeOp *)0;
6607  int4 i;
6608  for(i=0;i<2;++i) {
6609  shiftvn = addop->getIn(i);
6610  if (!shiftvn->isWritten()) continue;
6611  unshiftop = shiftvn->getDef();
6612  if (unshiftop->code() == CPUI_INT_RIGHT) {
6613  if (!unshiftop->getIn(1)->isConstant()) continue;
6614  break;
6615  }
6616  }
6617  if (i==2) return 0;
6618  Varnode *x = addop->getIn(1-i);
6619  if (x->isFree()) return 0;
6620  int4 n = unshiftop->getIn(1)->getOffset();
6621  if (n<=0) return 0;
6622  n = shiftvn->getSize()*8 - n;
6623  if (n<=0) return 0;
6624  uintb mask = calc_mask(shiftvn->getSize());
6625  mask = (mask<<n)&mask;
6626  if (mask != op->getIn(1)->getOffset()) return 0;
6627  Varnode *sgnvn = unshiftop->getIn(0);
6628  if (!sgnvn->isWritten()) return 0;
6629  PcodeOp *sshiftop = sgnvn->getDef();
6630  if (sshiftop->code() != CPUI_INT_SRIGHT) return 0;
6631  if (!sshiftop->getIn(1)->isConstant()) return 0;
6632  if (sshiftop->getIn(0) != x) return 0;
6633  int4 val = sshiftop->getIn(1)->getOffset();
6634  if (val != 8*x->getSize()-1) return 0;
6635 
6636  uintb pow = 1;
6637  pow <<= n;
6638  PcodeOp *newdiv = data.newOp(2,op->getAddr());
6639  data.opSetOpcode(newdiv,CPUI_INT_SDIV);
6640  Varnode *divvn = data.newUniqueOut(x->getSize(),newdiv);
6641  data.opSetInput(newdiv,x,0);
6642  data.opSetInput(newdiv,data.newConstant(x->getSize(),pow),1);
6643  data.opInsertBefore(newdiv,op);
6644 
6645  data.opSetOpcode(op,CPUI_INT_MULT);
6646  data.opSetInput(op,divvn,0);
6647  data.opSetInput(op,data.newConstant(x->getSize(),pow),1);
6648  return 1;
6649 }

6653 void RuleModOpt::getOpList(vector<uint4> &oplist) const
6654 
6655 {

6657  oplist.push_back(CPUI_INT_SDIV);
6658 }
6659 
6660 int4 RuleModOpt::applyOp(PcodeOp *op,Funcdata &data)
6661 
6662 {
6663  PcodeOp *multop,*addop;
6664  Varnode *div,*x,*outvn,*outvn2,*div2;
6665  list<PcodeOp *>::const_iterator iter1,iter2;
6666 
6667  x = op->getIn(0);
6668  div = op->getIn(1);
6669  outvn = op->getOut();
6670  for(iter1=outvn->beginDescend();iter1!=outvn->endDescend();++iter1) {
6671  multop = *iter1;
6672  if (multop->code() != CPUI_INT_MULT) continue;
6673  div2 = multop->getIn(1);
6674  if (div2 == outvn)
6675  div2 = multop->getIn(0);
6676  // Check that div is 2's complement of div2
6677  if (div2->isConstant()) {
6678  if (!div->isConstant()) continue;
6679  uintb mask = calc_mask(div2->getSize());
6680  if ((((div2->getOffset() ^ mask)+1)&mask) != div->getOffset())
6681  continue;
6682  }
6683  else {
6684  if (!div2->isWritten()) continue;
6685  if (div2->getDef()->code() != CPUI_INT_2COMP) continue;
6686  if (div2->getDef()->getIn(0) != div) continue;
6687  }
6688  outvn2 = multop->getOut();
6689  for(iter2=outvn2->beginDescend();iter2!=outvn2->endDescend();++iter2) {
6690  addop = *iter2;
6691  if (addop->code() != CPUI_INT_ADD) continue;
6692  Varnode *lvn;
6693  lvn = addop->getIn(0);
6694  if (lvn == outvn2)
6695  lvn = addop->getIn(1);
6696  if (lvn != x) continue;
6697  data.opSetInput(addop,x,0);
6698  if (div->isConstant())
6699  data.opSetInput(addop,data.newConstant(div->getSize(),div->getOffset()),1);
6700  else
6701  data.opSetInput(addop,div,1);
6702  if (op->code() == CPUI_INT_DIV) // Remainder of proper signedness
6703  data.opSetOpcode(addop,CPUI_INT_REM);
6704  else
6705  data.opSetOpcode(addop,CPUI_INT_SREM);
6706  return 1;
6707  }
6708  }
6709  return 0;
6710 }

6719 
6720 int4 RuleSegment::applyOp(PcodeOp *op,Funcdata &data)
6721 
6722 {
6723  SegmentOp *segdef = data.getArch()->userops.getSegmentOp(Address::getSpaceFromConst(op->getIn(0)->getAddr())->getIndex());
6724  if (segdef == (SegmentOp *)0)
6725  throw LowlevelError("Segment operand missing definition");
6726 
6727  Varnode *vn1 = op->getIn(1);
6728  Varnode *vn2 = op->getIn(2);
6729 
6730  if (vn1->isConstant() && vn2->isConstant()) {
6731  vector<uintb> bindlist;
6732  bindlist.push_back(vn2->getOffset());
6733  bindlist.push_back(vn1->getOffset());
6734  uintb val = segdef->execute(bindlist);
6735  data.opRemoveInput(op,2);
6736  data.opRemoveInput(op,1);
6737  data.opSetInput(op,data.newConstant(op->getOut()->getSize(),val),0);
6738  data.opSetOpcode(op,CPUI_COPY);
6739  return 1;
6740  }
6741  else if (segdef->hasFarPointerSupport()) {
6742  // If the hi and lo pieces come from a contigouous source
6743  if (!contiguous_test(vn1,vn2)) return 0;
6744  Varnode *whole = findContiguousWhole(data,vn1,vn2);
6745  if (whole == (Varnode *)0) return 0;
6746  if (whole->isFree()) return 0;
6747  // Use the contiguous source as the whole pointer
6748  data.opRemoveInput(op,2);
6749  data.opRemoveInput(op,1);
6750  data.opSetInput(op,whole,0);
6751  data.opSetOpcode(op,CPUI_COPY);
6752  return 1;
6753  }
6754  return 0;
6755 }
6756 
6759 void RuleSubvarAnd::getOpList(vector<uint4> &oplist) const
6760 
6761 {
6762  oplist.push_back(CPUI_INT_AND);
6763 }
6764 
6765 int4 RuleSubvarAnd::applyOp(PcodeOp *op,Funcdata &data)
6766 
6767 {
6768  if (!op->getIn(1)->isConstant()) return 0;
6769  Varnode *vn = op->getIn(0);
6770  Varnode *outvn = op->getOut();
6771  // if (vn->getSize() != 1) return 0; // Only for bitsize variables
6772  if (outvn->getConsume() != op->getIn(1)->getOffset()) return 0;
6773  if ((outvn->getConsume() & 1)==0) return 0;
6774  uintb cmask;
6775  if (outvn->getConsume() == (uintb)1)
6776  cmask = (uintb)1;
6777  else {
6778  cmask = calc_mask(vn->getSize());
6779  cmask >>=8;
6780  while(cmask != 0) {
6781  if (cmask == outvn->getConsume()) break;
6782  cmask >>=8;
6783  }
6784  }
6785  if (cmask == 0) return 0;
6786  // if (vn->getConsume() == 0) return 0;
6787  // if ((vn->getConsume() & 0xff)==0xff) return 0;
6788  // if (op->getIn(1)->getOffset() != (uintb)1) return 0;
6789  if (op->getOut()->hasNoDescend()) return 0;
6790  SubvariableFlow subflow(&data,vn,cmask,false,false);
6791  if (!subflow.doTrace()) return 0;
6792  subflow.doReplacement();
6793  return 1;
6794 }

6802 }
6803 
6804 int4 RuleSubvarSubpiece::applyOp(PcodeOp *op,Funcdata &data)
6805 
6806 {
6807  Varnode *vn = op->getIn(0);
6808  Varnode *outvn = op->getOut();
6809  uintb mask = calc_mask( outvn->getSize() );
6810  mask <<= 8*((int4)op->getIn(1)->getOffset());
6811  bool aggressive = outvn->isPtrFlow();
6812  if (!aggressive) {
6813  if (mask != vn->getConsume()) return 0;
6814  if (op->getOut()->hasNoDescend()) return 0;
6815  }
6816  SubvariableFlow subflow(&data,vn,mask,aggressive,false);
6817  if (!subflow.doTrace()) return 0;
6818  subflow.doReplacement();
6819  return 1;
6820 }

6834 int4 RuleSplitFlow::applyOp(PcodeOp *op,Funcdata &data)
6835 
6836 {
6837  int4 loSize = (int4)op->getIn(1)->getOffset();
6838  if (loSize == 0) // Make sure SUBPIECE doesn't take least significant part
6839  return 0;
6840  Varnode *vn = op->getIn(0);
6841  if (!vn->isWritten())
6842  return 0;
6843  if (op->getOut()->getSize() + loSize != vn->getSize())
6844  return 0; // Make sure SUBPIECE is taking most significant part
6845  PcodeOp *concatOp = (PcodeOp *)0;
6846  PcodeOp *multiOp = vn->getDef();
6847  while(multiOp->code() == CPUI_INDIRECT) { // PIECE may come through INDIRECT
6848  Varnode *tmpvn = multiOp->getIn(0);
6849  if (!tmpvn->isWritten()) return 0;
6850  multiOp = tmpvn->getDef();
6851  }
6852  if (multiOp->code() == CPUI_PIECE) {
6853  if (vn->getDef() != multiOp)
6854  concatOp = multiOp;
6855  }
6856  else if (multiOp->code() == CPUI_MULTIEQUAL) { // Otherwise PIECE comes through MULTIEQUAL
6857  for(int4 i=0;i<multiOp->numInput();++i) {
6858  Varnode *invn = multiOp->getIn(i);
6859  if (!invn->isWritten()) continue;
6860  PcodeOp *tmpOp = invn->getDef();
6861  if (tmpOp->code() == CPUI_PIECE) {
6862  concatOp = tmpOp;
6863  break;
6864  }
6865  }
6866  }
6867  if (concatOp == (PcodeOp *)0) // Didn't find the concatenate
6868  return 0;
6869  if (concatOp->getIn(1)->getSize() != loSize)
6870  return 0;
6871  SplitFlow splitFlow(&data,vn,loSize);
6872  if (!splitFlow.doTrace()) return 0;
6873  splitFlow.doReplacement();
6874  return 1;
6875 }

6910 bool RulePtrFlow::trialSetPtrFlow(PcodeOp *op)
6911 
6912 {
6913  switch(op->code()) {
6914  case CPUI_COPY:
6915  case CPUI_MULTIEQUAL:
6916  case CPUI_INT_ADD:
6917  case CPUI_INDIRECT:
6918  case CPUI_PTRSUB:
6919  case CPUI_PTRADD:
6920  if (!op->isPtrFlow()) {
6921  op->setPtrFlow();
6922  return true;
6923  }
6924  break;
6925  default:
6926  break;
6927  }
6928  return false;

6935 bool RulePtrFlow::propagateFlowToDef(Varnode *vn)
6936 
6937 {
6938  bool madeChange = false;
6939  if (!vn->isPtrFlow()) {
6940  vn->setPtrFlow();
6941  madeChange = true;
6942  }
6943  if (!vn->isWritten()) return madeChange;
6944  PcodeOp *op = vn->getDef();
6945  if (trialSetPtrFlow(op))
6946  madeChange = true;
6947  return madeChange;

6954 bool RulePtrFlow::propagateFlowToReads(Varnode *vn)
6955 
6956 {
6957  list<PcodeOp *>::const_iterator iter;
6958  bool madeChange = false;
6959  if (!vn->isPtrFlow()) {
6960  vn->setPtrFlow();
6961  madeChange = true;
6962  }
6963  for(iter=vn->beginDescend();iter!=vn->endDescend();++iter) {
6964  PcodeOp *op = *iter;
6965  if (trialSetPtrFlow(op))
6966  madeChange = true;
6967  }
6968  return madeChange;
6969 }

6981 Varnode *RulePtrFlow::truncatePointer(AddrSpace *spc,PcodeOp *op,Varnode *vn,int4 slot,Funcdata &data)
6982 
6983 {
6984  Varnode *newvn;
6985  PcodeOp *truncop = data.newOp(2,op->getAddr());
6986  data.opSetOpcode(truncop,CPUI_SUBPIECE);
6987  data.opSetInput(truncop,data.newConstant(vn->getSize(),0),1);
6988  if (vn->getSpace()->getType() == IPTR_INTERNAL) {
6989  newvn = data.newUniqueOut(spc->getAddrSize(),truncop);
6990  }
6991  else {
6992  Address addr = vn->getAddr();
6993  if (addr.isBigEndian())
6994  addr = addr + (vn->getSize() - spc->getAddrSize());
6995  newvn = data.newVarnodeOut(spc->getAddrSize(),addr,truncop);
6996  }
6997  data.opSetInput(op,newvn,slot);
6998  data.opSetInput(truncop,vn,0);
6999  data.opInsertBefore(truncop,op);
7000  return newvn;
7001 }
7002 
7003 int4 RulePtrFlow::applyOp(PcodeOp *op,Funcdata &data)
7004 
7005 { // Push pointer-ness
7006  Varnode *vn;
7007  AddrSpace *spc;
7008  int4 madeChange = 0;
7009 
7010  switch(op->code()) {
7011  case CPUI_LOAD:
7012  case CPUI_STORE:
7013  vn = op->getIn(1);
7014  spc = Address::getSpaceFromConst(op->getIn(0)->getAddr());
7015  if (vn->getSize() > spc->getAddrSize()) {
7016  vn = truncatePointer(spc,op,vn,1,data);
7017  madeChange = 1;
7018  }
7019  if (propagateFlowToDef(vn))
7020  madeChange = 1;
7021  break;
7022  case CPUI_CALLIND:
7023  case CPUI_BRANCHIND:
7024  vn = op->getIn(0);
7025  spc = data.getArch()->getDefaultSpace();
7026  if (vn->getSize() > spc->getAddrSize()) {
7027  vn = truncatePointer(spc,op,vn,0,data);
7028  madeChange = 1;
7029  }
7030  if (propagateFlowToDef(vn))
7031  madeChange = 1;
7032  break;
7033  case CPUI_NEW:
7034  vn = op->getOut();
7035  if (propagateFlowToReads(vn))
7036  madeChange = 1;
7037  break;
7038  case CPUI_INDIRECT:
7039  if (!op->isPtrFlow()) return 0;
7040  vn = op->getOut();
7041  if (propagateFlowToReads(vn))
7042  madeChange = 1;
7043  vn = op->getIn(0);
7044  if (propagateFlowToDef(vn))
7045  madeChange = 1;
7046  break;
7047  case CPUI_COPY:
7048  case CPUI_PTRSUB:
7049  case CPUI_PTRADD:
7050  if (!op->isPtrFlow()) return 0;
7051  vn = op->getOut();
7052  if (propagateFlowToReads(vn))
7053  madeChange = 1;
7054  vn = op->getIn(0);
7055  if (propagateFlowToDef(vn))
7056  madeChange = 1;
7057  break;
7058  case CPUI_MULTIEQUAL:
7059  case CPUI_INT_ADD:
7060  if (!op->isPtrFlow()) return 0;
7061  vn = op->getOut();
7062  if (propagateFlowToReads(vn))
7063  madeChange = 1;
7064  for(int4 i=0;i<op->numInput();++i) {
7065  vn = op->getIn(i);
7066  if (propagateFlowToDef(vn))
7067  madeChange = 1;
7068  }
7069  break;
7070  default:
7071  break;
7072  }
7073  return madeChange;
7074 }
7075 
7083 void RuleSubvarCompZero::getOpList(vector<uint4> &oplist) const
7084 
7085 {
7086  oplist.push_back(CPUI_INT_NOTEQUAL);
7087  oplist.push_back(CPUI_INT_EQUAL);
7088 }
7089 
7090 int4 RuleSubvarCompZero::applyOp(PcodeOp *op,Funcdata &data)
7091 
7092 {
7093  if (!op->getIn(1)->isConstant()) return 0;
7094  Varnode *vn = op->getIn(0);
7095  uintb mask = vn->getNZMask();
7096  int4 bitnum = leastsigbit_set(mask);
7097  if (bitnum == -1) return 0;
7098  if ((mask >> bitnum) != 1) return 0; // Check if only one bit active
7099 
7100  // Check if the active bit is getting tested
7101  if ((op->getIn(1)->getOffset()!=mask)&&
7102  (op->getIn(1)->getOffset()!=0))
7103  return 0;
7104 
7105  if (op->getOut()->hasNoDescend()) return 0;
7106  // We do a basic check that the stream from which it looks like
7107  // the bit is getting pulled is not fully consumed
7108  if (vn->isWritten()) {
7109  PcodeOp *andop = vn->getDef();
7110  if (andop->numInput()==0) return 0;
7111  Varnode *vn0 = andop->getIn(0);
7112  switch(andop->code()) {
7113  case CPUI_INT_AND:
7114  case CPUI_INT_OR:
7115  case CPUI_INT_RIGHT:
7116  {
7117  if (vn0->isConstant()) return 0;
7118  uintb mask0 = vn0->getConsume() & vn0->getNZMask();
7119  uintb wholemask = calc_mask(vn0->getSize()) & mask0;
7120  // We really need a popcnt here
7121  // We want: if the number of bits that are both consumed
7122  // and not known to be zero are "big" then don't continue
7123  // because it doesn't look like a few bits getting manipulated
7124  // within a status register
7125  if ((wholemask & 0xff)==0xff) return 0;
7126  if ((wholemask & 0xff00)==0xff00) return 0;
7127  }
7128  break;
7129  default:
7130  break;
7131  }
7132  }
7133 
7134  SubvariableFlow subflow(&data,vn,mask,false,false);
7135  if (!subflow.doTrace()) {
7136  return 0;
7137  }
7138  subflow.doReplacement();
7139  return 1;
7140 }
7141 
7148 void RuleSubvarShift::getOpList(vector<uint4> &oplist) const
7149 
7150 {
7151  oplist.push_back(CPUI_INT_RIGHT);
7152 }
7153 
7154 int4 RuleSubvarShift::applyOp(PcodeOp *op,Funcdata &data)
7155 
7156 {
7157  Varnode *vn = op->getIn(0);
7158  if (vn->getSize() != 1) return 0;
7159  if (!op->getIn(1)->isConstant()) return 0;
7160  int4 sa = (int4)op->getIn(1)->getOffset();
7161  uintb mask = vn->getNZMask();
7162  if ((mask >> sa) != (uintb)1) return 0; // Pulling out a single bit
7163  mask = (mask >> sa) << sa;
7164  if (op->getOut()->hasNoDescend()) return 0;
7165 
7166  SubvariableFlow subflow(&data,vn,mask,false,false);
7167  if (!subflow.doTrace()) return 0;
7168  subflow.doReplacement();
7169  return 1;
7170 }

7277 bool RuleConditionalMove::BoolExpress::initialize(Varnode *vn)
7278 
7279 {
7280  if (!vn->isWritten()) return false;
7281  op = vn->getDef();
7282  opc = op->code();
7283  switch(opc) {
7284  case CPUI_COPY:
7285  in0 = op->getIn(0);
7286  if (in0->isConstant()) {
7287  optype = 0;
7288  val = in0->getOffset();
7289  return ((val & ~((uintb)1)) == 0);
7290  }
7291  return false;
7292  case CPUI_INT_EQUAL:
7293  case CPUI_INT_NOTEQUAL:
7294  case CPUI_INT_SLESS:
7295  case CPUI_INT_SLESSEQUAL:
7296  case CPUI_INT_LESS:
7297  case CPUI_INT_LESSEQUAL:
7298  case CPUI_INT_CARRY:
7299  case CPUI_INT_SCARRY:
7300  case CPUI_INT_SBORROW:
7301  case CPUI_BOOL_XOR:
7302  case CPUI_BOOL_AND:
7303  case CPUI_BOOL_OR:
7304  case CPUI_FLOAT_EQUAL:
7305  case CPUI_FLOAT_NOTEQUAL:
7306  case CPUI_FLOAT_LESS:
7307  case CPUI_FLOAT_LESSEQUAL:
7308  case CPUI_FLOAT_NAN:
7309  in0 = op->getIn(0);
7310  in1 = op->getIn(1);
7311  optype = 2;
7312  break;
7313  case CPUI_BOOL_NEGATE:
7314  in0 = op->getIn(0);
7315  optype = 1;
7316  break;
7317  default:
7318  return false;
7319  }
7320  return true;
7321 }
7322 
7328 bool RuleConditionalMove::BoolExpress::evaluatePropagation(FlowBlock *root,FlowBlock *branch)
7329 
7330 {
7331  mustreconstruct = false;
7332  if (optype==0) return true; // Constants can always be propagated
7333  if (root == branch) return true; // Can always propagate if there is no branch
7334  if (op->getParent() != branch) return true; // Can propagate if value formed before branch
7335  mustreconstruct = true; // Final op is performed in branch, so it must be reconstructed
7336  if (in0->isFree() && !in0->isConstant()) return false;
7337  if (in0->isWritten() && (in0->getDef()->getParent()==branch)) return false;
7338  if (optype == 2) {
7339  if (in1->isFree() && !in1->isConstant()) return false;
7340  if (in1->isWritten() && (in1->getDef()->getParent()==branch)) return false;
7341  }
7342  return true;
7343 }
7344 
7351 Varnode *RuleConditionalMove::BoolExpress::constructBool(PcodeOp *insertop,Funcdata &data)
7352 
7353 {
7354  Varnode *resvn;
7355  if (mustreconstruct) {
7356  PcodeOp *newop = data.newOp(optype,op->getAddr()); // Keep the original address
7357  data.opSetOpcode(newop, opc );
7358  resvn = data.newUniqueOut(1,newop);
7359  if (in0->isConstant())
7360  in0 = data.newConstant(in0->getSize(),in0->getOffset());
7361  data.opSetInput(newop,in0,0);
7362  if (optype == 2) { // Binary op
7363  if (in1->isConstant())
7364  in1 = data.newConstant(in1->getSize(),in1->getOffset());
7365  data.opSetInput(newop,in1,1);
7366  }
7367  data.opInsertBefore(newop,insertop);
7368  }
7369  else {
7370  if (optype == 0)
7371  resvn = data.newConstant(1,val);
7372  else
7373  resvn = op->getOut();
7374  }
7375  return resvn;
7376 }
7377 
7384 Varnode *RuleConditionalMove::constructNegate(Varnode *vn,PcodeOp *op,Funcdata &data)
7385 
7386 {
7387  PcodeOp *negateop = data.newOp(1,op->getAddr());
7388  data.opSetOpcode(negateop,CPUI_BOOL_NEGATE);
7389  Varnode *resvn = data.newUniqueOut(1,negateop);
7390  data.opSetInput(negateop,vn,0);
7391  data.opInsertBefore(negateop,op);
7392  return resvn;
7393 }
7394 
7418 void RuleConditionalMove::getOpList(vector<uint4> &oplist) const
7419 
7420 {
7421  oplist.push_back(CPUI_MULTIEQUAL);
7422 }
7423 
7424 int4 RuleConditionalMove::applyOp(PcodeOp *op,Funcdata &data)
7425 
7426 {
7427  BoolExpress bool0;
7428  BoolExpress bool1;
7429  BlockBasic *bb;
7430  FlowBlock *inblock0,*inblock1;
7431  FlowBlock *rootblock0,*rootblock1;
7432 
7433  if (op->numInput() != 2) return 0; // MULTIEQUAL must have exactly 2 inputs
7434 
7435  if (!bool0.initialize(op->getIn(0))) return 0;
7436  if (!bool1.initialize(op->getIn(1))) return 0;
7437 
7438  // Look for the situation
7439  // inblock0
7440  // / |
7441  // rootblock -> bb
7442  // | /
7443  // inblock1
7444  //
7445  // Either inblock0 or inblock1 can be empty
7446  bb = op->getParent();
7447  inblock0 = bb->getIn(0);
7448  if (inblock0->sizeOut() == 1) {
7449  if (inblock0->sizeIn() != 1) return 0;
7450  rootblock0 = inblock0->getIn(0);
7451  }
7452  else
7453  rootblock0 = inblock0;
7454  inblock1 = bb->getIn(1);
7455  if (inblock1->sizeOut() == 1) {
7456  if (inblock1->sizeIn() != 1) return 0;
7457  rootblock1 = inblock1->getIn(0);
7458  }
7459  else
7460  rootblock1 = inblock1;
7461  if (rootblock0 != rootblock1) return 0;
7462 
7463  // rootblock must end in CBRANCH, which gives the boolean for the conditional move
7464  PcodeOp *cbranch = rootblock0->lastOp();
7465  if (cbranch == (PcodeOp *)0) return 0;
7466  if (cbranch->code() != CPUI_CBRANCH) return 0;
7467 
7468  if (!bool0.evaluatePropagation(rootblock0,inblock0)) return 0;
7469  if (!bool1.evaluatePropagation(rootblock0,inblock1)) return 0;
7470 
7471  bool path0istrue;
7472  if (rootblock0 != inblock0)
7473  path0istrue = (rootblock0->getTrueOut() == inblock0);
7474  else
7475  path0istrue = (rootblock0->getTrueOut() != inblock1);
7476  if (cbranch->isBooleanFlip())
7477  path0istrue = !path0istrue;
7478 
7479  if (!bool0.isConstant() && !bool1.isConstant()) {
7480  if (inblock0 == rootblock0) {
7481  Varnode *boolvn = cbranch->getIn(1);
7482  bool andorselect = path0istrue;
7483  // Force 0 branch to either be boolvn OR !boolvn
7484  if (boolvn != op->getIn(0)) {
7485  if (!boolvn->isWritten()) return 0;
7486  PcodeOp *negop = boolvn->getDef();
7487  if (negop->code() != CPUI_BOOL_NEGATE) return 0;
7488  if (negop->getIn(0) != op->getIn(0)) return 0;
7489  andorselect = !andorselect;
7490  }
7491  OpCode opc = andorselect ? CPUI_BOOL_OR : CPUI_BOOL_AND;
7492  data.opUninsert( op );
7493  data.opSetOpcode(op, opc);
7494  data.opInsertBegin(op, bb);
7495  Varnode *firstvn = bool0.constructBool(op,data);
7496  Varnode *secondvn = bool1.constructBool(op,data);
7497  data.opSetInput(op,firstvn,0);
7498  data.opSetInput(op,secondvn,1);
7499  return 1;
7500  }
7501  else if (inblock1 == rootblock0) {
7502  Varnode *boolvn = cbranch->getIn(1);
7503  bool andorselect = !path0istrue;
7504  // Force 1 branch to either be boolvn OR !boolvn
7505  if (boolvn != op->getIn(1)) {
7506  if (!boolvn->isWritten()) return 0;
7507  PcodeOp *negop = boolvn->getDef();
7508  if (negop->code() != CPUI_BOOL_NEGATE) return 0;
7509  if (negop->getIn(0) != op->getIn(1)) return 0;
7510  andorselect = !andorselect;
7511  }
7512  data.opUninsert( op );
7513  OpCode opc = andorselect ? CPUI_BOOL_OR : CPUI_BOOL_AND;
7514  data.opSetOpcode(op, opc);
7515  data.opInsertBegin(op, bb);
7516  Varnode *firstvn = bool1.constructBool(op,data);
7517  Varnode *secondvn = bool0.constructBool(op,data);
7518  data.opSetInput(op,firstvn,0);
7519  data.opSetInput(op,secondvn,1);
7520  return 1;
7521  }
7522  return 0;
7523  }
7524 
7525  // Below here some change is being made
7526  data.opUninsert( op ); // Changing from MULTIEQUAL, this should be reinserted
7527  int4 sz = op->getOut()->getSize();
7528  if (bool0.isConstant() && bool1.isConstant()) {
7529  if (bool0.getVal() == bool1.getVal()) {
7530  data.opRemoveInput(op,1);
7531  data.opSetOpcode(op,CPUI_COPY);
7532  data.opSetInput(op, data.newConstant( sz, bool0.getVal() ), 0 );
7533  data.opInsertBegin(op,bb);
7534  }
7535  else {
7536  data.opRemoveInput(op,1);
7537  Varnode *boolvn = cbranch->getIn(1);
7538  bool needcomplement = ( (bool0.getVal()==0) == path0istrue );
7539  if (sz == 1) {
7540  if (needcomplement)
7541  data.opSetOpcode(op,CPUI_BOOL_NEGATE);
7542  else
7543  data.opSetOpcode(op,CPUI_COPY);
7544  data.opInsertBegin(op,bb);
7545  data.opSetInput(op, boolvn, 0);
7546  }
7547  else {
7548  data.opSetOpcode(op,CPUI_INT_ZEXT);
7549  data.opInsertBegin(op,bb);
7550  if (needcomplement)
7551  boolvn = constructNegate(boolvn,op,data);
7552  data.opSetInput(op,boolvn,0);
7553  }
7554  }
7555  }
7556  else if (bool0.isConstant()) {
7557  bool needcomplement = (path0istrue != (bool0.getVal()!=0));
7558  OpCode opc = (bool0.getVal()!=0) ? CPUI_BOOL_OR : CPUI_BOOL_AND;
7559  data.opSetOpcode(op,opc);
7560  data.opInsertBegin(op,bb);
7561  Varnode *boolvn = cbranch->getIn(1);
7562  if (needcomplement)
7563  boolvn = constructNegate(boolvn,op,data);
7564  Varnode *body1 = bool1.constructBool(op,data);
7565  data.opSetInput(op,boolvn,0);
7566  data.opSetInput(op,body1,1);
7567  }
7568  else { // bool1 must be constant
7569  bool needcomplement = (path0istrue == (bool1.getVal()!=0));
7570  OpCode opc = (bool1.getVal()!=0) ? CPUI_BOOL_OR : CPUI_BOOL_AND;
7571  data.opSetOpcode(op,opc);
7572  data.opInsertBegin(op,bb);
7573  Varnode *boolvn = cbranch->getIn(1);
7574  if (needcomplement)
7575  boolvn = constructNegate(boolvn,op,data);
7576  Varnode *body0 = bool0.constructBool(op,data);
7577  data.opSetInput(op,boolvn,0);
7578  data.opSetInput(op,body0,1);
7579  }
7580  return 1;
7581 }

7585 void RuleFloatCast::getOpList(vector<uint4> &oplist) const

7592 int4 RuleFloatCast::applyOp(PcodeOp *op,Funcdata &data)
7593 
7594 {
7595  Varnode *vn1 = op->getIn(0);
7596  if (!vn1->isWritten()) return 0;
7597  PcodeOp *castop = vn1->getDef();
7598  OpCode opc2 = castop->code();
7599  if ((opc2 != CPUI_FLOAT_FLOAT2FLOAT)&&(opc2 != CPUI_FLOAT_INT2FLOAT))
7600  return 0;
7601  OpCode opc1 = op->code();
7602  Varnode *vn2 = castop->getIn(0);
7603  int4 insize1 = vn1->getSize();
7604  int4 insize2 = vn2->getSize();
7605  int4 outsize = op->getOut()->getSize();
7606 
7607  if (vn2->isFree()) return 0; // Don't propagate free
7608 
7609  if ((opc2 == CPUI_FLOAT_FLOAT2FLOAT)&&(opc1 == CPUI_FLOAT_FLOAT2FLOAT)) {
7610  if (insize1 > outsize) { // op is superfluous
7611  data.opSetInput(op,vn2,0);
7612  if (outsize == insize2)
7613  data.opSetOpcode(op,CPUI_COPY); // We really have the identity
7614  return 1;
7615  }
7616  else if (insize2 < insize1) { // Convert two increases -> one combined increase
7617  data.opSetInput(op,vn2,0);
7618  return 1;
7619  }
7620  }
7621  else if ((opc2 == CPUI_FLOAT_INT2FLOAT)&&(opc1 == CPUI_FLOAT_FLOAT2FLOAT)) {
7622  // Convert integer straight into final float size
7623  data.opSetInput(op,vn2,0);
7624  data.opSetOpcode(op,CPUI_FLOAT_INT2FLOAT);
7625  return 1;
7626  }
7627  else if ((opc2 == CPUI_FLOAT_FLOAT2FLOAT)&&(opc1 == CPUI_FLOAT_TRUNC)) {
7628  // Convert float straight into final integer
7629  data.opSetInput(op,vn2,0);
7630  return 1;
7631  }
7632 
7633  return 0;
7634 }

7671 int4 RuleFuncPtrEncoding::applyOp(PcodeOp *op,Funcdata &data)
7672 
7673 {
7674  int4 align = data.getArch()->funcptr_align;
7675  if (align == 0) return 0;
7676  Varnode *vn = op->getIn(0);
7677  if (!vn->isWritten()) return 0;
7678  PcodeOp *andop = vn->getDef();
7679  if (andop->code() != CPUI_INT_AND) return 0;
7680  Varnode *maskvn = andop->getIn(1);
7681  if (!maskvn->isConstant()) return 0;
7682  uintb val = maskvn->getOffset();
7683  uintb testmask = calc_mask(maskvn->getSize());
7684  uintb slide = ~((uintb)0);
7685  slide <<= align;
7686  if ((testmask & slide)==val) { // 1-bit encoding
7687  data.opRemoveInput(andop,1); // Eliminate the mask
7688  data.opSetOpcode(andop,CPUI_COPY);
7689  return 1;
7690  }
7691  return 0;
7692 }

7705 int4 RuleThreeWayCompare::testCompareEquivalence(PcodeOp *lessop,PcodeOp *lessequalop)
7706 
7707 {
7708  bool twoLessThan;
7709  if (lessop->code() == CPUI_INT_LESS) { // Make sure second zext is matching lessequal
7710  if (lessequalop->code() == CPUI_INT_LESSEQUAL)
7711  twoLessThan = false;
7712  else if (lessequalop->code() == CPUI_INT_LESS)
7713  twoLessThan = true;
7714  else
7715  return -1;
7716  }
7717  else if (lessop->code() == CPUI_INT_SLESS) {
7718  if (lessequalop->code() == CPUI_INT_SLESSEQUAL)
7719  twoLessThan = false;
7720  else if (lessequalop->code() == CPUI_INT_SLESS)
7721  twoLessThan = true;
7722  else
7723  return -1;
7724  }
7725  else if (lessop->code() == CPUI_FLOAT_LESS) {
7726  if (lessequalop->code() == CPUI_FLOAT_LESSEQUAL)
7727  twoLessThan = false;
7728  else
7729  return -1; // No partial form for floating-point comparison
7730  }
7731  else
7732  return -1;
7733  Varnode *a1 = lessop->getIn(0);
7734  Varnode *a2 = lessequalop->getIn(0);
7735  Varnode *b1 = lessop->getIn(1);
7736  Varnode *b2 = lessequalop->getIn(1);
7737  int4 res = 0;
7738  if (a1 != a2) { // Make sure a1 and a2 are equivalent
7739  if ((!a1->isConstant())||(!a2->isConstant())) return -1;
7740  if ((a1->getOffset() != a2->getOffset())&&twoLessThan) {
7741  if (a2->getOffset() + 1 == a1->getOffset()) {
7742  twoLessThan = false; // -lessequalop- is LESSTHAN, equivalent to LESSEQUAL
7743  }
7744  else if (a1->getOffset() + 1 == a2->getOffset()) {
7745  twoLessThan = false; // -lessop- is LESSTHAN, equivalent to LESSEQUAL
7746  res = 1; // we need to swap
7747  }
7748  else
7749  return -1;
7750  }
7751  }
7752  if (b1 != b2) { // Make sure b1 and b2 are equivalent
7753  if ((!b1->isConstant())||(!b2->isConstant())) return -1;
7754  if ((b1->getOffset() != b2->getOffset())&&twoLessThan) {
7755  if (b1->getOffset() + 1 == b2->getOffset()) {
7756  twoLessThan = false;
7757  }
7758  else if (b2->getOffset() + 1 == b1->getOffset()) {
7759  twoLessThan = false;
7760  res = 1; // we need to swap
7761  }
7762  }
7763  else
7764  return -1;
7765  }
7766  if (twoLessThan)
7767  return -1; // Did not compensate for two LESSTHANs with differing constants
7768  return res;
7769 }
7770 
7780 PcodeOp *RuleThreeWayCompare::detectThreeWay(PcodeOp *op,bool &isPartial)
7781 
7782 {
7783  Varnode *vn1, *vn2, *tmpvn;
7784  PcodeOp *zext1, *zext2;
7785  PcodeOp *addop, *lessop, *lessequalop;
7786  uintb mask;
7787  vn2 = op->getIn(1);
7788  if (vn2->isConstant()) { // Form 1 : (z + z) - 1
7789  mask = calc_mask(vn2->getSize());
7790  if (mask != vn2->getOffset()) return (PcodeOp *)0; // Match the -1
7791  vn1 = op->getIn(0);
7792  if (!vn1->isWritten()) return (PcodeOp *)0;
7793  addop = vn1->getDef();
7794  if (addop->code() != CPUI_INT_ADD) return (PcodeOp *)0; // Match the add
7795  tmpvn = addop->getIn(0);
7796  if (!tmpvn->isWritten()) return (PcodeOp *)0;
7797  zext1 = tmpvn->getDef();
7798  if (zext1->code() != CPUI_INT_ZEXT) return (PcodeOp *)0; // Match the first zext
7799  tmpvn = addop->getIn(1);
7800  if (!tmpvn->isWritten()) return (PcodeOp *)0;
7801  zext2 = tmpvn->getDef();
7802  if (zext2->code() != CPUI_INT_ZEXT) return (PcodeOp *)0; // Match the second zext
7803  }
7804  else if (vn2->isWritten()) {
7805  PcodeOp *tmpop = vn2->getDef();
7806  if (tmpop->code() == CPUI_INT_ZEXT) { // Form 2 : (z - 1) + z
7807  zext2 = tmpop; // Second zext is already matched
7808  vn1 = op->getIn(0);
7809  if (!vn1->isWritten()) return (PcodeOp *)0;
7810  addop = vn1->getDef();
7811  if (addop->code() != CPUI_INT_ADD) { // Partial form: (z + z)
7812  zext1 = addop;
7813  if (zext1->code() != CPUI_INT_ZEXT)
7814  return (PcodeOp *)0; // Match the first zext
7815  isPartial = true;
7816  }
7817  else {
7818  tmpvn = addop->getIn(1);
7819  if (!tmpvn->isConstant()) return (PcodeOp *)0;
7820  mask = calc_mask(tmpvn->getSize());
7821  if (mask != tmpvn->getOffset()) return (PcodeOp *)0; // Match the -1
7822  tmpvn = addop->getIn(0);
7823  if (!tmpvn->isWritten()) return (PcodeOp *)0;
7824  zext1 = tmpvn->getDef();
7825  if (zext1->code() != CPUI_INT_ZEXT) return (PcodeOp *)0; // Match the first zext
7826  }
7827  }
7828  else if (tmpop->code() == CPUI_INT_ADD) { // Form 3 : z + (z - 1)
7829  addop = tmpop; // Matched the add
7830  vn1 = op->getIn(0);
7831  if (!vn1->isWritten()) return (PcodeOp *)0;
7832  zext1 = vn1->getDef();
7833  if (zext1->code() != CPUI_INT_ZEXT) return (PcodeOp *)0; // Match the first zext
7834  tmpvn = addop->getIn(1);
7835  if (!tmpvn->isConstant()) return (PcodeOp *)0;
7836  mask = calc_mask(tmpvn->getSize());
7837  if (mask != tmpvn->getOffset()) return (PcodeOp *)0; // Match the -1
7838  tmpvn = addop->getIn(0);
7839  if (!tmpvn->isWritten()) return (PcodeOp *)0;
7840  zext2 = tmpvn->getDef();
7841  if (zext2->code() != CPUI_INT_ZEXT) return (PcodeOp *)0; // Match the second zext
7842  }
7843  else
7844  return (PcodeOp *)0;
7845  }
7846  else
7847  return (PcodeOp *)0;
7848  vn1 = zext1->getIn(0);
7849  if (!vn1->isWritten()) return (PcodeOp *)0;
7850  vn2 = zext2->getIn(0);
7851  if (!vn2->isWritten()) return (PcodeOp *)0;
7852  lessop = vn1->getDef();
7853  lessequalop = vn2->getDef();
7854  OpCode opc = lessop->code();
7855  if ((opc != CPUI_INT_LESS)&&(opc != CPUI_INT_SLESS)&&(opc != CPUI_FLOAT_LESS)) { // Make sure first zext is less
7856  PcodeOp *tmpop = lessop;
7857  lessop = lessequalop;
7858  lessequalop = tmpop;
7859  }
7860  int4 form = testCompareEquivalence(lessop,lessequalop);
7861  if (form < 0)
7862  return (PcodeOp *)0;
7863  if (form == 1) {
7864  PcodeOp *tmpop = lessop;
7865  lessop = lessequalop;
7866  lessequalop = tmpop;
7867  }
7868  return lessop;
7869 }

7882 void RuleThreeWayCompare::getOpList(vector<uint4> &oplist) const
7883 
7884 {
7885  oplist.push_back(CPUI_INT_SLESS);
7886  oplist.push_back(CPUI_INT_SLESSEQUAL);
7887  oplist.push_back(CPUI_INT_EQUAL);
7888  oplist.push_back(CPUI_INT_NOTEQUAL);
7889 }
7890 
7891 int4 RuleThreeWayCompare::applyOp(PcodeOp *op,Funcdata &data)
7892 
7893 {
7894  int4 constSlot=0;
7895  int4 form;
7896  Varnode *tmpvn = op->getIn(constSlot);
7897  if (!tmpvn->isConstant()) { // One of the two inputs must be a constant
7898  constSlot = 1;
7899  tmpvn = op->getIn(constSlot);
7900  if (!tmpvn->isConstant()) return 0;
7901  }
7902  uintb val = tmpvn->getOffset(); // Encode const value (-1, 0, 1, 2) as highest 3 bits of form (000, 001, 010, 011)
7903  if (val <= 2)
7904  form = (int)val + 1;
7905  else if (val == calc_mask(tmpvn->getSize()))
7906  form = 0;
7907  else
7908  return 0;
7909 
7910  tmpvn = op->getIn(1-constSlot);
7911  if (!tmpvn->isWritten()) return 0;
7912  if (tmpvn->getDef()->code() != CPUI_INT_ADD) return 0;
7913  bool isPartial = false;
7914  PcodeOp *lessop = detectThreeWay(tmpvn->getDef(),isPartial);
7915  if (lessop == (PcodeOp *)0)
7916  return 0;
7917  if (isPartial) { // Only found a partial three-way
7918  if (form == 0)
7919  return 0; // -1 const value is now out of range
7920  form -= 1; // Subtract 1 (from both sides of equation) to complete the three-way form
7921  }
7922  form <<= 1;
7923  if (constSlot == 1) // Encode const position (0 or 1) as next bit
7924  form += 1;
7925  OpCode lessform = lessop->code(); // Either INT_LESS, INT_SLESS, or FLOAT_LESS
7926  form <<= 2;
7927  if (op->code() == CPUI_INT_SLESSEQUAL)
7928  form += 1;
7929  else if (op->code() == CPUI_INT_EQUAL)
7930  form += 2;
7931  else if (op->code() == CPUI_INT_NOTEQUAL)
7932  form += 3;
7933  // Encode base op (SLESS, SLESSEQUAL, EQUAL, NOTEQUAL) as final 2 bits
7934 
7935  Varnode *bvn = lessop->getIn(0); // First parameter to LESSTHAN is second parameter to cmp3way function
7936  Varnode *avn = lessop->getIn(1); // Second parameter to LESSTHAN is first parameter to cmp3way function
7937  if ((!avn->isConstant())&&(avn->isFree())) return 0;
7938  if ((!bvn->isConstant())&&(bvn->isFree())) return 0;
7939  switch(form) {
7940  case 1: // -1 s<= threeway => always true
7941  case 21: // threeway s<= 1 => always true
7942  data.opSetOpcode(op,CPUI_INT_EQUAL);
7943  data.opSetInput(op,data.newConstant(1,0),0);
7944  data.opSetInput(op,data.newConstant(1,0),1);
7945  break;
7946  case 4: // threeway s< -1 => always false
7947  case 16: // 1 s< threeway => always false
7948  data.opSetOpcode(op,CPUI_INT_NOTEQUAL);
7949  data.opSetInput(op,data.newConstant(1,0),0);
7950  data.opSetInput(op,data.newConstant(1,0),1);
7951  break;
7952  case 2: // -1 == threeway => a < b
7953  case 5: // threeway s<= -1 => a < b
7954  case 6: // threeway == -1 => a < b
7955  case 12: // threeway s< 0 => a < b
7956  data.opSetOpcode(op,lessform);
7957  data.opSetInput(op,avn,0);
7958  data.opSetInput(op,bvn,1);
7959  break;
7960  case 13: // threeway s<= 0 => a <= b
7961  case 19: // 1 != threeway => a <= b
7962  case 20: // threeway s< 1 => a <= b
7963  case 23: // threeway != 1 => a <= b
7964  data.opSetOpcode(op,(OpCode)(lessform+1)); // LESSEQUAL form
7965  data.opSetInput(op,avn,0);
7966  data.opSetInput(op,bvn,1);
7967  break;
7968  case 8: // 0 s< threeway => a > b
7969  case 17: // 1 s<= threeway => a > b
7970  case 18: // 1 == threeway => a > b
7971  case 22: // threeway == 1 => a > b
7972  data.opSetOpcode(op,lessform);
7973  data.opSetInput(op,bvn,0);
7974  data.opSetInput(op,avn,1);
7975  break;
7976  case 0: // -1 s< threeway => a >= b
7977  case 3: // -1 != threeway => a >= b
7978  case 7: // threeway != -1 => a >= b
7979  case 9: // 0 s<= threeway => a >= b
7980  data.opSetOpcode(op,(OpCode)(lessform+1)); // LESSEQUAL form
7981  data.opSetInput(op,bvn,0);
7982  data.opSetInput(op,avn,1);
7983  break;
7984  case 10: // 0 == threeway => a == b
7985  case 14: // threeway == 0 => a == b
7986  if (lessform == CPUI_FLOAT_LESS) // Choose the right equal form
7987  lessform = CPUI_FLOAT_EQUAL; // float form
7988  else
7989  lessform = CPUI_INT_EQUAL; // or integer form
7990  data.opSetOpcode(op,lessform);
7991  data.opSetInput(op,avn,0);
7992  data.opSetInput(op,bvn,1);
7993  break;
7994  case 11: // 0 != threeway => a != b
7995  case 15: // threeway != 0 => a != b
7996  if (lessform == CPUI_FLOAT_LESS) // Choose the right notequal form
7997  lessform = CPUI_FLOAT_NOTEQUAL; // float form
7998  else
7999  lessform = CPUI_INT_NOTEQUAL; // or integer form
8000  data.opSetOpcode(op,lessform);
8001  data.opSetInput(op,avn,0);
8002  data.opSetInput(op,bvn,1);
8003  break;
8004  default:
8005  return 0;
8006  }
8007  return 1;
8008 }
TypePointer
